{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/17803.After_Dark", "title": "After Dark", "titleComplete": "After Dark", "description": "In After Dark\u2014a gripping novel of late night encounters\u2014Murakami\u2019s trademark humor and psychological insight are distilled with an extraordinary, harmonious mastery.Nineteen-year-old Mari is waiting out the night in an anonymous Denny\u2019s when she meets a young man who insists he knows her older sister, thus setting her on an odyssey through the sleeping city. In the space of a single night, the lives of a diverse cast of Tokyo residents\u2014models, prostitutes, mobsters, and musicians\u2014collide in a world suspended between fantasy and reality. Utterly enchanting and infused with surrealism, After Dark is a thrilling account of the magical hours separating midnight from dawn.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1437952316i/17803.jpg", "genres": ["Literary Fiction", "Japan", "Literature", "Japanese Literature", "Fantasy", "Contemporary", "Magical Realism", "Fiction", "Novels", "Asia"], "asin": "0307265838", "isbn": "0307265838", "isbn13": "9780307265838", "publisher": "Knopf", "author": ["Haruki Murakami", "Jay Rubin"], "publishDate": 1178607600000, "characters": ["Mari Asai", "Kaoru", "Takahashi Tetsuya", "Eri Asai", "Shirakawa"], "places": ["Japan", "Tokyo"], "ratingHistogram": [1821, 10148, 47008, 63732, 32719], "ratingsCount": 155428, "reviewsCount": 12076, "numPages": 191, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Dublin Literary Award", "awardedAt": 1230796800000, "category": null, "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/193755.The_Diving_Bell_and_the_Butterfly", "title": "The Diving Bell and the Butterfly", "titleComplete": "The Diving Bell and the Butterfly", "description": "\u2018Locked-in syndrome: paralysed from head to toe, the patient, his mind intact, is imprisoned inside his own body, unable to speak or move. In my case, blinking my left eyelid is my only means of communication.\u2019In December 1995, Jean-Dominique Bauby, editor-in-chief of French \u2018Elle\u2019 and the father of two young children, suffered a massive stroke and found himself paralysed and speechless, but entirely conscious, trapped by what doctors call \u2018locked-in syndrome\u2019. Using his only functioning muscle \u2013 his left eyelid \u2013 he began dictating this remarkable story, painstakingly spelling it out letter by letter.His book offers a haunting, harrowing look inside the cruel prison of locked-in syndrome, but it is also a triumph of the human spirit.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1336930564i/193755.jpg", "genres": ["Nonfiction", "Biography Memoir", "Memoir", "Classics", "Medicine", "Medical", "Disability", "Autobiography", "France", "Biography"], "asin": "0375701214", "isbn": "0375701214", "isbn13": "9780375701214", "publisher": "Vintage", "author": ["Jeremy Leggatt", "Jean-Dominique Bauby"], "publishDate": 898585200000, "characters": ["Jean-Dominique Bauby"], "places": ["Berck-sur-Mer", "France"], "ratingHistogram": [1343, 3715, 14703, 26771, 24458], "ratingsCount": 70990, "reviewsCount": 5387, "numPages": 132, "language": "English"}
