{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/331319.An_American_Tragedy", "title": "An American Tragedy", "titleComplete": "An American Tragedy", "description": "'An American Tragedy' is the story of Clyde Griffiths, who spends his life in the desperate pursuit of success. On a deeper, more profound level, it is the masterful portrayal of the society whose values both shape Clyde's ambitions and seal his fate; it is an unsurpassed depiction of the harsh realities of American life and of the dark side of the American dream. Extraordinary in scope and power, vivid in its sense of wholesale human waste, unceasing in its rich compassion, 'An American Tragedy' stands as Theodore Dreiser's supreme achievement.Based on an actual criminal case, 'An American Tragedy' was the inspiration for the film 'A Place in the Sun', which won six Academy Awards and starred Elizabeth Taylor and Montgomery Clift.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1309283443i/331319.jpg", "genres": ["Crime", "20th Century", "Classic Literature", "Literature", "Banned Books", "Fiction", "American", "Historical Fiction", "Classics", "Novels"], "asin": "0451527704", "isbn": "0451527704", "isbn13": "9780451527707", "publisher": "Signet Classics", "author": ["Richard R. Lingeman", "Theodore Dreiser"], "publishDate": 967791600000, "characters": ["Asa Griffiths", "Samuel Griffiths", "Mr. Shurlock", "Frank Harriet", "Esta Griffiths", "Charlie Trone", "Justice Oberwaltzer", "Sondra Finchley", "Alvin Belknap", "Bert Gettler", "Hortense Briggs", "Miss Vanda Steele", "Orville Mason", "Roberta Alden", "Thomas Ratterer", "Tom Keary", "Reuben Jephson", "Gilbert Griffiths", "Violet Taylor", "Elvira Griffiths", "Legare Atterbury", "Mrs. George Newton", "Perley Haynes", "Nicholas Kraut", "Clyde Griffiths", "Sonda"], "places": ["Lycurgus, New York", "Kansas City, Missouri"], "ratingHistogram": [1051, 2226, 7347, 12420, 13367], "ratingsCount": 36411, "reviewsC