{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/40669887-cheaper-by-the-dozen", "title": "Cheaper by the Dozen", "titleComplete": "Cheaper by the Dozen (Cheaper by the Dozen, #1)", "description": "Adapted into two classic motion pictures, this bestselling memoir is the unforgettable story of two parents, twelve kids, and a world of laughter and love. Translated into more than fifty languages, Cheaper by the Dozen is the unforgettable story of the Gilbreth clan as told by two of its members. In this endearing, amusing memoir, siblings Frank Jr. and Ernestine capture the hilarity and heart of growing up in an oversized family.Mother and Dad are world-renowned efficiency experts, helping factories fine-tune their assembly lines for maximum output at minimum cost. At home, the Gilbreths themselves have cranked out twelve kids, and Dad is out to prove that efficiency principles can apply to family as well as the workplace. The heartwarming and comic stories of the jumbo-size Gilbreth clan have delighted generations of readers, and will keep you and yours laughing for years.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1530288546i/40669887.jpg", "genres": ["Childrens", "Humor", "Family", "Nonfiction", "Biography Memoir", "Memoir", "History", "Autobiography", "Classics", "Biography"], "asin": "B00FTOANM2", "publisher": "Open Road Media", "series": ["Cheaper by the Dozen"], "author": ["Frank B. Gilbreth Jr.", "Ernestine Gilbreth Carey"], "publishDate": 1383638400000, "places": ["Montclair, New Jersey"], "ratingHistogram": [970, 2151, 9022, 14927, 15768], "ratingsCount": 42838, "reviewsCount": 2240, "numPages": 292, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/5267365-don-t-judge-a-girl-by-her-cover", "title": "Don't Judge a Girl by Her Cover", "titleComplete": "Don't Judge a Girl by Her Cover (Gallagher Girls, #3)", "description": "When Cammie \"The Chameleon\" Morgan visits her roommate Macey in Boston, she thinks she's in for an exciting end to her summer break. After all, she's there to watch Macey's father accept the nomination for vice president of the United States. But when you go to the world's best school (for spies), \"exciting\" and \"deadly\" are never far apart. Cammie and Macey soon find themselves trapped in a kidnappers' plot, with only their espionage skills to save them.As her junior year begins, Cammie can't shake the memory of what happened in Boston, and even the Gallagher Academy for Exceptional Young Women doesn't feel like the safe haven it once did. Shocking secrets and old flames seem to lurk around every one of the mansion's corners as Cammie and her friends struggle to answer the questions, Who is after Macey? And how can the Gallagher Girls keep her safe?Soon Cammie is joining Bex and Liz as Macey's private security team on the campaign trail. The girls must use their spy training at every turn as the stakes are raised, and Cammie gets closer and closer to the shocking truth. . . .", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1359827132i/5267365.jpg", "genres": ["Adventure", "Chick Lit", "Teen", "Contemporary", "Young Adult", "Espionage", "Mystery", "Fiction", "Action", "Romance"], "asin": "1423116380", "isbn": "1423116380", "isbn13": "9781423116387", "publisher": "Disney \u25cf Hyperion Books", "series": ["Gallagher Girls"], "author": ["Ally Carter"], "publishDate": 1244530800000, "characters": ["Zachary Goode", "Rebecca \"Bex\" Baxter", "Liz Sutton", "Macey McHenry", "Cammie Morgan"], "places": ["Roseville, Virginia"], "ratingHistogram": [654, 2090, 11970, 23487, 32680], "ratingsCount": 7088