{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/9915.Less_Than_Zero", "title": "Less Than Zero", "titleComplete": "Less Than Zero", "description": "Set in Los Angeles in the early 1980s, this coolly mesmerizing novel is a raw, powerful portrait of a lost generation that experienced sex, drugs, and disaffection at too early an age, growing up in a world shaped by casual nihilism, passivity, and too much money.Clay comes home for Christmas vacation from his Eastern college and re-enters a landscape of limitless privilege and absolute moral entropy, where everyone drives Porches, dines at Spago, and snorts mountains of cocaine. He tries to renew feelings for his girlfriend, Blair, and for his best friend from high school, Julian, who is careering into hustling and heroin. Clay's holiday turns into a dizzying spiral of desperation that takes him through the relentless parties in glitzy mansions, seedy bars, and underground rock clubs, and into the seamy world of L.A. after dark.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1443060100i/9915.jpg", "genres": ["Coming Of Age", "20th Century", "Literary Fiction", "The United States Of America", "Literature", "Contemporary", "Fiction", "American", "Classics", "Novels"], "asin": "0679781498", "publisher": "Vintage Books", "author": ["Bret Easton Ellis"], "publishDate": 1276066800000, "characters": ["Griffin (Less Than Zero)", "Daniel (Less Than Zero)", "Trent (Less Than Zero)", "Kim (Less Than Zero)", "Clay (Less Than Zero)", "Julian (Less Than Zero)", "Alana (Less Than Zero)", "Finn (Less Than Zero)", "Blair (Less Than Zero)", "Rip (Less Than Zero)"], "places": ["Los Angeles, California", "California"], "ratingHistogram": [3226, 8481, 24129, 29676, 17475], "ratingsCount": 82987, "reviewsCount": 4784, "numPages": 208, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6479550-magic-bleeds", "title": "Magic Bleeds", "titleComplete": "Magic Bleeds (Kate Daniels, #4)", "description": "Kate Daniels works for the Order of the Knights of Merciful Aid, officially as a liaison with the mercenary guild. Unofficially, she cleans up the paranormal problems no one else wants to handle\u2014especially if they involve Atlanta\u2019s shapeshifting community.When she\u2019s called in to investigate a fight at the Steel Horse, a bar midway between the territories of the shapeshifters and the necromancers, Kate quickly discovers there\u2019s a new player in town. One who\u2019s been around for thousands of years\u2014and rode to war at the side of Kate\u2019s father.This foe may be too much even for Kate and Curran, the Lord of the Beasts, to handle. Because this time, Kate will be taking on family\u2026", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1407110429i/6479550.jpg", "genres": ["Magic", "Shapeshifters", "Fantasy", "Urban Fantasy", "Vampires", "Paranormal Romance", "Adult", "Fiction", "Paranormal", "Romance"], "asin": "0441018521", "isbn": "0441018521", "isbn13": "9780441018529", "publisher": "Ace", "series": ["Kate Daniels", "World of Kate Daniels"], "author": ["Ilona Andrews"], "publishDate": 1274770800000, "characters": ["Dr. George Doolittle", "Kate Daniels", "Julie Olsen", "Ghastek", "Andrea Nash", "Saiman", "Derek Gaunt", "Curran Lennart", "Dali Harimau", "Mahon Delany", "Ted Moynohan", "Barabas Gilliam", "Raphael Medrano", "Beatrice \"Aunt B\"", "Jim Shrapshire"], "places": ["Atlanta, Georgia"], "ratingHistogram": [472, 984, 7387, 26626, 46805], "ratingsCount": 82274, "reviewsCount": 3749, "numPages": 349, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Romantic Times Reviewers' Choice Award (RT Award)", "awardedAt": 1262332800000, "category": "Urban Fantasy", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "DABWAHA Romance Tournament", "awardedAt": 12938688000