{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/50365.A_Suitable_Boy", "title": "A Suitable Boy", "titleComplete": "A Suitable Boy (A Bridge of Leaves, #1)", "description": "Vikram Seth's novel is, at its core, a love story: Lata and her mother, Mrs. Rupa Mehra, are both trying to find\u2014through love or through exacting maternal appraisal\u2014a suitable boy for Lata to marry. Set in the early 1950s, in an India newly independent and struggling through a time of crisis, A Suitable Boy takes us into the richly imagined world of four large extended families and spins a compulsively readable tale of their lives and loves. A sweeping panoramic portrait of a complex, multiethnic society in flux, A Suitable Boy remains the story of ordinary people caught up in a web of love and ambition, humor and sadness, prejudice and reconciliation, the most delicate social etiquette and the most appalling violence.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1329421639i/50365.jpg", "genres": ["Indian Literature", "Romance", "Literature", "Historical", "India", "Fiction", "Historical Fiction", "Classics", "Novels", "Asia"], "asin": "0060786523", "isbn": "0060786523", "isbn13": "9780060786526", "publisher": "Harper Perennial Modern Classics", "series": ["A Bridge of Leaves"], "author": ["Vikram Seth"], "publishDate": 1128409200000, "characters": ["Meenakshi Mehra (n\u00e9e Chatterji)", "Amit Chatterji", "Arun Mehra", "Lata Mehra", "Rupa Mehra", "Varun Mehra", "Maan Kapoor", "Pran Kapoor", "Savita Mehra"], "places": ["Brahmapur", "Delhi", "Calcutta", "India", "Kanpur"], "ratingHistogram": [888, 2110, 7846, 16338, 20315], "ratingsCount": 47497, "reviewsCount": 2952, "numPages": 1474, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "WH Smith Literary Award", "awardedAt": 757411200000, "category": null, "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Commonwealth Writers' Prize", "awardedAt": 757411200000, "category": "Best Book Overall", "hasWon": null}]}
