{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/25300956-royal-assassin", "title": "Royal Assassin", "titleComplete": "Royal Assassin (Farseer Trilogy, #2)", "description": "Fitz has survived his first hazardous mission as king\u2019s assassin, but is left little more than a cripple. Battered and bitter, he vows to abandon his oath to King Shrewd, remaining in the distant mountains. But love and events of terrible urgency draw him back to the court at Buckkeep, and into the deadly intrigues of the royal family. Renewing their vicious attacks on the coast, the Red-Ship Raiders leave burned-out villages and demented victims in their wake. The kingdom is also under assault from within, as treachery threatens the throne of the ailing king. In this time of great danger, the fate of the kingdom may rest in Fitz\u2019s hands\u2014and his role in its salvation may require the ultimate sacrifice.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1428234219i/25300956.jpg", "genres": ["Epic", "Magic", "Adventure", "Science Fiction Fantasy", "Fantasy", "Fiction", "Adult", "Audiobook", "High Fantasy", "Epic Fantasy"], "publisher": "Spectra", "series": ["The Farseer Trilogy", "The Realm of the Elderlings"], "author": ["Robin Hobb"], "publishDate": 1427871600000, "characters": ["Serene (Farseer)", "Hands (Elderling)", "The Fool (Elderling Saga)", "Shrewd Farseer", "Nighteyes", "Lacey (Elderling Saga)", "Regal Farseer", "Kettricken (Farseer)", "Rosemary (Elderling)", "FitzChivalry Farseer", "Molly Chandler", "Verity Farseer", "Burrich", "Kebal Rawbread", "Lady Patience", "Chade Fallstar"], "ratingHistogram": [1705, 5023, 24403, 69597, 88448], "ratingsCount": 189176, "reviewsCount": 7676, "numPages": 675, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Locus Award", "awardedAt": 852105600000, "category": "Best Fantasy Novel", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/608474.The_Sign_of_Four", "title": "The Sign of Four", "titleComplete": "The Sign of Four (Sherlock Holmes, #2)", "description": "As a dense yellow fog swirls through the streets of London, a deep melancholy has descended on Sherlock Holmes, who sits in a cocaine-induced haze at 221B Baker Street. His mood is only lifted by a visit from a beautiful but distressed young woman - Mary Morstan, whose father vanished ten years before. Four years later she began to receive an exquisite gift every year: a large, lustrous pearl. Now she has had an intriguing invitation to meet her unknown benefactor and urges Holmes and Watson to accompany her. And in the ensuing investigation - which involves a wronged woman, a stolen hoard of Indian treasure, a wooden-legged ruffian, a helpful dog and a love affair - even the jaded Holmes is moved to exclaim, 'Isn't it gorgeous!'--back cover", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1299346921i/608474.jpg", "genres": ["Crime", "Detective", "Mystery Thriller", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Audiobook", "19th Century", "Historical Fiction", "Classics", "Thriller"], "publisher": "Penguin Books", "series": ["Sherlock Holmes"], "author": ["Peter Ackroyd", "Arthur Conan Doyle"], "publishDate": 994316400000, "characters": ["Dr. John Watson", "Mary Morstan", "Sherlock Holmes", "Athelney Jones"], "ratingHistogram": [1662, 6897, 39067, 59829, 43253], "ratingsCount": 150708, "reviewsCount": 7363, "numPages": 129, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/38500.Women", "title": "Women", "titleComplete": "Women", "description": "Low-life writer and unrepentant alcoholic Henry Chinaski was born to survive. After decades of slacking off at low-paying dead-end jobs, blowing his cash on booze and women, and scrimping by in flea-bitten apartments, Chinaski sees his poetic star rising at last. Now, at fifty, he is reveling in his sudden rock-star life, running three hundred hangovers a year, and maintaining a sex life that would cripple Casanova.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1325028693i/38500.jpg", "genres": ["Humor", "20th Century", "The United States Of America", "Literature", "Contemporary", "Fiction", "American", "Classics", "Poetry", "Novels"], "asin": "0061177598", "isbn": "0061177598", "isbn13": "9780061177590", "publisher": "Ecco", "author": ["Charles Bukowski"], "publishDate": 1406617200000, "characters": ["Henry Chinaski"], "places": ["Los Angeles, California"], "ratingHistogram": [2342, 5542, 17800, 28130, 22418], "ratingsCount": 76232, "reviewsCount": 3770, "numPages": 291, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/89147256-marry-christmas", "title": "Marry Christmas", "titleComplete": "Marry Christmas", "description": "Growing up with an undiagnosed learning disability and a name that screams intelligence, Britanica Jaymes suffers ridicule as a child. Pudgy, frazzled hair and a face plastered with freckles added to the ridicule. The support of family, friends and God provided all the love she needed. But there was one serious candy canes are her form of kryptonite. Desperate, she made a secret Christmas wish. Most everything is coming true, except for true love.Signs of reverting back to the learning disability and still seeking true love, the magic of Christmas lingers in the air, and a dose of Shakespeare, Rambo and snowflakes help to create a perfect Christmas recipe of hope.Skip the final peppermint At least for now, until the cure is found.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1678401187i/89147256.jpg", "asin": "B09KY84YXG", "isbn": "1955784256", "isbn13": "9781955784252", "publisher": "Satin Romance", "author": ["Linda Phillips"], "publishDate": 1637049600000, "ratingHistogram": [9, 34, 46, 539, 556], "ratingsCount": 1184, "reviewsCount": 9, "numPages": 263, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/28449207-strange-the-dreamer", "title": "Strange the Dreamer", "titleComplete": "Strange the Dreamer (Strange the Dreamer, #1)", "description": "The dream chooses the dreamer, not the other way around\u2014and Lazlo Strange, war orphan and junior librarian, has always feared that his dream chose poorly. Since he was five years old he\u2019s been obsessed with the mythic lost city of Weep, but it would take someone bolder than he to cross half the world in search of it. Then a stunning opportunity presents itself, in the person of a hero called the Godslayer and a band of legendary warriors, and he has to seize his chance or lose his dream forever.What happened in Weep two hundred years ago to cut it off from the rest of the world? What exactly did the Godslayer slay that went by the name of god? And what is the mysterious problem he now seeks help in solving?The answers await in Weep, but so do more mysteries\u2014including the blue-skinned goddess who appears in Lazlo\u2019s dreams. How did he dream her before he knew she existed? And if all the gods are dead, why does she seem so real?Welcome to Weep.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1519915549i/28449207.jpg", "genres": ["Magic", "Adventure", "Science Fiction Fantasy", "Young Adult Fantasy", "High Fantasy", "Fantasy", "Young Adult", "Fiction", "Audiobook", "Romance"], "asin": "0316341681", "isbn": "0316341681", "isbn13": "9780316341684", "publisher": "Little, Brown Books for Young Readers", "series": ["Strange the Dreamer"], "author": ["Laini Taylor"], "publishDate": 1490684400000, "characters": ["Minya", "Sparrow", "Sarai", "Feral", "Suheyla", "Ruby", "Calixte", "Lazlo Strange", "Ruza", "Azareen"], "ratingHistogram": [1666, 3920, 13585, 37560, 59874], "ratingsCount": 116605, "reviewsCount": 20779, "numPages": 544, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Michael L. Printz Award", "awardedAt": 151479