{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/60931.Kindred", "title": "Kindred", "titleComplete": "Kindred", "description": "The visionary author\u2019s masterpiece pulls us\u2014along with her Black female hero\u2014through time to face the horrors of slavery and explore the impacts of racism, sexism, and white supremacy then and now.Dana, a modern Black woman, is celebrating her 26th birthday with her new husband when she is snatched abruptly from her home in California and transported to the antebellum South. Rufus, the white son of a plantation owner, is drowning, and Dana has been summoned to save him. Dana is drawn back repeatedly through time to the slave quarters, and each time the stay grows longer, more arduous, and more dangerous until it is uncertain whether or not Dana\u2019s life will end, long before it has a chance to begin.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1339423248i/60931.jpg", "genres": ["Time Travel", "Science Fiction", "Race", "Fantasy", "Historical", "Fiction", "Audiobook", "African American", "Historical Fiction", "Classics"], "asin": "0807083690", "isbn": "0807083690", "isbn13": "9780807083697", "publisher": "Beacon Press", "author": ["Octavia E. Butler"], "publishDate": 1075622400000, "characters": ["Rufus Weylin", "Alice Greenwood", "Kevin Franklin", "Tom Weylin", "Dana Franklin", "Margaret Weylin"], "places": ["Altadena, California", "Maryland"], "ratingHistogram": [1192, 4361, 23283, 75510, 96750], "ratingsCount": 201096, "reviewsCount": 22298, "numPages": 288, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Locus Award", "awardedAt": 315561600000, "category": "Best Fantasy Novel", "hasWon": null}]}
