{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/95693.The_Blue_Castle", "title": "The Blue Castle", "titleComplete": "The Blue Castle", "description": "An unforgettable story of courage and romance. Will Valancy Stirling ever escape her strict family and find true love?Valancy Stirling is 29, unmarried, and has never been in love. Living with her overbearing mother and meddlesome aunt, she finds her only consolation in the \"forbidden\" books of John Foster and her daydreams of the Blue Castle--a place where all her dreams come true and she can be who she truly wants to be. After getting shocking news from the doctor, she rebels against her family and discovers a surprising new world, full of love and adventures far beyond her most secret dreams.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1684723987i/95693.jpg", "genres": ["Romance", "Historical Romance", "Historical", "Young Adult", "Fiction", "Canada", "Adult", "Historical Fiction", "Adult Fiction", "Classics"], "asin": "0553280511", "isbn": "0553280511", "isbn13": "9780553280517", "publisher": "Bantam Books", "author": ["L.M. Montgomery"], "publishDate": 607420800000, "characters": ["Valancy Stirling", "Barney Snaith"], "places": ["Deerwood, Ontario", "Canada"], "ratingHistogram": [353, 993, 5535, 13762, 21092], "ratingsCount": 41735, "reviewsCount": 6303, "numPages": 218, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/4952.What_Is_the_What", "title": "What Is the What", "titleComplete": "What Is the What", "description": "From the bestselling author of A Heartbreaking Work of Staggering Genius, What Is the What is the epic novel based on the life of Valentino Achak Deng who, along with thousands of other children \u2014the so-called Lost Boys\u2014was forced to leave his village in Sudan at the age of seven and trek hundreds of miles by foot, pursued by militias, government bombers, and wild animals, crossing the deserts of three countries to find freedom. When he finally is resettled in the United States, he finds a life full of promise, but also heartache and myriad new challenges. Moving, suspenseful, and unexpectedly funny, What Is the What is an astonishing novel that illuminates the lives of millions through one extraordinary man.-back cover", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1328837457i/4952.jpg", "genres": ["War", "Literature", "Sudan", "Historical", "Contemporary", "Fiction", "American", "Book Club", "Historical Fiction", "Novels"], "asin": "1932416641", "isbn": "1932416641", "isbn13": "9781932416640", "publisher": "McSweeney's", "author": ["Dave Eggers"], "publishDate": 1161154800000, "places": ["East Africa", "North Africa", "Kenya", "Kakuma", "Sudan", "South Sudan", "Ethiopia", "Africa", "Marial Bai"], "ratingHistogram": [1417, 3046, 12691, 32569, 34613], "ratingsCount": 84336, "reviewsCount": 7459, "numPages": 475, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Independent Publisher Book Award (IPPY)", "awardedAt": 1167638400000, "category": "Literary Fiction", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Prix M\u00e9dicis Etranger", "awardedAt": 1230796800000, "category": "", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "National Book Critics Circle Award", "awardedAt": 1136102400000, "category": "Fiction", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/34066798-a-gentleman-in-moscow", "title": "A Gentleman in Moscow", "titleComplete": "A Gentleman in Moscow", "description": "From the New York Times bestselling author of Rules of Civility\u2014a transporting novel about a man who is ordered to spend the rest of his life inside a luxury hotelWith his breakout debut novel, Rules of Civility, Amor Towles established himself as a master of absorbing, sophisticated fiction, bringing late 1930s Manhattan to life with splendid atmosphere and a flawless command of style. Readers and critics were enchanted; as NPR commented, \u201cTowles writes with grace and verve about the mores and manners of a society on the cusp of radical change.\u201dA Gentleman in Moscow immerses us in another elegantly drawn era with the story of Count Alexander Rostov. When, in 1922, he is deemed an unrepentant aristocrat by a Bolshevik tribunal, the count is sentenced to house arrest in the Metropol, a grand hotel across the street from the Kremlin. Rostov, an indomitable man of erudition and wit, has never worked a day in his life, and must now live in an attic room while some of the most tumultuous decades in Russian history are unfolding outside the hotel\u2019s doors. Unexpectedly, his reduced circumstances provide him a doorway into a much larger world of emotional discovery.Brimming with humour, a glittering cast of characters, and one beautifully rendered scene after another, this singular novel casts a spell as it relates the count\u2019s endeavour to gain a deeper understanding of what it means to be a man of purpose.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1551480896i/34066798.jpg", "genres": ["Russia", "Literary Fiction", "Historical", "Audiobook", "Fiction", "Adult", "Book Club", "Historical Fiction", "Adult Fiction", "Novels"], "asin": "0143110438", "publisher": "Penguin Books", "author": ["Amor Towles"], "publishDate": 155358360