{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/34084.The_Waste_Lands", "title": "The Waste Lands", "titleComplete": "The Waste Lands (The Dark Tower, #3)", "description": "Several months have passed, and Roland\u2019s two new tet-mates have become proficient gunslingers. Eddie Dean has given up heroin, and Odetta\u2019s two selves have joined, becoming the stronger and more balanced personality of Susannah Dean. But while battling The Pusher in 1977 New York, Roland altered ka by saving the life of Jake Chambers, a boy who\u2014in Roland\u2019s where and when\u2014has already died. Now Roland and Jake exist in different worlds, but they are joined by the same madness: the paradox of double memories. Roland, Susannah, and Eddie must draw Jake into Mid-World then follow the Path of the Beam all the way to the Dark Tower. But nothing is easy in Mid-World. Along the way our tet stumbles into the ruined city of Lud, and are caught between the warring gangs of the Pubes and the Grays. The only way out of Lud is to wake Blaine the Mono, an insane train that has a passion for riddling, and for suicidal journeys.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1532334476i/34084.jpg", "genres": ["Adventure", "Science Fiction Fantasy", "Science Fiction", "Post Apocalyptic", "Fantasy", "Westerns", "Fiction", "Audiobook", "Horror", "Thriller"], "asin": "0670032565", "isbn": "0670032565", "isbn13": "9780670032563", "publisher": "Viking Adult", "series": ["The Dark Tower"], "author": ["Stephen King", "Ned Dameron"], "publishDate": 1056351600000, "characters": ["Andrew Quick", "Calvin Tower", "Detta Walker", "Aaron Deepneau", "Henry Dean", "Richard Fannin", "Jake Chambers", "Eddie Dean", "Roland Deschain", "Susannah Dean (The Dark Tower)", "Talitha Unwin", "Blaine"], "ratingHistogram": [1561, 4926, 29996, 81926, 97807], "ratingsCount": 216216, "reviewsCount": 7295, "numPages": 590, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/56034.The_French_Lieutenant_s_Woman", "title": "The French Lieutenant's Woman", "titleComplete": "The French Lieutenant's Woman", "description": "The scene is the village of Lyme Regis on Dorset's Lyme Bay...\"the largest bite from the underside of England's out-stretched southwestern leg.\" The major characters in the love-intrigue triangle are Charles Smithson, 32, a gentleman of independent means &amp; vaguely scientific bent; his fianc\u00e9e, Ernestina Freeman, a pretty heiress daughter of a wealthy &amp; pompous dry goods merchant; &amp; Sarah Woodruff, mysterious &amp; fascinating...deserted after a brief affair with a French naval officer a short time before the story begins. Obsessed with an irresistible fascination for the enigmatic Sarah, Charles is hurtled by a moment of consummated lust to the brink of the existential void. Duty dictates that his engagement to Tina must be broken as he goes forth once again to seek the woman who has captured his Victorian soul &amp; gentleman's heart.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1466630905i/56034.jpg", "genres": ["20th Century", "Literary Fiction", "Literature", "British Literature", "Classics", "Historical", "Fiction", "Historical Fiction", "Romance", "Novels"], "asin": "0099478331", "isbn": "0099478331", "isbn13": "9780099478331", "publisher": "Vintage", "author": ["John Fowles"], "publishDate": 1230796800000, "characters": ["Charles Smithson", "Sarah Woodruff", "Mrs. Poulteney", "Dr Grogan", "Sam Farrow", "Ernestina Freeman"], "places": ["London, England", "Dorset, England", "Exeter, Devon, England", "Lyme Regis, England"], "ratingHistogram": [1031, 3095, 12371, 20289, 15343], "ratingsCount": 52129, "reviewsCount": 2058, "numPages": 470, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "WH Smith Literary Award", "awardedAt": 28800000, "category": null, "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/31173.Villette", "title": "Villette", "titleComplete": "Villette", "description": "With her final novel, Villette, Charlotte Bront\u00eb reached the height of her artistic power. First published in 1853, Villette is Bront\u00eb's most accomplished and deeply felt work, eclipsing even Jane Eyre in critical acclaim. Her narrator, the autobiographical Lucy Snowe, flees England and a tragic past to become an instructor in a French boarding school in the town of Villette. There she unexpectedly confronts her feelings of love and longing as she witnesses the fitful romance between Dr. John, a handsome young Englishman, and Ginerva Fanshawe, a beautiful coquette. The first pain brings others, and with them comes the heartache Lucy has tried so long to escape. Yet in spite of adversity and disappointment, Lucy Snowe survives to recount the unstinting vision of a turbulent life's journey - a journey that is one of the most insightful fictional studies of a woman's consciousness in English literature.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1320412741i/31173.jpg", "genres": ["Literature", "British Literature", "Gothic", "Classics", "Victorian", "19th Century", "Fiction", "Historical Fiction", "Romance", "Novels"], "publisher": "Modern Library", "author": ["Ignes Sodre", "Charlotte Bront\u00eb", "A.S. Byatt"], "publishDate": 1002610800000, "characters": ["M. Paul Carl David Emanuel", "Dr. John Graham Bretton", "Mrs. Louisa Lucy Bretton", "Madame Modeste Maria Beck", "Ginevra Laura Fanshawe", "Paulina Mary Home", "Lucy Snowe"], "ratingHistogram": [1925, 5921, 18939, 23936, 20410], "ratingsCount": 71131, "reviewsCount": 5210, "numPages": 573, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/10215349-the-immortal-rules", "title": "The Immortal Rules", "titleComplete": "The Immortal Rules (Blood of Eden, #1)", "description": "To survive in a ruined world, she must embrace the darkness\u2026Allison Sekemoto survives in the Fringe, the outermost circle of a walled-in city. By day, she and her crew scavenge for food. By night, any one of them could be eaten. Some days, all that drives Allie is her hatred of them\u2014the vampires who keep humans as blood cattle. Until the night Allie herself dies and becomes one of the monsters.Forced to flee her city, Allie must pass for human as she joins a ragged group of pilgrims seeking a legend\u2014a place that might have a cure for the disease that killed off most of civilization and created the rabids, the bloodthirsty creatures who threaten human and vampire alike. And soon Allie will have to decide what and who is worth dying for\u2026 again.Enter Julie Kagawa's dark and twisted world as an unforgettable journey begins.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1677007850i/10215349.jpg", "genres": ["Post Apocalyptic", "Supernatural", "Fantasy", "Urban Fantasy", "Vampires", "Young Adult", "Dystopia", "Fiction", "Paranormal", "Romance"], "asin": "0373210515", "isbn": "0373210515", "isbn13": "9780373210510", "publisher": "Harlequin Teen", "series": ["Blood of Eden"], "author": ["Julie Kagawa"], "publishDate": 1335250800000, "characters": ["Stick", "Zeke Crosse", "Kanin", "Jackal", "Allison Sekemoto"], "ratingHistogram": [2063, 3444, 11591, 23358, 29775], "ratingsCount": 70231, "reviewsCount": 6265, "numPages": 485, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Goodreads Choice Award", "awardedAt": 1325404800000, "category": "Young Adult Fantasy & Science Fiction", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/68210.Gilead", "title": "Gilead", "titleComplete": "Gilead (Gilead, #1)", "description": "Nearly 25 years after Housekeeping, Marilynne Robinson returns with an intimate tale of three generations, from the Civil War to the 20th century: a story about fathers and sons and the spiritual battles that still rage at America's heart. In the words of Kirkus, it is a novel \"as big as a nation, as quiet as thought, and moving as prayer. Matchless and towering.\" GILEAD tells the story of America and will break your heart.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1558681761i/68210.jpg", "genres": ["Literary Fiction", "Literature", "Historical", "Contemporary", "Fiction", "Audiobook", "American", "Historical Fiction", "Classics", "Novels"], "asin": "031242440X", "isbn": "031242440X", "isbn13": "9780312424404", "publisher": "Picador USA", "series": ["Gilead"], "author": ["Marilynne Robinson"], "publishDate": 1136880000000, "characters": ["Reverend Robert Boughton", "John Ames", "Jack Boughton"], "places": ["Gilead, Iowa"], "ratingHistogram": [4173, 9172, 22955, 33718, 37419], "ratingsCount": 107437, "reviewsCount": 13738, "numPages": 247, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Pulitzer Prize", "awardedAt": 1104566400000, "category": "Fiction", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Orange Prize", "awardedAt": 1136102400000, "category": "Fiction Longlist", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "PEN/Faulkner Award for Fiction", "awardedAt": 1104566400000, "category": "", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Ambassador Book Award", "awardedAt": 1104566400000, "category": "Fiction", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Los Angeles Times Book Prize", "awardedAt": 1072944000000, "category": "Fiction", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Chicago Tribune Heartland Prize", "awardedAt": 1104566400000, "category": "Fiction", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Rodda Book Award", "awardedAt": 1136102400000, "category": null, "hasWon": null},