{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/37186.The_Miraculous_Journey_of_Edward_Tulane", "title": "The Miraculous Journey of Edward Tulane", "titleComplete": "The Miraculous Journey of Edward Tulane", "description": "A timeless tale by the incomparable Kate DiCamillo, complete with stunning full-color plates by Bagram Ibatoulline, honors the enduring power of love.Once, in a house on Egypt Street, there lived a china rabbit named Edward Tulane. The rabbit was very pleased with himself, and for good he was owned by a girl named Abilene, who treated him with the utmost care and adored him completely.And then, one day, he was lost.Kate DiCamillo takes us on an extraordinary journey, from the depths of the ocean to the net of a fisherman, from the top of a garbage heap to the fireside of a hoboes' camp, from the bedside of an ailing child to the bustling streets of Memphis. And along the way, we are shown a true miracle \u2014 that even a heart of the most breakable kind can learn to love, to lose, and to love again.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1361121815i/37186.jpg", "genres": ["Childrens", "Adventure", "Juvenile", "Fantasy", "Animals", "Young Adult", "Fiction", "Middle Grade", "Audiobook", "Chapter Books"], "asin": "0763625892", "isbn": "0763625892", "isbn13": "9780763625894", "publisher": "Candlewick Press", "author": ["Kate DiCamillo", "Bagram Ibatoulline"], "publishDate": 1139904000000, "characters": ["Abilene", "Edward Tulane"], "ratingHistogram": [1192, 2593, 11569, 30072, 59846], "ratingsCount": 105272, "reviewsCount": 12352, "numPages": 228, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Zilveren Griffel", "awardedAt": 1167638400000, "category": null, "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Grand Canyon Reader Award", "awardedAt": 1199174400000, "category": "Intermediate Book", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Sunshine State Young Readers Award", "awardedAt": 1167638400000, "category": "Grades 3-5", "hasWon