{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/11594257-under-the-never-sky", "title": "Under the Never Sky", "titleComplete": "Under the Never Sky (Under the Never Sky, #1)", "description": "WORLDS KEPT THEM APART.DESTINY BROUGHT THEM TOGETHER.Aria has lived her whole life in the protected dome of Reverie. Her entire world confined to its spaces, she's never thought to dream of what lies beyond its doors. So when her mother goes missing, Aria knows her chances of surviving in the outer wasteland long enough to find her are slim.Then Aria meets an outsider named Perry. He's searching for someone too. He's also wild\u2014a savage\u2014but might be her best hope at staying alive.If they can survive, they are each other's best hope for finding answers.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1356591725i/11594257.jpg", "genres": ["Adventure", "Post Apocalyptic", "Science Fiction", "Teen", "Fantasy", "Young Adult", "Dystopia", "Fiction", "Paranormal", "Romance"], "asin": "1907411054", "isbn": "1907411054", "isbn13": "9781907411052", "publisher": "Atom", "series": ["Under the Never Sky"], "author": ["Veronica Rossi"], "publishDate": 1328601600000, "characters": ["Roar", "Peregrine \"Perry\"", "Cinder", "Aria"], "ratingHistogram": [3506, 6139, 21047, 40997, 42202], "ratingsCount": 113891, "reviewsCount": 9051, "numPages": 374, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Goodreads Choice Award", "awardedAt": 1325404800000, "category": "Young Adult Fantasy & Science Fiction", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Premio El Templo de las Mil Puertas", "awardedAt": 1325404800000, "category": "Mejor novela extranjera perteneciente a saga", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/43483262-love-is-the-answer-god-is-the-cure", "title": "Love is the Answer, God is the Cure: A True Story of Abuse, Betrayal and Unconditional Love", "titleComplete": "Love is the Answer, God is the Cure: A True Story of Abuse, Betrayal and Unconditional Love", "description": "Her family secrets burst in the spotlight when Aimee and her sister went to the authorities. In this riveting memoir Aimee Cabo shares the inside story of a young girl's courage to stand up to sexual, physical, and emotional abuse while facing her abusers in a trial the media dubbed \"The Case from Hell.\" As she fought court battles, poverty, abuse, and addiction Aimee always turned to love and God.Love is the Answer, God is the Cure is a story of a woman who triumphed against all odds, persevered to find true love and form a family that could withstand anything.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1547961493i/43483262.jpg", "genres": ["Inspirational", "Nonfiction", "Drama", "Abuse", "Contemporary", "Education", "Adult", "True Story", "Book Club", "Biography"], "asin": "0578433869", "isbn": "0578433869", "isbn13": "9780578433868", "publisher": "Inspirational Books Publishing", "author": ["Aimee Cabo Nikolov"], "publishDate": 1546329600000, "ratingHistogram": [177, 586, 742, 6253, 6642], "ratingsCount": 14400, "reviewsCount": 114, "numPages": 150, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Feathered Quill Book Award", "awardedAt": 1546329600000, "category": "Memoir/Biography (1st) and for Inspirational (1st)", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Body Mind Spirit Book Award", "awardedAt": 1514793600000, "category": "Inspirational", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/2832909-an-echo-in-the-bone", "title": "An Echo in the Bone", "titleComplete": "An Echo in the Bone (Outlander, #7)", "description": "A new Outlander novel \u2014 the seventh \u2014 from #1 National Bestselling author Diana Gabaldon.Readers have been waiting with bated breath for the seventh volume in bestselling author Diana Gabaldon\u2019s epic Outlander saga \u2014 a masterpiece of historical fiction featuring Jamie and Claire, from one of the genre\u2019s most popular and beloved authors.Jamie Fraser, erstwhile Jacobite and reluctant rebel, knows three things about the American rebellion: the Americans will win, unlikely as that seems in 1778; being on the winning side is no guarantee of survival; and he\u2019d rather die than face his illegitimate son \u2014 a young lieutenant in the British Army \u2014 across the barrel of a gun. Fraser\u2019s time-travelling wife, Claire, also knows a couple of things: that the Americans will win, but that the ultimate price of victory is a mystery. What she does believe is that the price won\u2019t include Jamie\u2019s life or happiness \u2014 not if she has anything to say.Claire\u2019s grown daughter Brianna, and her husband, Roger, watch the unfolding of Brianna\u2019s parents\u2019 history \u2014 a past that may be sneaking up behind their own family.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1370918297i/2832909.jpg", "genres": ["Time Travel", "Historical Romance", "Fantasy", "Historical", "Scotland", "Fiction", "Audiobook", "Adult", "Historical Fiction", "Romance"], "asin": "0752898477", "isbn": "0752898477", "isbn13": "9780752898476", "publisher": "Orion", "series": ["Le Chardon et le Tartan", "Outlander"], "author": ["Diana Gabaldon"], "publishDate": 1264060800000, "characters": ["Brianna Randall", "Michael Murray", "Jeremiah MacKenzie", "Young Ian Murray", "Claire Randall Fraser", "William Buccleigh MacKenzie", "Ge