{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6604794-the-sky-is-everywhere", "title": "The Sky Is Everywhere", "titleComplete": "The Sky Is Everywhere", "description": "Adrift after her sister Bailey's sudden death, Lennie finds herself torn between quiet, seductive Toby\u2014Bailey's boyfriend who shares her grief\u2014and Joe, the new boy in town who bursts with life and musical genius. Each offers Lennie something she desperately needs... though she knows if the two of them collide her whole world will explode.Join Lennie on this heartbreaking and hilarious journey of profound sorrow and mad love, as she makes colossal mistakes and colossal discoveries, as she traipses through band rooms and forest bedrooms and ultimately right into your heart.As much a celebration of love as a poignant portrait of loss, Lennie's struggle to sort her own melody out of the noise around her is always honest, often uproarious, and absolutely unforgettable.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1496659743i/6604794.jpg", "genres": ["Chick Lit", "Teen", "Young Adult Contemporary", "Death", "Young Adult", "Contemporary", "Fiction", "Realistic Fiction", "Romance", "Music"], "asin": "0803734956", "isbn": "0803734956", "isbn13": "9780803734951", "publisher": "Dial Books", "author": ["Jandy Nelson"], "publishDate": 1268121600000, "characters": ["Joe Fontaine", "Bailey Walker", "Gram", "Toby Shaw", "Marcus Fontaine", "Rachel Brazile", "Lennie Walker", "DougFred Fontaine"], "places": ["California"], "ratingHistogram": [2729, 6513, 21357, 35178, 38939], "ratingsCount": 104716, "reviewsCount": 10478, "numPages": 288, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Milwaukee County Teen Book Award", "awardedAt": 1293868800000, "category": "", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Boston Globe-Horn Book Award", "awardedAt": 1262332800000, "category": null, "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Lincoln Award", "awardedAt": 1357027200000, "category": null, "hasW