{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/18386.The_Death_of_Ivan_Ilych", "title": "The Death of Ivan Ilych", "titleComplete": "The Death of Ivan Ilych", "description": "Hailed as one of the world's supreme masterpieces on the subject of death and dying, The Death of Ivan Ilyich is the story of a worldly careerist, a high court judge who has never given the inevitability of his dying so much as a passing thought. But one day, death announces itself to him, and to his shocked surprise, he is brought face to face with his own mortality. How, Tolstoy asks, does an unreflective man confront his one and only moment of truth?This short novel was an artistic culmination of a profound spiritual crisis in Tolstoy's life, a nine-year period following the publication of Anna Karenina during which he wrote not a word of fiction.A thoroughly absorbing, and, at times, terrifying glimpse into the abyss of death, it is also a strong testament to the possibility of finding spiritual salvation.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1663546974i/18386.jpg", "genres": ["Short Stories", "Novella", "Philosophy", "Russia", "Literature", "Russian Literature", "Fiction", "19th Century", "Classics", "Novels"], "asin": "1600964338", "isbn": "1600964338", "isbn13": "9781600964336", "publisher": "Waking Lion Press", "author": ["Louise Maude", "Aylmer Maude", "Leo Tolstoy"], "publishDate": 1154588400000, "characters": ["Praskovya F\u00ebdorovna Golovina", "Gerasim", "Ivan Ilyich Golovin", "Peter Ivanovich", "Lisa Golovina"], "ratingHistogram": [1304, 5103, 26423, 59234, 59047], "ratingsCount": 151111, "reviewsCount": 10984, "numPages": 86, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/10073506-tinker-tailor-soldier-spy", "title": "Tinker, Tailor, Soldier, Spy", "titleComplete": "Tinker, Tailor, Soldier, Spy (George Smiley, #5; Karla Trilogy, #1)", "description": "A modern classic in which John le Carr\u00e9 expertly creates a total vision of a secret world, Tinker, Tailor, Soldier, Spy begins George Smiley's chess match of wills and wits with Karla, his Soviet counterpart. It is now beyond a doubt that a mole, implanted decades ago by Moscow Centre, has burrowed his way into the highest echelons of British Intelligence. His treachery has already blown some of its most vital operations and its best networks. It is clear that the double agent is one of its own kind. But which one? George Smiley is assigned to identify him. And once identified, the traitor must be destroyed.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1349070201i/10073506.jpg", "genres": ["Crime", "Suspense", "Mystery Thriller", "Novels", "Espionage", "Mystery", "Fiction", "Classics", "Thriller", "Spy Thriller"], "asin": "0143119788", "isbn": "0143119788", "isbn13": "9780143119784", "publisher": "Penguin Books", "series": ["The Karla Trilogy", "George Smiley"], "author": ["John le Carr\u00e9"], "publishDate": 1307430000000, "characters": ["Inspector Mendel", "Roy Bland", "Bill Haydon", "Connie Sachs", "Jim Prideaux", "Ricki Tarr", "Percy Alleline", "George Smiley", "Bill Roach", "Peter Guillam", "Oliver Lacon", "Aleksey Polyakov", "Roddy Martindale", "Toby Esterhase", "Ann Smiley"], "places": ["London, England"], "ratingHistogram": [2121, 4689, 15489, 33422, 36174], "ratingsCount": 91895, "reviewsCount": 5243, "numPages": 381, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "CWA Silver Dagger", "awardedAt": 126259200000, "category": null, "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/39058.The_Gormenghast_Novels", "title": "The Gormenghast Novels", "titleComplete": "The Gormenghast Novels (Gormenghast, #1-3)", "description": "A doomed lord, an emergent hero, and a dazzling array of bizarre creatures inhabit the magical world of the Gormenghast novels which, along with Tolkien's Lord of the Rings, reign as one of the undisputed fantasy classics of all time. At the center of it all is the seventy-seventh Earl, Titus Groan, who stands to inherit the miles of rambling stone and mortar that form Gormenghast Castle and its kingdom, unless the conniving Steerpike, who is determined to rise above his menial position and control the House of Groan, has his way.In these extraordinary novels, Peake has created a world where all is like a dream - lush, fantastical, and vivid. Accompanying the text are Peake's own drawings, illustrating the whole assembly of strange and marvelous creatures that inhabit Gormenghast.Also featuring:Introductory essays by Anthony Burgess and Quentin CrispTwelve critical essays, curated by Peake scholar Peter G. WinningtonFragment of the unpublished novel, Titus Awakes", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1651356062i/39058.jpg", "genres": ["Science Fiction Fantasy", "Science Fiction", "Literature", "Fantasy", "Gothic", "Speculative Fiction", "Fiction", "Horror", "Classics", "Novels"], "asin": "0879516283", "isbn": "0879516283", "isbn13": "9780879516284", "publisher": "Overlook Press", "series": ["Gormenghast"], "author": ["Quentin Crisp", "Mervyn Peake", "Anthony Burgess"], "publishDate": 817804800000, "characters": ["Mr. Flay", "Steerpike", "Fuchsia Groan", "Lord Sepulchrave", "Dr. Alfred Prunesquallor", "Gertrude Groan", "Clarice Groan", "Titus Groan", "Cora Groan", "Abiatha Swelter", "Keda", "Nannie Slagg"], "places": ["Gormenghast"], "ratingHistogram": [411, 597, 1466, 2760, 4013], "ratingsCount": 9247, "reviewsCount":