{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/10222.The_Far_Pavilions", "title": "The Far Pavilions", "titleComplete": "The Far Pavilions", "description": "A magnificent romantic/historical/adventure novel set in India at the time of mutiny. The Far Pavilions is a story of 19th Century India, when the thin patina of English rule held down dangerously turbulent undercurrents. It is a story about and English man - Ashton Pelham-Martyn - brought up as a Hindu and his passionate, but dangerous love for an Indian princess. It's a story of divided loyalties, of tender camaraderie, of greedy imperialism and of the clash between east and west. To the burning plains and snow-capped mountains of this great, humming continent, M.M. Kaye brings her quite exceptional gift of immediacy and meticulous historical accuracy, plus her insight into the human heart.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1403391799i/10222.jpg", "genres": ["Adventure", "Historical Romance", "Historical", "Classics", "India", "Fiction", "19th Century", "Historical Fiction", "Romance", "Asia"], "asin": "B004Y6MW0M", "isbn": "031215125X", "isbn13": "9780312151256", "publisher": "St. Martin's Griffin", "author": ["M.M. Kaye"], "publishDate": 853315200000, "places": ["Rajasthan", "Khyber Pakhtunkhwa", "Afghanistan", "Mardan", "South Asia", "Pakistan", "India"], "ratingHistogram": [543, 1429, 6905, 14735, 20098], "ratingsCount": 43710, "reviewsCount": 1604, "numPages": 958, "language": "English"}
