{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6192.Disgrace", "title": "Disgrace", "titleComplete": "Disgrace", "description": "Set in post-apartheid South Africa, J. M. Coetzee\u2019s searing novel tells the story of David Lurie, a twice divorced, 52-year-old professor of communications and Romantic Poetry at Cape Technical University. Lurie believes he has created a comfortable, if somewhat passionless, life for himself. He lives within his financial and emotional means. Though his position at the university has been reduced, he teaches his classes dutifully; and while age has diminished his attractiveness, weekly visits to a prostitute satisfy his sexual needs. He considers himself happy. However, when Lurie seduces one of his students, he sets in motion a chain of events that will shatter his complacency and leave him utterly disgraced.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1385161943i/6192.jpg", "genres": ["20th Century", "Literary Fiction", "Literature", "South Africa", "Contemporary", "Nobel Prize", "Fiction", "Africa", "Classics", "Novels"], "asin": "0143036378", "isbn": "0143036378", "isbn13": "9780143036371", "publisher": "Penguin Books", "author": ["J.M. Coetzee"], "publishDate": 1125385200000, "characters": ["Lucy Lurie", "Melanie Isaacs", "Petrus", "David Lurie", "Bev Shaw"], "places": ["Grahamstown", "South Africa", "Cape Town"], "ratingHistogram": [2488, 6869, 23597, 41408, 29110], "ratingsCount": 103472, "reviewsCount": 7862, "numPages": 220, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Booker Prize", "awardedAt": 915177600000, "category": null, "hasWon": null}, {"name": "National Book Critics Circle Award", "awardedAt": 915177600000, "category": "Fiction", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Commonwealth Writers' Prize", "awardedAt": 946713600000, "category": "Best Book Overall", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "The Best of the Booker", "awardedAt": 1199174400000, "category": null, "hasWon": null}, {"nam