{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/17728.The_House_of_Mirth", "title": "The House of Mirth", "titleComplete": "The House of Mirth", "description": "First published in 1905, The House of Mirth shocked the New York society it so deftly chronicles, portraying the moral, social and economic restraints on a woman who dared to claim the privileges of marriage without assuming the responsibilities.Lily Bart, beautiful, witty and sophisticated, is accepted by 'old money' and courted by the growing tribe of nouveaux riches. But as she nears thirty, her foothold becomes precarious; a poor girl with expensive tastes, she needs a husband to preserve her social standing, and to maintain her in the luxury she has come to expect. Whilst many have sought her, something - fastidiousness or integrity- prevents her from making a 'suitable' match.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1328729186i/17728.jpg", "genres": ["20th Century", "Classic Literature", "Literature", "Historical", "New York", "Fiction", "American", "Historical Fiction", "Classics", "Novels"], "asin": "1844082938", "isbn": "1844082938", "isbn13": "9781844082933", "publisher": "Virago UK", "author": ["Nina Bawden", "Edith Wharton"], "publishDate": 1137657600000, "characters": ["Julia Peniston", "Lily Bart", "Gus Trenor", "Judy Trenor", "Simon Rosedale", "George Dorset", "Lawrence Selden", "Gerty Farish", "Percy Gryce", "Bertha Dorset", "Lily Bart, Lawrence Selden, Simon Rosedale, Judy Trenor, Gus Trenor, Percy Gryce, Bertha Dorset, George Dorset, Gerty Farish, Ju", "Carry Fisher"], "places": ["New York (State)", "New York City, New York"], "ratingHistogram": [2375, 5345, 19343, 34952, 33724], "ratingsCount": 95739, "reviewsCount": 6149, "numPages": 351, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/991197.The_Complete_Persepolis", "title": "The Complete Persepolis", "titleComplete": "The Complete Persepolis", "description": "Here, in one volume: Marjane Satrapi's best-selling, internationally acclaimed memoir-in-comic-strips.Persepolis is the story of Satrapi's unforgettable childhood and coming of age within a large and loving family in Tehran during the Islamic Revolution; of the contradictions between private and public life in a country plagued by political upheaval; of her high school years in Vienna facing the trials of adolescence far from her family; of her homecoming\u2014both sweet and terrible; and, finally, of her self-imposed exile from her beloved homeland. It is the chronicle of a girlhood and adolescence at once outrageous and familiar, a young life entwined with the history of her country yet filled with the universal trials and joys of growing up.Edgy, searingly observant, and candid, often heartbreaking but threaded throughout with raw humor and hard-earned wisdom\u2014Persepolis is a stunning work from one of the most highly regarded, singularly talented graphic artists at work today.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1327876995i/991197.jpg", "genres": ["Graphic Novels", "Feminism", "Nonfiction", "Iran", "Memoir", "Comics", "History", "Autobiography", "Graphic Novels Comics", "Biography"], "asin": "0375714839", "isbn": "0375714839", "isbn13": "9780375714832", "publisher": "Pantheon Books", "series": ["Persepolis", "I Classici del Fumetto di Repubblica - Serie Oro"], "author": ["Marjane Satrapi"], "publishDate": 1193727600000, "characters": ["Mrs. Nasrine", "Khosro (Persepolis)", "Fereydoon Satrapi", "Anoosh Satrapi", "Mali (Persepolis)", "Mardana", "Zozo (Persepolis)", "Dr. Fathi", "Ebi Satrapi", "Ahmadi", "Taher Chaltchi", "Grandma Chaltchi", "Laly Jari", "Hossein (Bee Gees)", "Shahab", "Sherrie", "Peyman", "Marjane Satrapi", "Ka