{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/7824322-between-shades-of-gray", "title": "Between Shades of Gray", "titleComplete": "Between Shades of Gray", "description": "Lina is just like any other fifteen-year-old Lithuanian girl in 1941. She paints, she draws, she gets crushes on boys. Until one night when Soviet officers barge into her home, tearing her family from the comfortable life they've known. Separated from her father, forced onto a crowded and dirty train car, Lina, her mother, and her young brother slowly make their way north, crossing the Arctic Circle, to a work camp in the coldest reaches of Siberia. Here they are forced, under Stalin's orders, to dig for beets and fight for their lives under the cruelest of conditions.Lina finds solace in her art, meticulously\u2014and at great risk\u2014documenting events by drawing, hoping these messages will make their way to her father's prison camp to let him know they are still alive. It is a long and harrowing journey, spanning years and covering 6,500 miles, but it is through incredible strength, love, and hope that Lina ultimately survives. Between Shades of Gray is a novel that will steal your breath and capture your heart.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1327873479i/7824322.jpg", "genres": ["War", "Teen", "Russia", "World War II", "Historical", "Young Adult", "Fiction", "Audiobook", "Historical Fiction", "Romance"], "asin": "0399254129", "isbn": "0399254129", "isbn13": "9780399254123", "publisher": "Philomel Books", "author": ["Ruta Sepetys"], "publishDate": 1300777200000, "characters": ["Lina Vilkas", "Andrius Aras", "Elena Vilkas", "Jonas Vilkas"], "places": ["Siberia", "Lithuania", "Russia"], "ratingHistogram": [2093, 4160, 23397, 78982, 123274], "ratingsCount": 231906, "reviewsCount": 26323, "numPages": 344, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Georgia Peach Book Award", "awardedAt": 1325404800000, "category": "Honor book", 