{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/24192.The_Runaway_Jury", "title": "The Runaway Jury", "titleComplete": "The Runaway Jury", "description": "Every jury has a leader, and the verdict belongs to him. In Biloxi, Mississippi, a landmark tobacco trial with hundreds of millions of dollars at stake begins routinely, then swerves mysteriously off course. The jury is behaving strangely, and at least one juror is convinced he's being watched. Soon they have to be sequestered. Then a tip from an anonymous young woman suggests she is able to predict the jurors' increasingly odd behavior. Is the jury somehow being manipulated, or even controlled? If so, by whom? And, more importantly, why?From the Trade Paperback edition.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1388444668i/24192.jpg", "genres": ["Crime", "Suspense", "Mystery Thriller", "Law", "Mystery", "Fiction", "Thriller", "Adult Fiction", "Legal Thriller", "Novels"], "asin": "0385339690", "isbn": "0385339690", "isbn13": "9780385339698", "publisher": "Delta", "author": ["John Grisham"], "publishDate": 1145948400000, "characters": ["Rankin Fitch", "Wendall Rohr", "Celeste Wood", "Nicholas Easter"], "places": ["The United States of America", "Biloxi, Mississippi"], "ratingHistogram": [2677, 10811, 67388, 117309, 101951], "ratingsCount": 300136, "reviewsCount": 2639, "numPages": 464, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/45047384-the-house-in-the-cerulean-sea", "title": "The House in the Cerulean Sea", "titleComplete": "The House in the Cerulean Sea (The House in the Cerulean Sea, #1)", "description": "A magical island. A dangerous task. A burning secret.Linus Baker leads a quiet, solitary life. At forty, he lives in a tiny house with a devious cat and his old records. As a Case Worker at the Department in Charge Of Magical Youth, he spends his days overseeing the well-being of children in government-sanctioned orphanages.When Linus is unexpectedly summoned by Extremely Upper Management he's given a curious and highly classified assignment: travel to Marsyas Island Orphanage, where six dangerous children reside: a gnome, a sprite, a wyvern, an unidentifiable green blob, a were-Pomeranian, and the Antichrist. Linus must set aside his fears and determine whether or not they\u2019re likely to bring about the end of days.But the children aren\u2019t the only secret the island keeps. Their caretaker is the charming and enigmatic Arthur Parnassus, who will do anything to keep his wards safe. As Arthur and Linus grow closer, long-held secrets are exposed, and Linus must make a choice: destroy a home or watch the world burn.An enchanting story, masterfully told, The House in the Cerulean Sea is about the profound experience of discovering an unlikely family in an unexpected place\u2014and realizing that family is yours.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1569514209i/45047384.jpg", "genres": ["Magic", "Fantasy", "Young Adult", "LGBT", "Contemporary", "Fiction", "Adult", "Magical Realism", "Romance", "Queer"], "publisher": "Tor Books", "series": ["The House in the Cerulean Sea"], "author": ["T.J. Klune"], "publishDate": 1584428400000, "characters": ["Arthur Parnassus", "Linus Baker"], "places": ["Marsyas Island"], "ratingHistogram": [4406, 11639, 52806, 156920, 318251], "ratingsCount