{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/10603.Cujo", "title": "Cujo", "titleComplete": "Cujo", "description": "Durante toda su vida Cujo fue un buen perro, un San Bernardo grandote, pac\u00edfico, juguet\u00f3n y amante de los ni\u00f1os. Realmente se trataba de un perro bueno y feliz. Feliz hasta que le sucedi\u00f3 algo, y el cerebro de perro de Cujo se cubri\u00f3 de una de esas oscuridades que se alimentan de sangre. Ahora, se ha convertido en un perro asesino; doblemente cruel por cuanto la gente no conoce su mutaci\u00f3n y a\u00fan le ve en su anterior bondad. Heraldo de un peque\u00f1o Apocalipsis, Cujo desencadenar\u00e1 sobre un pueblo mod\u00e9lico un hurac\u00e1n de p\u00e1nico y de muerte.Uno de los grandes cl\u00e1sicos de Stephen King, el gran maestro actual de la literatura de terror.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1394208144i/10603.jpg", "genres": ["Suspense", "Dogs", "Animals", "Fantasy", "Fiction", "Audiobook", "Adult", "Horror", "Thriller", "Novels"], "asin": "0307348245", "isbn": "0307348245", "isbn13": "9780307348241", "publisher": "Debolsillo", "author": ["Stephen King"], "publishDate": 1149577200000, "characters": ["Joe Camber", "Brett Camber", "Cujo", "Roger Breakstone", "Vic Trenton", "Charity Camber", "Frank Dodd", "Steve Kemp", "Gary Pervier", "Tad Trenton", "Donna Trenton"], "places": ["Boston, Massachusetts", "Castle Rock, Maine", "Stratford, Connecticut"], "ratingHistogram": [6058, 21617, 79070, 90753, 77846], "ratingsCount": 275344, "reviewsCount": 7371, "numPages": 432, "language": "Spanish; Castilian", "awards": [{"name": "Locus Award", "awardedAt": 378720000000, "category": "Best Fantasy Novel", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Balrog Award", "awardedAt": 378720000000, "category": "Best Novel", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "British Fantasy Award", "awardedAt": 378720000000, "category": "Best Novel (August Derlith Fantasy Award)", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/68783.Girl_Interrupted", "title": "Girl, Interrupted", "titleComplete": "Girl, Interrupted", "description": "In 1967, after a session with a psychiatrist she'd never seen before, eighteen-year-old Susanna Kaysen was put in a taxi and sent to McLean Hospital. She spent most of the next two years on the ward for teenage girls in a psychiatric hospital as renowned for its famous clientele--Sylvia Plath, Robert Lowell, James Taylor, and Ray Charles--as for its progressive methods of treating those who could afford its sanctuary. Kaysen's memoir encompasses horror and razor-edged perception while providing vivid portraits of her fellow patients and their keepers. It is a brilliant evocation of a \"parallel universe\" set within the kaleidoscopically shifting landscape of the late sixties. Girl, Interrupted is a clear-sighted, unflinching documnet that gives lasting and specific dimension to our definitions of sane and insane, mental illness and recovery.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1475482930i/68783.jpg", "genres": ["Nonfiction", "Biography Memoir", "Memoir", "Classics", "Psychology", "Mental Health", "Contemporary", "Autobiography", "Mental Illness", "Biography"], "asin": "0679746048", "isbn": "0679746048", "isbn13": "9780679746041", "publisher": "Vintage ", "author": ["Susanna Kaysen"], "publishDate": 766738800000, "characters": ["Susanna Kaysen"], "places": ["Massachusetts"], "ratingHistogram": [3036, 11785, 56775, 89231, 72477], "ratingsCount": 233304, "reviewsCount": 9087, "numPages": 169, "language": "English"}
