{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/12432220-the-false-prince", "title": "The False Prince", "titleComplete": "The False Prince (Ascendance, #1)", "description": "In a discontent kingdom, civil war is brewing. To unify the divided people, Conner, a nobleman of the court, devises a cunning plan to find an impersonator of the king's long-lost son and install him as a puppet prince. Four orphans are recruited to compete for the role, including a defiant boy named Sage. Sage knows that Conner's motives are more than questionable, yet his life balances on a sword's point\u2014he must be chosen to play the prince or he will certainly be killed. But Sage's rivals have their own agendas as well.As Sage moves from a rundown orphanage to Conner's sumptuous palace, layer upon layer of treachery and deceit unfold, until finally, a truth is revealed that, in the end, may very well prove more dangerous than all of the lies taken together.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1585683740i/12432220.jpg", "genres": ["Childrens", "Adventure", "Young Adult Fantasy", "Fantasy", "Young Adult", "Fiction", "Middle Grade", "Mystery", "Audiobook", "Historical Fiction"], "asin": "0545284139", "isbn": "0545284139", "isbn13": "9780545284134", "publisher": "Scholastic, Inc.", "series": ["Ascendance"], "author": ["Jennifer A. Nielsen"], "publishDate": 1333263600000, "ratingHistogram": [1425, 2982, 12736, 31819, 43947], "ratingsCount": 92909, "reviewsCount": 11092, "numPages": 342, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Utah Book Award", "awardedAt": 1388563200000, "category": "Young Adult Literature", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Whitney Award", "awardedAt": 1325404800000, "category": "Best Youth Fiction", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Pennsylvania Young Readers' Choice Award", "awardedAt": 1388563200000, "category": "Grades 6-8", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Rhode Island Teen Book Award", "awardedAt": 1388563200000, "category