{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/77163.Stones_from_the_River", "title": "Stones from the River", "titleComplete": "Stones from the River (Burgdorf Cycle, #1)", "description": "Alternate cover edition of ISBN 9780684844770From the highly acclaimed, award-winning author of Floating in My Mother's Palm comes a stunning novel about ordinary people living in extraordinary times.Trudi Montag is a Zwerg\u2014a dwarf\u2014short, undesirable, different, the voice of anyone who has ever tried to fit in. Eventually she learns that being different is a secret that all humans share\u2014from her mother who flees into madness, to her friend Georg whose parents pretend he's a girl, to the Jews Trudy harbors in her cellar.Ursula Hegi brings us a timeless and unforgettable story in Trudi and a small town, weaving together a profound tapestry of emotional power, humanity, and truth.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1366513909i/77163.jpg", "genres": ["War", "World War II", "Holocaust", "Literary Fiction", "Historical", "Fiction", "Germany", "Book Club", "Historical Fiction", "Adult Fiction"], "publisher": "Scribner Paperback Fiction", "series": ["Burgdorf Cycle"], "author": ["Ursula Hegi"], "publishDate": 794044800000, "places": ["Germany"], "ratingHistogram": [1546, 4144, 16939, 33731, 38663], "ratingsCount": 95023, "reviewsCount": 2190, "numPages": 525, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "PEN/Faulkner Award for Fiction", "awardedAt": 788947200000, "category": null, "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Washington State Book Award", "awardedAt": 788947200000, "category": null, "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Premio Grinzane Cavour", "awardedAt": 946713600000, "category": "Narrativa Straniera", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/31434883-eleanor-oliphant-is-completely-fine", "title": "Eleanor Oliphant Is Completely Fine", "titleComplete": "Eleanor Oliphant Is Completely Fine", "description": "No one\u2019s ever told Eleanor that life should be better than fineMeet Eleanor Oliphant: she struggles with appropriate social skills and tends to say exactly what she\u2019s thinking. Nothing is missing in her carefully timetabled life of avoiding unnecessary human contact, where weekends are punctuated by frozen pizza, vodka, and phone chats with Mummy. But everything changes when Eleanor meets Raymond, the bumbling and deeply unhygienic IT guy from her office. When she and Raymond together save Sammy, an elderly gentleman who has fallen, the three rescue one another from the lives of isolation that they had been living. Ultimately, it is Raymond\u2019s big heart that will help Eleanor find the way to repair her own profoundly damaged one. If she does, she'll learn that she, too, is capable of finding friendship\u2014and even love\u2014after all.Smart, warm, uplifting, Eleanor Oliphant Is Completely Fine is the story of an out-of-the-ordinary heroine whose deadpan weirdness and unconscious wit make for an irresistible journey as she realizes. . .  the only way to survive is to open your heart.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1493724347i/31434883.jpg", "genres": ["Literary Fiction", "Contemporary", "Mental Health", "Audiobook", "Adult", "Fiction", "Book Club", "Adult Fiction", "Romance", "Novels"], "asin": "0735220689", "isbn": "0735220689", "isbn13": "9780735220683", "publisher": "Pamela Dorman Books / Viking", "author": ["Gail Honeyman"], "publishDate": 1494313200000, "characters": ["Eleanor Oliphant", "Laura Thom", "Raymond Gibbons", "Sammy Thom", "Dr. Maria Temple", "Mrs. Gibbons"], "places": ["Scotland", "United Kingdom", "Glasgow, Scotland"], "ratingHistogram": [12640, 32252, 14872