{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/35879889-christy", "title": "Christy", "titleComplete": "Christy", "description": "The train taking nineteen-year-old teacher Christy Huddleston from her home in Asheville, North Carolina, might as well be transporting her to another world. The Smoky Mountain community of Cutter Gap feels suspended in time, trapped by poverty, superstitions, and century-old traditions.But as Christy struggles to find acceptance in her new home, some see her \u2014 and her one-room school \u2014 as a threat to their way of life. Her faith is challenged and her heart is torn between two strong men with conflicting views about how to care for the families of the Cove.Yearning to make a difference, will Christy\u2019s determination and devotion be enough?", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1507060335i/35879889.jpg", "genres": ["Inspirational", "Romance", "Christian", "Historical", "Young Adult", "Fiction", "Christian Fiction", "Adult", "Historical Fiction", "Classics"], "asin": "B0745KTJSY", "publisher": "Evergreen Farm", "author": ["Catherine Marshall"], "publishDate": 1507014000000, "characters": ["Fairlight Spencer", "Ida Grantland", "Christy Rudd Huddleston", "David Grantland", "Bird's Eye Taylor", "Lundy Tylor", "Alice Henderson", "Dr. Neil Macneill"], "places": ["Tennessee", "North Carolina"], "ratingHistogram": [679, 1664, 8061, 17292, 26268], "ratingsCount": 53964, "reviewsCount": 2170, "numPages": 514, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/307791.The_City_of_Ember", "title": "The City of Ember", "titleComplete": "The City of Ember (Book of Ember, #1)", "description": "An alternate cover edition can be found here.Many hundreds of years ago, the city of Ember was created by the Builders to contain everything needed for human survival. It worked\u2026but now the storerooms are almost out of food, crops are blighted, corruption is spreading through the city and worst of all\u2014the lights are failing. Soon Ember could be engulfed by darkness\u2026But when two children, Lina and Doon, discover fragments of an ancient parchment, they begin to wonder if there could be a way out of Ember. Can they decipher the words from long ago and find a new future for everyone? Will the people of Ember listen to them?", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1591616783i/307791.jpg", "genres": ["Childrens", "Adventure", "Post Apocalyptic", "Science Fiction", "Fantasy", "School", "Young Adult", "Dystopia", "Fiction", "Middle Grade"], "asin": "0375822747", "isbn": "0375822747", "isbn13": "9780375822742", "publisher": "Random House Children's Books", "series": ["Book of Ember "], "author": ["Jeanne DuPrau"], "publishDate": 1041408000000, "characters": ["Lina Mayfleet", "Doon Harrow"], "ratingHistogram": [4975, 16511, 67807, 101753, 85303], "ratingsCount": 276349, "reviewsCount": 12775, "numPages": 270, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "California Book Award", "awardedAt": 1041408000000, "category": "Young Adult (Silver)", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Maryland Black-Eyed Susan Book Award", "awardedAt": 1136102400000, "category": "Grade 6-9", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Rhode Island Teen Book Award", "awardedAt": 1104566400000, "category": null, "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Vermont Golden Dome Book Award", "awardedAt": 1104566400000, "category": null, "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Child Magazine Best Book of the Year", "a