{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/28407.Germinal", "title": "Germinal", "titleComplete": "Germinal", "description": "The thirteenth novel in \u00c9mile Zola\u2019s great Rougon-Macquart sequence, Germinal expresses outrage at the exploitation of the many by the few, but also shows humanity\u2019s capacity for compassion and hope.Etienne Lantier, an unemployed railway worker, is a clever but uneducated young man with a dangerous temper. Forced to take a back-breaking job at Le Voreux mine when he cannot get other work, he discovers that his fellow miners are ill, hungry, in debt, and unable to feed and clothe their families. When conditions in the mining community deteriorate even further, Lantier finds himself leading a strike that could mean starvation or salvation for all.\u2022New translation\u2022 Includes introduction, suggestions for further reading, filmography, chronology, explanatory notes, and glossary", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1628462562i/28407.jpg", "genres": ["Novels", "Literature", "Roman", "Historical", "Fiction", "French Literature", "19th Century", "Historical Fiction", "Classics", "France"], "asin": "0140447423", "isbn": "0140447423", "isbn13": "9780140447422", "publisher": "Penguin Classics", "series": ["Les Rougon-Macquart"], "author": ["\u00c9mile Zola", "Roger Pearson"], "publishDate": 1085468400000, "characters": ["Zacharie Maheu", "Maigrat", "Souvarine", "\u00c9tienne Lantier", "Catherine Maheu", "L\u00e9onore Maheu", "Deneulin", "Pluchart", "Paul N\u00e9grel", "Chaval", "Alzire Maheu", "C\u00e9cile Gr\u00e9goire", "Madame Hennebeau", "Monsieur Gr\u00e9goire", "Constance Maheude", "Rasseneur", "Father Bonnemort", "Jeanlin Maheu", "Madame Gr\u00e9goire", "Monsieur Hennebeau", "Toussaint Maheu"], "ratingHistogram": [675, 1457, 5383, 12128, 16855], "ratingsCount": 36498, "reviewsCount": 2022, "numPages": 592, "language": "English"}
