{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/19405702-walks-away-woman", "title": "Walks Away Woman", "titleComplete": "Walks Away Woman", "description": "Ki Longfellow, acclaimed author of Flow Down Like Silver: Hypatia of Alexandria, The Secret Magdalene, and Houdini Heart has penned Walks Away Woman, a remarkable story of an ordinary woman driven to an extraordinary decision. Overwhelmed, overwrought, and overweight, an everyday housewife walks into the Sonoran Desert to die.But there's more to a desert than sand or death. There's thorns, venom, claws, heat, thirst, other people\u2014and unexpected adventure.As she says, \"It's because your gums are receding and your hair is thinning and your neckline is sagging. It's because all you ever had was your youth, and you spent that so long ago now it's hard to remember what you bought with it. Mrs. Warner shuddered in her loosening skin, was almost running now. It's because you're scared. Lately you're so scared and so aimless and so useless you sleep half the day and panic half the night. In between, you watch TV to ward off the evil of watching yourself. So\u2014if not death, then what?\"When she tripped over a rock\u2014and in tripping, plunged over the edge of a cliff\u2014Mrs. Warner had forgotten the desert, the cacti, the heat, the hunger, the thirst. All that was left was an ever increasing panic and an ever deepening desperation. And then there was the shock of falling and the screaming inside: Here we go, here we go\u2014but don't hurt, don't hurt. Oh god, please! Don't hurt!After that, there was nothing.\"Until she woke up at the bottom of an arroyo with a lot of surviving to do. And all she had was her purse. It wasn't much to face a desert with, but Mrs. Warner, born Molly Brock, was in a fight for her life, the life she didn't want until she was just about to lose it.What's an everyday housewife to do? In Molly's case, a lot. And every bit of it changing her from ordinary to extraordinary.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1386953097i/19405702.jpg", "genres": ["Adventure", "Humor", "Literature", "Contemporary", "Womens", "Fiction", "Book Club", "Survival", "Thriller", "Novels"], "asin": "1937819906", "isbn": "1937819906", "isbn13": "9781937819903", "publisher": "Eio Books", "author": ["Ki Longfellow"], "publishDate": 1386403200000, "ratingHistogram": [8, 15, 50, 555, 526], "ratingsCount": 1154, "reviewsCount": 132, "numPages": 254, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/3463.A_Bend_in_the_Road", "title": "A Bend in the Road", "titleComplete": "A Bend in the Road", "description": "Miles Ryan's life seemed to end the day his wife was killed in a hit-and-run accident two years ago. Missy had been his first love, and Miles fervently believes she will be his last. As a deputy in the North Carolina town of New Bern, Miles Ryan not only grieves for Missy, but also longs to bring the unknown driver to justice. Then Miles meets Sarah Andrews. The second grade teacher of his son, Jonah, Sarah had left Baltimore after a difficult divorce to start over in the gentler surroundings of New Bern. Perhaps it's her own emotional wounds that make her sensitive to the hurt she first sees in Jonah's eyes, and then his father's. Tentatively, Sarah and Miles reach out to each other. Soon they are both laughing for the first time in years . . . and falling in love. Neither will be able to guess how closely linked they are to a shocking secret -- one that will force them to question everything they ever believed in . . . and make a heartbreaking choice that will change their lives forever.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1388453919i/3463.jpg", "genres": ["Chick Lit", "Drama", "Contemporary Romance", "Contemporary", "Fiction", "Adult", "Mystery", "Audiobook", "Adult Fiction", "Romance"], "asin": "0446696137", "isbn": "0446696137", "isbn13": "9780446696135", "publisher": "Grand Central Publishing", "author": ["Nicholas Sparks"], "publishDate": 1112342400000, "characters": ["Sarah Andrews", "Miles Ryan", "Jonah Ryan"], "places": ["New Bern, North Carolina"], "ratingHistogram": [1773, 6764, 33254, 54453, 58148], "ratingsCount": 154392, "reviewsCount": 4617, "numPages": 341, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/3570231-at-grave-s-end", "title": "At Grave's End", "titleComplete": "At Grave's End (Night Huntress, #3)", "description": "Some Things Won\u2019t Stay Buried \u2026 At Grave\u2019s EndIt should be the best time of half-vampire Cat Crawfield\u2019s life. With her undead lover Bones at her side, she\u2019s successfully protected mortals from the rogue undead. But though Cat\u2019s worn disguise after disguise to keep her true identity a secret from the brazen bloodsuckers, her cover\u2019s finally been blown, placing her in terrible danger.As if that wasn\u2019t enough, a woman from Bones\u2019s past is determined to bury him once and for all. Caught in the crosshairs of a vengeful vamp, yet determined to help Bones stop a lethal magic from being unleashed, Cat\u2019s about to learn the true meaning of bad blood. And the tricks she\u2019s learned as a special agent won\u2019t help her. She will need to fully embrace her vampire instincts in order to save herself \u2013 and Bones \u2013 from a fate worse than the grave.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1448167943i/3570231.jpg", "genres": ["Supernatural", "Fantasy", "Urban Fantasy", "Vampires", "Paranormal Romance", "Adult", "Fiction", "Audiobook", "Paranormal", "Romance"], "asin": "0061583073", "isbn": "0061583073", "isbn13": "9780061583070", "publisher": "Avon", "series": ["Night Huntress Universe", "Night Huntress"], "author": ["Jeaniene Frost"], "publishDate": 1229760000000, "characters": ["Annette De Witt", "Don Williams", "Vlad Tepesh", "Catherine Crawfield-Russell", "Spade (Night Huntress series)", "Ian Flannery", "Denise MacGregor", "Bones (Night Huntress series)", "Tate Bradley", "Mencheres"], "places": ["South Dakota", "Tennessee", "British Columbia", "Canada", "Richmond, Virginia", "Virginia"], "ratingHistogram": [862, 2186, 12064, 29243, 44637], "ratingsCount": 88992, "reviewsCount": 3031, "numPa