{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/5168.Where_the_Heart_Is", "title": "Where the Heart Is", "titleComplete": "Where the Heart Is", "description": "Talk about unlucky sevens. An hour ago, seventeen-year-old, seven months pregnant Novalee Nation was heading for California with her boyfriend. Now she finds herself stranded at a Wal-Mart in Sequoyah, Oklahoma, with just $7.77 in change. But Novalee is about to discover hidden treasures in this small Southwest town--a group of down-to-earth, deeply caring people willing to help a homeless, jobless girl living secretly in a Wal-Mart. From Bible-thumping blue-haired Sister Thelma Husband to eccentric librarian Forney Hull who loves Novalee more than she loves herself, they are about to take her--and you, too--on a moving, funny, and unforgettable journey to . . . Where the Heart Is.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1327959469i/5168.jpg", "genres": ["Chick Lit", "Drama", "Contemporary", "Young Adult", "Fiction", "Adult", "Realistic Fiction", "Adult Fiction", "Romance", "Novels"], "isbn": "0446672211", "isbn13": "9780446672214", "publisher": "Grand Central Publishing", "author": ["Billie Letts"], "publishDate": 896684400000, "places": ["Oklahoma"], "ratingHistogram": [2547, 9915, 53321, 92592, 88811], "ratingsCount": 247186, "reviewsCount": 4176, "numPages": 376, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Eliot Rosewater Indiana High School Book Award", "awardedAt": 946713600000, "category": null, "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/27883214-caraval", "title": "Caraval", "titleComplete": "Caraval (Caraval, #1)", "description": "A legendary competition.A mesmerizing romance.An unbreakable bondbetween two sisters.Scarlett Dragna has never left the tiny island where she and her sister, Tella, live with their powerful, and cruel, father. Now Scarlett\u2019s father has arranged a marriage for her, and Scarlett thinks her dreams of seeing Caraval\u2014the faraway, once-a-year performance where the audience participates in the show\u2014are over.But this year, Scarlett\u2019s long-dreamt-of invitation finally arrives. With the help of a mysterious sailor, Tella whisks Scarlett away to the show. Only, as soon as they arrive, Tella is kidnapped by Caraval\u2019s mastermind organizer, Legend. It turns out that this season\u2019s Caraval revolves around Tella, and whoever finds her first is the winner.Scarlett has been told that everything that happens during Caraval is only an elaborate performance. Nevertheless she becomes enmeshed in a game of love, heartbreak, and magic. And whether Caraval is real or not, Scarlett must find Tella before the five nights of the game are over or a dangerous domino effect of consequences will be set off, and her beloved sister will disappear forever.Welcome, welcome to Caraval . . . beware of getting swept too far away.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1465563623i/27883214.jpg", "genres": ["Magic", "Adventure", "Young Adult Fantasy", "High Fantasy", "Fantasy", "Young Adult", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Audiobook", "Romance"], "asin": "1250095255", "isbn": "1250095255", "isbn13": "9781250095251", "publisher": "Flatiron Books", "series": ["Caraval"], "author": ["Stephanie Garber"], "publishDate": 1485849600000, "characters": ["Dante (Caraval)", "Donatella \"Tella\" Dragna", "Annalise Dragna", "Scarlett Dragna", "Marcello Dragna", "Legend", "Julian Santos"], "ratingHi