{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/41057294-normal-people", "title": "Normal People", "titleComplete": "Normal People", "description": "At school Connell and Marianne pretend not to know each other. He\u2019s popular and well-adjusted, star of the school soccer team while she is lonely, proud, and intensely private. But when Connell comes to pick his mother up from her housekeeping job at Marianne\u2019s house, a strange and indelible connection grows between the two teenagers - one they are determined to conceal.A year later, they\u2019re both studying at Trinity College in Dublin. Marianne has found her feet in a new social world while Connell hangs at the sidelines, shy and uncertain. Throughout their years in college, Marianne and Connell circle one another, straying toward other people and possibilities but always magnetically, irresistibly drawn back together. Then, as she veers into self-destruction and he begins to search for meaning elsewhere, each must confront how far they are willing to go to save the other.Sally Rooney brings her brilliant psychological acuity and perfectly spare prose to a story that explores the subtleties of class, the electricity of first love, and the complex entanglements of family and friendship.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1571423190i/41057294.jpg", "genres": ["Literary Fiction", "Ireland", "Contemporary", "Audiobook", "Fiction", "Adult", "Coming Of Age", "Adult Fiction", "Romance", "Novels"], "asin": "1984822179", "isbn": "1984822179", "isbn13": "9781984822178", "publisher": "Hogarth", "author": ["Sally Rooney"], "publishDate": 1555398000000, "characters": ["Helen Brophy", "Lorraine Waldron", "Marianne Sheridan", "Rachel Moran", "Connell Waldron"], "places": ["Ireland", "Dublin"], "ratingHistogram": [36796, 106202, 290246, 434271, 376588], "ratingsCount": 1244103, "reviewsCount": 120282, "numPages": 273, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name":