{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/110494.Living_Dead_in_Dallas", "title": "Living Dead in Dallas", "titleComplete": "Living Dead in Dallas (Sookie Stackhouse, #2)", "description": "Cocktail waitress Sookie Stackhouse is having a streak of bad luck. First her co-worker is killed, and no one seems to care. Then she comes face to-face with a beastly creature that gives her a painful and poisonous lashing. Enter the vampires, who graciously suck the poison from her veins (like they didn't enjoy it).The point is: they saved her life. So when one of the bloodsuckers asks for a favor, she obliges - and soon Sookie's in Dallas, using her telepathic skills to search for a missing vampire. She's supposed to interview certain humans involved, but she makes one condition: the vampires must promise to behave and let the humans go unharmed. But that's easier said than done, and all it takes is one delicious blonde and one small mistake for things to turn deadly....", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1329501808i/110494.jpg", "genres": ["Supernatural", "Fantasy", "Urban Fantasy", "Vampires", "Paranormal Romance", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Adult", "Paranormal", "Romance"], "asin": "1841493007", "isbn": "1841493007", "isbn13": "9781841493008", "publisher": "Orbit", "series": ["Sookie Stackhouse"], "author": ["Charlaine Harris"], "publishDate": 1080806400000, "characters": ["Eric Northman", "Pam Ravenscroft", "Tara Thornton", "Barry \"Bellboy\" Horowitz", "Jason Stackhouse", "Sookie Stackhouse", "Bill Compton", "Sam Merlotte"], "places": ["Bon Temps, Louisiana", "Dallas, Texas"], "ratingHistogram": [2721, 10926, 59608, 96228, 80409], "ratingsCount": 249892, "reviewsCount": 7514, "numPages": 291, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Lord Ruthven Award", "awardedAt": 1041408000000, "category": "Fiction", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/35519.The_Power_of_Myth", "title": "The Power of Myth", "titleComplete": "The Power of Myth", "description": "The Power Of Myth launched an extraordinary resurgence of interest in Joseph Campbell and his work. A preeminent scholar, writer, and teacher, he has had a profound influence on millions of people. To him, mythology was the \"song of the universe, the music of the spheres.\" With Bill Moyers, one of America's most prominent journalists, as his thoughtful and engaging interviewer, The Power Of Myth touches on subjects from modern marriage to virgin births, from Jesus to John Lennon, offering a brilliant combination of intelligence and wit.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1327878742i/35519.jpg", "genres": ["Mythology", "Nonfiction", "Philosophy", "Writing", "Spirituality", "Religion", "History", "Psychology", "Anthropology", "Classics"], "asin": "0385418868", "isbn": "0385418868", "isbn13": "9780385418867", "publisher": "Anchor", "series": ["Joseph Campbell and Power of Myth"], "author": ["Bill Moyers", "Joseph Campbell"], "publishDate": 581151600000, "ratingHistogram": [868, 1682, 6585, 15623, 25667], "ratingsCount": 50425, "reviewsCount": 2308, "numPages": 293, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/7728.Antigone", "title": "Antigone", "titleComplete": "Antigone (The Theban Plays, #3)", "description": "The curse placed on Oedipus lingers and haunts a younger generation in this new and brilliant translation of Sophocles' classic drama. The daughter of Oedipus and Jocasta, Antigone is an unconventional heroine who pits her beliefs against the King of Thebes in a bloody test of wills that leaves few unharmed. Emotions fly as she challenges the king for the right to bury her own brother. Determined but doomed, Antigone shows her inner strength throughout the play.Antigone raises issues of law and morality that are just as relevant today as they were more than two thousand years ago. Whether this is your first reading or your twentieth, Antigone will move you as few pieces of literature can.To make this quintessential Greek drama more accessible to the modern reader, this Prestwick House Literary Touchstone Edition includes a glossary of difficult terms, a list of vocabulary words, and convenient sidebar notes. By providing these, it is our intention that readers will more fully enjoy the beauty, wisdom, and intent of the play.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1486701308i/7728.jpg", "genres": ["Mythology", "Drama", "Literature", "High School", "Read For School", "School", "Theatre", "Fiction", "Classics", "Plays"], "asin": "1580493882", "isbn": "1580493882", "isbn13": "9781580493888", "publisher": "Prestwick House, Inc.", "series": ["The Theban Plays"], "author": ["Sophocles"], "publishDate": 1133337600000, "characters": ["Haemon", "Ismene (sister of Antigone)", "Eurydice (wife of Creon)", "Creon", "Antigone", "Tiresias"], "ratingHistogram": [3598, 13865, 44702, 49203, 34429], "ratingsCount": 145797, "reviewsCount": 5634, "numPages": 80, "language": "English"}
