{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/41684.The_Jungle_Books", "title": "The Jungle Books", "titleComplete": "The Jungle Books", "description": "The Jungle Books can be regarded as classic stories told by an adult to children. But they also constitute a complex literary work of art in which the whole of Kipling's philosophy of life is expressed in miniature. They are best known for the 'Mowgli' stories; the tale of a baby abandoned and brought up by wolves, educated in the ways and secrets of the jungle by Kaa the python, Baloo the bear, and Bagheera the black panther. The stories, a mixture of fantasy, myth, and magic, are underpinned by Kipling's abiding preoccupation with the theme of self-discovery, and the nature of the 'Law'.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1349066474i/41684.jpg", "genres": ["Childrens", "Adventure", "Short Stories", "Literature", "Fantasy", "Animals", "Young Adult", "India", "Fiction", "Classics"], "asin": "0451529758", "isbn": "0451529758", "isbn13": "9780451529756", "publisher": "Signet Classics", "series": ["The Jungle Book"], "author": ["Rudyard Kipling", "Alev Lytle Croutier"], "publishDate": 1115103600000, "characters": ["Nagaina", "Shere Khan", "Hathin", "Bagheera (Rudyard Kipling)", "Darzee", "Tabaqui", "Messua", "Baloo (Rudyard Kipling)", "Kaa", "Mowgli (Rudyard Kipling)", "Rikki-Tikki-Tavi", "Nag", "Akela"], "ratingHistogram": [1013, 3887, 19683, 31072, 31358], "ratingsCount": 87013, "reviewsCount": 1297, "numPages": 368, "language": "English"}
