{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/821611.The_Story_of_My_Life", "title": "The Story of My Life", "titleComplete": "The Story of My Life", "description": "When she was 19 months old, Helen Keller (1880\u20131968) suffered a severe illness that left her blind and deaf. Not long after, she also became mute. Her tenacious struggle to overcome these handicaps-with the help of her inspired teacher, Anne Sullivan-is one of the great stories of human courage and dedication. In this classic autobiography, first published in 1903, Miss Keller recounts the first 22 years of her life, including the magical moment at the water pump when, recognizing the connection between the word \"water\" and the cold liquid flowing over her hand, she realized that objects had names. Subsequent experiences were equally noteworthy: her joy at eventually learning to speak, her friendships with Oliver Wendell Holmes, Edward Everett Hale and other notables, her education at Radcliffe (from which she graduated cum laude), and-underlying all-her extraordinary relationship with Miss Sullivan, who showed a remarkable genius for communicating with her eager and quick-to-learn pupil.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1320429331i/821611.jpg", "genres": ["Nonfiction", "Biography Memoir", "Memoir", "History", "Historical", "Audiobook", "Disability", "Autobiography", "Classics", "Biography"], "asin": "0553213873", "isbn": "0553213873", "isbn13": "9780553213874", "publisher": "Bantam Classics", "author": ["Helen Keller"], "publishDate": 641545200000, "characters": ["Anne Sullivan", "Helen Keller"], "places": ["Boston, Massachusetts", "Tuscumbia, Alabama", "Alabama"], "ratingHistogram": [3596, 6314, 26906, 47781, 61490], "ratingsCount": 146087, "reviewsCount": 3173, "numPages": 240, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6325285-rubinrot", "title": "Rubinrot", "titleComplete": "Rubinrot (Edelstein-Trilogie, #1)", "description": "Manchmal ist es ein echtes Kreuz, in einer Familie zu leben, die jede Menge Geheimnisse hat. Der \u00dcberzeugung ist zumindest die 16-j\u00e4hrige Gwendolyn.Bis sie sich eines Tages aus heiterem Himmel im London um die letzte Jahrhundertwende wiederfindet. Und ihr klar wird, dass ausgerechnet sie das allergr\u00f6\u00dfte Geheimnis ihrer Familie ist. Was ihr dagegen nicht klar ist: Dass man sich zwischen den Zeiten m\u00f6glichst nicht verlieben sollte. Denn das macht die Sache erst recht kompliziert!", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1327918185i/6325285.jpg", "genres": ["Time Travel", "Science Fiction", "Young Adult Fantasy", "Fantasy", "Historical", "Young Adult", "Fiction", "Paranormal", "Historical Fiction", "Romance"], "asin": "3401063340", "isbn": "3401063340", "isbn13": "9783401063348", "publisher": "Arena Verlag", "series": ["Edelstein-Trilogie"], "author": ["Kerstin Gier"], "publishDate": 1231228800000, "characters": ["Grace Shepherd", "Leslie Hay", "Gideon de Villiers", "James Augustus Peregrine Pympoole-Bothame", "Gwendolyn Shepherd", "Cynthia Dale", "Gordan Gelderman"], "places": ["London, England", "England"], "ratingHistogram": [2020, 5491, 25600, 54933, 61218], "ratingsCount": 149262, "reviewsCount": 12095, "numPages": 345, "language": "German"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/53496.Walk_Two_Moons", "title": "Walk Two Moons", "titleComplete": "Walk Two Moons", "description": "\"How about a story? Spin us a yarn.\"Instantly, Phoebe Winterbottom came to mind. \"I could tell you an extensively strange story,\" I warned.\"Oh, good!\" Gram said. \"Delicious!\"And that is how I happened to tell them about Phoebe, her disappearing mother, and the lunatic.As Sal entertains her grandparents with Phoebe's outrageous story, her own story begins to unfold \u2014 the story of a thirteen-year-old girl whose only wish is to be reunited with her missing mother.In her own award-winning style, Sharon Creech intricately weaves together two tales, one funny, one bittersweet, to create a heartwarming, compelling, and utterly moving story of love, loss, and the complexity of human emotion.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1389035862i/53496.jpg", "genres": ["Childrens", "Family", "School", "Young Adult", "Contemporary", "Fiction", "Middle Grade", "Realistic Fiction", "Classics", "Read For School"], "asin": "0060739495", "isbn": "0060739495", "isbn13": "9780060739492", "publisher": "HarperTrophy", "author": ["Sharon Creech"], "publishDate": 832921200000, "characters": ["Phoebe Winterbottom", "Gramps Hiddle", "Margaret Cadaver", "Gram Hiddle", "Salamanca Tree Hiddle"], "places": ["Lewiston, Idaho", "Ohio", "Kentucky"], "ratingHistogram": [3973, 9702, 34188, 54125, 63664], "ratingsCount": 165652, "reviewsCount": 7905, "numPages": 280, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Newbery Medal", "awardedAt": 788947200000, "category": null, "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Vermont Golden Dome Book Award", "awardedAt": 820483200000, "category": null, "hasWon": null}, {"name": "W.H. Smith's Mind-Boggling Books Award", "awardedAt": 820483200000, "category": "", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Oklahoma Sequoyah Award", "awardedAt": 852105600000, "category": "YA", "hasWon