{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/18045891-sharp-objects", "title": "Sharp Objects", "titleComplete": "Sharp Objects", "description": "Fresh from a brief stay at a psych hospital, reporter Camille Preaker faces a troubling assignment: she must return to her tiny hometown to cover the unsolved murder of a preteen girl and the disappearance of another. For years, Camille has hardly spoken to her neurotic, hypochondriac mother or to the half-sister she barely knows: a beautiful thirteen-year-old with an eerie grip on the town. Now, installed in her old bedroom in her family's Victorian mansion, Camille finds herself identifying with the young victims\u2014a bit too strongly. Dogged by her own demons, she must unravel the psychological puzzle of her own past if she wants to get the story\u2014and survive this homecoming.Librarian's Note: this is an alternate cover edition - ISBN 10: 0307341550 (ISBN 13: 9780307341556)", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1475695315i/18045891.jpg", "genres": ["Crime", "Suspense", "Mystery Thriller", "Horror", "Contemporary", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Audiobook", "Adult", "Thriller"], "publisher": "Broadway Paperbacks", "author": ["Gillian Flynn"], "publishDate": 1185865200000, "characters": ["Alan Crellin", "Ann Nash", "John Keene", "Natalie Keene", "Annabelle Gasser and Jackie O'Neele", "Kylie, Kelsey and Kelsey", "Katie Lacey", "Gayla (Sharp Objects)", "Amma Crellin", "Frank Curry", "Meredith Wheeler", "Camille Preaker", "Marian Crellin", "James Capisi", "Chief Bill Vickery", "Richard Willis", "Adora Crellin"], "places": ["Chicago, Illinois", "Missouri", "Wind Gap, Missouri"], "ratingHistogram": [14379, 43231, 195261, 389469, 337935], "ratingsCount": 980275, "reviewsCount": 61919, "numPages": 254, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Barry Award", "awardedAt": 1167638400000, "category": "Best First Novel", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "CWA New Blood Dagger", "a