{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/12914.The_Aeneid", "title": "The Aeneid", "titleComplete": "The Aeneid", "description": "The Aeneid \u2013 thrilling, terrifying and poignant in equal measure \u2013 has inspired centuries of artists, writers and musicians.Virgil\u2019s epic tale tells the story of Aeneas, a Trojan hero, who flees his city after its fall, with his father Anchises and his young son Ascanius \u2013 for Aeneas is destined to found Rome and father the Roman race. As Aeneas journeys closer to his goal, he must first prove his worth and attain the maturity necessary for such an illustrious task. He battles raging storms in the Mediterranean, encounters the fearsome Cyclopes, falls in love with Dido, Queen of Carthage, travels into the Underworld and wages war in Italy.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1386923968i/12914.jpg", "genres": ["Epic", "Mythology", "Ancient", "Classic Literature", "Literature", "Fantasy", "School", "Fiction", "Classics", "Poetry"], "asin": "0679729526", "isbn": "0679729526", "isbn13": "9780679729525", "publisher": "Vintage", "author": ["Robert Fitzgerald", "Virgil", "David   West"], "publishDate": 645519600000, "characters": ["Anchises", "Mercury (God)", "Dido of Carthage", "Venus (goddess)", "Ixion", "Neoptolemus", "Ascanius", "Sybil (Ancient oracle)", "Turnus (King of the Rutuli)", "Misenus", "Charon (mythology)", "Aeneas", "Juno (Goddess)", "Iris (Goddess)", "Jupiter (God)", "Pallas (son of Evander)", "Priam", "Lavinia (mythology)", "Vulcan (God)", "Camilla (mythology)"], "places": ["Carthage", "Troy", "Sicily", "Rome", "Italy"], "ratingHistogram": [2258, 8753, 32814, 42829, 39650], "ratingsCount": 126304, "reviewsCount": 4016, "numPages": 442, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/73968.Love_Story", "title": "Love Story", "titleComplete": "Love Story (Love Story, #1)", "description": "Oliver Barrett IV, a wealthy jock from a stuffy WASP family on his way to a Harvard degree and a career in law . . . Jenny Cavilleri, a sharp-tongued, working-class beauty studying music at Radcliffe . . .Opposites in nearly every way, Oliver and Jenny are kindred spirits from vastly different worlds. Falling deeply and powerfully, their attraction to one another defies everything they have ever believed\u2014as they share a passion far greater than anything they dreamed possible . . . and explore the wonder of a love that must end too soon.One of the most adored novels of our time, this is the book that defined a generation\u2014a story of uncompromising devotion, of life as it really is . . . and love that changes everything.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1388812297i/73968.jpg", "genres": ["Chick Lit", "Love Story", "Drama", "Classics", "Love", "Contemporary", "Fiction", "Adult", "Romance", "Novels"], "asin": "B006DUJM8M", "isbn": "0380017601", "isbn13": "9780380017607", "publisher": "HarperTorch", "series": ["Ekranla\u015fd\u0131r\u0131lm\u0131\u015f \u0259s\u0259rl\u0259r", "Love Story"], "author": ["Erich Segal"], "publishDate": 1009872000000, "characters": ["Oliver Barrett IV", "Jennifer Cavilleri"], "places": ["Boston, Massachusetts", "Massachusetts"], "ratingHistogram": [2292, 6530, 16895, 18596, 15335], "ratingsCount": 59648, "reviewsCount": 3412, "numPages": 224, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6440.Ivanhoe", "title": "Ivanhoe", "titleComplete": "Ivanhoe", "description": "For this novel, Scott moved far away from the setting of his own turbulent time. He went back to the late 12th century, and to England rather than the Scottish settings of all his previous novels. He connected his writing Ivanhoe with his concerns about contemporary events.Scott drew together the apparently opposing themes of historical reality and chivalric romance, social realism and high adventure, past and present.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1630481585i/6440.jpg", "genres": ["Adventure", "Romance", "Classic Literature", "Literature", "Medieval", "Historical", "Fiction", "19th Century", "Historical Fiction", "Classics"], "asin": "0140436588", "publisher": "Penguin Books /Penguin Classics", "author": ["Graham Tulloch", "Walter Scott", "Walter Brendel"], "publishDate": 970383600000, "characters": ["Prince John Lackland", "Cedric of Rotherwood", "Wilfred of Ivanhoe", "Iorlvaux", "John of England", "Brian de Bois-Guilbert", "Little John", "Maurice De Bracy", "Isaac of York", "Maid Marion", "Le Noir-Fain\u00e9ant", "Black Knight", "Bruder Gurth", "Reginald Front-de-Boeuf", "Rebecca of York", "Robert von der Normandie", "Richard I of England", "Robin of Locksley", "Ivanhoe", "Waldemar Fitzurse"], "places": ["England"], "ratingHistogram": [2606, 7330, 25678, 32555, 25486], "ratingsCount": 93655, "reviewsCount": 2995, "numPages": 496, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/2767793-the-hero-of-ages", "title": "The Hero of Ages", "titleComplete": "The Hero of Ages (Mistborn, #3)", "description": "\"Description contains spoilers for previous book in the series\"Who is the Hero of Ages?To end the Final Empire and restore freedom, Vin killed the Lord Ruler. But as a result, the Deepness\u2014the lethal form of the ubiquitous mists\u2014is back, along with increasingly heavy ashfalls and ever more powerful earthquakes. Humanity appears to be doomed.Having escaped death at the climax of The Well of Ascension only by becoming a Mistborn himself, Emperor Elend Venture hopes to find clues left behind by the Lord Ruler that will allow him to save the world. Vin is consumed with guilt at having been tricked into releasing the mystic force known as Ruin from the Well. Ruin wants to end the world, and its near omniscience and ability to warp reality make stopping it seem impossible. Vin can't even discuss it with Elend lest Ruin learn their plans!", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1628563911i/2767793.jpg", "genres": ["Magic", "Adventure", "Science Fiction Fantasy", "Fantasy", "Young Adult", "Adult", "Fiction", "Audiobook", "High Fantasy", "Epic Fantasy"], "asin": "0765316897", "isbn": "0765316897", "isbn13": "9780765316899", "publisher": "Tor Books", "series": ["The Mistborn Saga", "The Cosmere", "The Mistborn Trilogy"], "author": ["Brandon Sanderson"], "publishDate": 1223967600000, "characters": ["Vin", "Elend Venture", "Marsh", "Breeze", "Sazed", "Hammond", "Spook"], "ratingHistogram": [1694, 4880, 28379, 108697, 250524], "ratingsCount": 394174, "reviewsCount": 27116, "numPages": 572, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "David Gemmell Legend Award", "awardedAt": 1230796800000, "category": "", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Whitney Award", "awardedAt": 1199174400000, "category": "Speculative Fiction", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Grand 