{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/14290364-champion", "title": "Champion", "titleComplete": "Champion (Legend, #3)", "description": "He is a Legend.She is a Prodigy.Who will be Champion?  June and Day have sacrificed so much for the people of the Republic\u2014and each other\u2014and now their country is on the brink of a new existence. June is back in the good graces of the Republic, working within the government\u2019s elite circles as Princeps-Elect, while Day has been assigned a high-level military position. But neither could have predicted the circumstances that will reunite them: just when a peace treaty is imminent, a plague outbreak causes panic in the Colonies, and war threatens the Republic\u2019s border cities. This new strain of plague is deadlier than ever, and June is the only one who knows the key to her country\u2019s defense. But saving the lives of thousands will mean asking the one she loves to give up everything. With heart-pounding action and suspense, Marie Lu\u2019s bestselling trilogy draws to a stunning conclusion.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1382652310i/14290364.jpg", "genres": ["Adventure", "Science Fiction", "Teen", "Fantasy", "Young Adult", "Dystopia", "Fiction", "Audiobook", "Action", "Romance"], "asin": "0399256776", "isbn": "0399256776", "isbn13": "9780399256776", "publisher": "Putnam Juvenile", "series": ["Legend"], "author": ["Marie Lu"], "publishDate": 1383638400000, "characters": ["Daniel Altan Wing", "June Iparis"], "ratingHistogram": [1974, 5461, 26252, 66831, 111518], "ratingsCount": 212036, "reviewsCount": 18974, "numPages": 369, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/33507.Twenty_Thousand_Leagues_Under_the_Sea", "title": "Twenty Thousand Leagues Under the Sea", "titleComplete": "Twenty Thousand Leagues Under the Sea (Captain Nemo, #2)", "description": "When an unidentified \u201cmonster\u201d threatens international shipping, French oceanographer Pierre Aronnax and his unflappable assistant Conseil join an expedition organized by the US Navy to hunt down and destroy the menace. After months of fruitless searching, they finally grapple with their quarry, but Aronnax, Conseil, and the brash Canadian harpooner Ned Land are thrown overboard in the attack, only to find that the \u201cmonster\u201d is actually a futuristic submarine, the Nautilus, commanded by a shadowy, mystical, preternaturally imposing man who calls himself Captain Nemo. Thus begins a journey of 20,000 leagues\u2014nearly 50,000 miles\u2014that will take Captain Nemo, his crew, and these three adventurers on a journey of discovery through undersea forests, coral graveyards, miles-deep trenches, and even the sunken ruins of Atlantis. Jules Verne\u2019s novel of undersea exploration has been captivating readers ever since its first publication in 1870, and Frederick Paul Walter\u2019s reader-friendly, scientifically meticulous translation of this visionary science fiction classic is complete and unabridged down to the smallest substantive detail.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1494979127i/33507.jpg", "genres": ["Adventure", "Science Fiction", "Novels", "Literature", "Fantasy", "Fiction", "Steampunk", "Audiobook", "Classics", "France"], "asin": "076072850X", "isbn": "076072850X", "isbn13": "9780760728505", "publisher": "Barnes & Noble", "series": ["Capitaine Nemo"], "author": ["Jules Verne", "Anthony Bonner"], "publishDate": 1017648000000, "characters": ["Captain Nemo", "Pierre Aronnax", "Ned Land"], "places": ["Atlantis", "Pacific Ocean", "Bahamas", "Red