{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/33385229-they-both-die-at-the-end", "title": "They Both Die at the End", "titleComplete": "They Both Die at the End", "description": "On September 5, a little after midnight, Death-Cast calls Mateo Torrez and Rufus Emeterio to give them some bad news: They\u2019re going to die today.Mateo and Rufus are total strangers, but, for different reasons, they\u2019re both looking to make a new friend on their End Day. The good news: There\u2019s an app for that. It\u2019s called the Last Friend, and through it, Rufus and Mateo are about to meet up for one last great adventure\u2014to live a lifetime in a single day.Adam Silvera reminds us that there\u2019s no life without death and no love without loss in this devastating yet uplifting story about two people whose lives change over the course of one unforgettable day.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1494333138i/33385229.jpg", "genres": ["Science Fiction", "Fantasy", "Gay", "Contemporary", "Young Adult", "LGBT", "Fiction", "Audiobook", "Romance", "Queer"], "asin": "0062457799", "isbn": "0062457799", "isbn13": "9780062457790", "publisher": "Quill Tree Books", "series": ["Death-Cast"], "author": ["Adam Silvera"], "publishDate": 1504594800000, "places": ["New York City, New York"], "ratingHistogram": [22915, 62764, 166326, 221190, 211144], "ratingsCount": 684339, "reviewsCount": 81732, "numPages": 389, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Flicker Tale Children's Book Award", "awardedAt": 1609488000000, "category": "Older Readers", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Lincoln Award", "awardedAt": 1577865600000, "category": "", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Goodreads Choice Award", "awardedAt": 1483257600000, "category": "Young Adult Fiction", "hasWon": null}]}
