{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/11337.The_Bluest_Eye", "title": "The Bluest Eye", "titleComplete": "The Bluest Eye", "description": "The Bluest Eye is Toni Morrison's first novel, a book heralded for its richness of language and boldness of vision. Set in the author's girlhood hometown of Lorain, Ohio, it tells the story of black, eleven-year-old Pecola Breedlove. Pecola prays for her eyes to turn blue so that she will be as beautiful and beloved as all the blond, blue-eyed children in America. In the autumn of 1941, the year the marigolds in the Breedloves' garden do not bloom. Pecola's life does change\u2014in painful, devastating ways. What its vivid evocation of the fear and loneliness at the heart of a child's yearning, and the tragedy of its fulfillment. The Bluest Eye remains one of Toni Morrisons's most powerful, unforgettable novels- and a significant work of American fiction.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1388208495i/11337.jpg", "genres": ["Literary Fiction", "Race", "Banned Books", "Literature", "School", "Fiction", "African American", "Historical Fiction", "Classics", "Novels"], "asin": "0452287065", "isbn": "0452287065", "isbn13": "9780452287068", "publisher": "Plume", "author": ["Toni Morrison"], "publishDate": 1125990000000, "characters": ["Cholly Breedlove", "Pauline Breedlove", "Pecola Breedlove"], "places": ["Ohio", "Lorain, Ohio", "Kentucky"], "ratingHistogram": [3702, 9386, 40262, 89667, 96264], "ratingsCount": 239281, "reviewsCount": 15628, "numPages": 216, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/24800.House_of_Leaves", "title": "House of Leaves", "titleComplete": "House of Leaves", "description": "A young family moves into a small home on Ash Tree Lane where they discover something is terribly wrong: their house is bigger on the inside than it is on the outside.Of course, neither Pulitzer Prize-winning photojournalist Will Navidson nor his companion Karen Green was prepared to face the consequences of that impossibility, until the day their two little children wandered off and their voices eerily began to return another story\u2014of creature darkness, of an ever-growing abyss behind a closet door, and of that unholy growl which soon enough would tear through their walls and consume all their dreams.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1403889034i/24800.jpg", "genres": ["Literature", "Fantasy", "Paranormal", "Contemporary", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Adult", "Horror", "Thriller", "Novels"], "asin": "038560310X", "isbn": "038560310X", "isbn13": "9780385603102", "publisher": "Random House", "author": ["Mark Z. Danielewski"], "publishDate": 952416000000, "characters": ["Johnny Truant", "Zampan\u00f2", "Karen Green", "Will Navidson"], "ratingHistogram": [6224, 9956, 23909, 45402, 76535], "ratingsCount": 162026, "reviewsCount": 16076, "numPages": 710, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Bram Stoker Award", "awardedAt": 946713600000, "category": "Best First Novel", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Locus Award", "awardedAt": 978336000000, "category": "Best First Novel", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "New York Public Library Young Lions Fiction Award", "awardedAt": 978336000000, "category": null, "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Guardian First Book Award", "awardedAt": 946713600000, "category": null, "hasWon": null}, {"name": "James Tait Black Memorial Prize", "awardedAt": 946713600000, "category": "Fiction", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "International Horror Guild Award"