{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/1554.Oedipus_Rex", "title": "Oedipus Rex", "titleComplete": "Oedipus Rex  (The Theban Plays, #1)", "description": "\"...what man wins more happiness than just its shape and the ruin when that shape collapses?\"Sophocles' Oedipus Rex has never been surpassed for the raw and terrible power with which its hero struggles to answer the eternal question, \"Who am I?\" The play, a story of a king who acting entirely in ignorance kills his father and marries his mother, unfolds with shattering power; we are helplessly carried along with Oedipus towards the final, horrific truth. To make Oedipus more accessible for the modern reader, our Prestwick House Literary Touchstone Classics includes a glossary of the more difficult words, as well as convenient sidebar notes to enlighten the reader on aspects that may be confusing or overlooked. We hope that the reader may, through this edition, more fully enjoy the beauty of the verse, the wisdom of the insights, and the impact of the drama.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1388182316i/1554.jpg", "genres": ["Mythology", "Tragedy", "Literature", "High School", "Read For School", "School", "Theatre", "Fiction", "Classics", "Plays"], "asin": "1580495931", "isbn": "1580495931", "isbn13": "9781580495936", "publisher": "Prestwick House Inc", "series": ["The Theban Plays"], "author": ["Elizabeth Osborne", "Sophocles", "J.E. Thomas"], "publishDate": 1088406000000, "characters": ["Oedipus", "Jocasta (Greek Mythology)", "Creon", "Sphinx (Greek mythology)", "Tiresias"], "places": ["Greece", "Thebes"], "ratingHistogram": [4799, 17958, 62066, 71918, 52915], "ratingsCount": 209656, "reviewsCount": 5680, "numPages": 75, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/8492825-where-she-went", "title": "Where She Went", "titleComplete": "Where She Went (If I Stay, #2)", "description": "It's been three years since the devastating accident... three years since Mia walked out of Adam's life forever.Now living on opposite coasts, Mia is Juilliard's rising star and Adam is LA tabloid fodder, thanks to his new rock star status and celebrity girlfriend. When Adam gets stuck in New York by himself, chance brings the couple together again, for one last night. As they explore the city that has become Mia's home, Adam and Mia revisit the past and open their hearts to the future - and each other.Told from Adam's point of view in the spare, lyrical prose that defined If I Stay, Where She Went explores the devastation of grief, the promise of new hope, and the flame of rekindled romance.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1347810457i/8492825.jpg", "genres": ["New Adult", "Teen", "Young Adult Contemporary", "Young Adult", "Contemporary", "Fiction", "Audiobook", "Realistic Fiction", "Romance", "Music"], "asin": "0525422943", "isbn": "0525422943", "isbn13": "9780525422945", "publisher": "Dutton Juvenile", "series": ["If I Stay"], "author": ["Gayle Forman"], "publishDate": 1301986800000, "characters": ["Mia Hall", "Teddy Hall", "Adam Wilde", "Kim Schein"], "places": ["Oregon", "New York City, New York"], "ratingHistogram": [4674, 16692, 62624, 101879, 105057], "ratingsCount": 290926, "reviewsCount": 21181, "numPages": 264, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Milwaukee County Teen Book Award", "awardedAt": 1325404800000, "category": "", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "The Inky Awards", "awardedAt": 1293868800000, "category": "Silver Inky", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Goodreads Choice Award", "awardedAt": 1293868800000, "category": "Young Adult Fiction", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "The Inky Awards Shortlist", "awardedAt": 1293868800000, "ca