{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/17841.Foucault_s_Pendulum", "title": "Foucault's Pendulum", "titleComplete": "Foucault's Pendulum", "description": "Three clever editors (who have spent altogether too much time reviewing crackpot manuscripts on the occult by fanatics and dilettantes) decide to have a little fun. They are inspired by an extraordinary fable they heard years before from a suspiciously natty colonel, who claimed to know of a mystic source of power greater than atomic energy.On a lark, the editors begin randomly feeding esoteric bits of knowledge into an incredible computer capable of inventing connections between all their entries. What they believe they are creating is a long, lazy game - until the game starts taking over...Here is an incredible journey of thought and history, memory and fantasy, a tour de force as enthralling as anything Umberto Eco\u2014or indeed anyone\u2014has ever devised.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1396645125i/17841.jpg", "genres": ["Philosophy", "Literature", "Italian Literature", "Mystery", "Fiction", "Italy", "Historical Fiction", "Classics", "Thriller", "Novels"], "asin": "015603297X", "isbn": "015603297X", "isbn13": "9780156032971", "publisher": "Mariner Books", "author": ["Umberto Eco", "William Weaver"], "publishDate": 1173081600000, "characters": ["Mary Lena", "Sergei Witte", "Signor Casaubon", "Abb\u00e9 Barruel", "Philippe Nizier Anselme Vachot", "Leo Fox", "Hugues de Champagne", "Theo Fox", "Artois", "Gabriel Naud\u00e9", "Diotallevi", "Justine Glinka", "P\u00e9ladan", "Dr. Diotallevi", "Monsieur Rodin", "Dufy", "Aglie", "Belbo", "Jacopo Belbo", "de Maistre", "Elie de Cyon", "Casaubon"], "places": ["Italy", "Milan, Lombardy"], "ratingHistogram": [2245, 4977, 14073, 23052, 24302], "ratingsCount": 68649, "reviewsCount": 3964, "numPages": 623, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "PEN Translation Prize", "awardedAt": 631180800000, 