{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/17212231-inferno", "title": "Inferno", "titleComplete": "Inferno (Robert Langdon, #4)", "description": "Harvard professor of symbology Robert Langdon awakens in an Italian hospital, disoriented and with no recollection of the past thirty-six hours, including the origin of the macabre object hidden in his belongings. With a relentless female assassin trailing them through Florence, he and his resourceful doctor, Sienna Brooks, are forced to flee. Embarking on a harrowing journey, they must unravel a series of codes, which are the work of a brilliant scientist whose obsession with the end of the world is matched only by his passion for one of the most influential masterpieces ever written, Dante Alighieri's The Inferno.  Dan Brown has raised the bar yet again, combining classical Italian art, history, and literature with cutting-edge science in this sumptuously entertaining thriller.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1534070896i/17212231.jpg", "genres": ["Adventure", "Crime", "Suspense", "Mystery Thriller", "Mystery", "Fiction", "Adult", "Historical Fiction", "Thriller", "Novels"], "asin": "0385537859", "isbn": "0385538170", "isbn13": "9780385538176", "publisher": "Doubleday", "series": ["Robert Langdon"], "author": ["Dan Brown"], "publishDate": 1368514800000, "characters": ["Christoph Br\u00fcder", "Bertrand Zobrist", "Sienna Brooks", "Laurence Knowlton", "Elizabeth Sinskey", "Robert Langdon", "Jonathan Ferris"], "places": ["Istanbul", "Venice", "Florence, Tuscany"], "ratingHistogram": [10189, 34804, 128821, 201849, 164567], "ratingsCount": 540230, "reviewsCount": 39048, "numPages": 463, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Goodreads Choice Award", "awardedAt": 1357027200000, "category": "Mystery & Thriller", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/227571.Peace_Like_a_River", "title": "Peace Like a River", "titleComplete": "Peace Like a River", "description": "Once in a great while, we encounter a novel in our voluminous reading that begs to be read aloud. Leif Enger's debut, Peace Like a River, is one such work. His richly evocative novel, narrated by an asthmatic 11-year-old named Reuben Land, is the story of Reuben's unusual family and their journey across the frozen Badlands of the Dakotas in search of his fugitive older brother. Charged with the murder of two locals who terrorized their family, Davy has fled, understanding that the scales of justice will not weigh in his favor. But Reuben, his father, Jeremiah\u2014a man of faith so deep he has been known to produce miracles\u2014and Reuben's little sister, Swede, follow closely behind the fleeing Davy.Affecting and dynamic, Peace Like a River is at once a tragedy, a romance, and an unflagging exploration into the spirituality and magic possible in the everyday world, and in that of the world awaiting us on the other side of life. In Enger's superb debut effort, we witness a wondrous celebration of family, faith, and spirit, the likes of which we haven't seen in a long, long time\u2014and the birth of a classic work of literature.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1436139976i/227571.jpg", "genres": ["Coming Of Age", "Family", "Literary Fiction", "Contemporary", "Fiction", "Adult", "Book Club", "Historical Fiction", "Adult Fiction", "Novels"], "asin": "B007CV7V5W", "isbn": "0802139256", "isbn13": "9780802139252", "publisher": "Grove Pr", "author": ["Leif Enger"], "publishDate": 978336000000, "characters": ["Jeremiah Land", "Swede Land", "Rube Land", "Davy Land"], "places": ["The United States of America", "North Dakota"], "ratingHistogram": [1787, 4781, 17544, 32189, 32765], "ratingsCount": 89066, "reviewsCount": 8961, "numPages": 312, "language"