{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/30868.The_Bean_Trees", "title": "The Bean Trees", "titleComplete": "The Bean Trees (Greer Family, #1)", "description": "Clear-eyed and spirited, Taylor Greer grew up poor in rural Kentucky with the goals of avoiding pregnancy and getting away. But when she heads west with high hopes and a barely functional car, she meets the human condition head-on. By the time Taylor arrives in Tucson, Arizona, she has acquired a completely unexpected child, a three-year-old American Indian girl named Turtle, and must somehow come to terms with both motherhood and the necessity for putting down roots. Hers is a story about love and friendship, abandonment and belonging, and the discovery of surprising resources in apparently empty places.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1443483961i/30868.jpg", "genres": ["Literary Fiction", "Literature", "School", "Contemporary", "Fiction", "Adult", "Realistic Fiction", "Adult Fiction", "Classics", "Novels"], "asin": "0812474945", "isbn": "0812474945", "isbn13": "9780812474947", "publisher": "Perfection Learning", "series": ["Greer Family"], "author": ["Barbara Kingsolver"], "publishDate": 599644800000, "characters": ["Estevan", "Turtle Greer", "Mattie", "Taylor Greer", "Lou Ann Ruiz", "Esperanza"], "places": ["Tucson, Arizona", "Arizona"], "ratingHistogram": [1729, 6088, 32534, 63999, 48602], "ratingsCount": 152952, "reviewsCount": 7645, "numPages": 232, "language": "English"}
