{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/80660.We_Need_to_Talk_About_Kevin", "title": "We Need to Talk About Kevin", "titleComplete": "We Need to Talk About Kevin", "description": " The gripping international bestseller about motherhood gone awry.Eva never really wanted to be a mother - and certainly not the mother of the unlovable boy who murdered seven of his fellow high school students, a cafeteria worker, and a much-adored teacher who tried to befriend him, all two days before his sixteenth birthday. Now, two years later, it is time for her to come to terms with marriage, career, family, parenthood, and Kevin's horrific rampage in a series of startlingly direct correspondences with her estranged husband, Franklin. Uneasy with the sacrifices and social demotion of motherhood from the start, Eva fears that her alarming dislike for her own son may be responsible for driving him so nihilistically off the rails. ", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1327865017i/80660.jpg", "genres": ["Crime", "Book Club", "Drama", "Literary Fiction", "Psychology", "Contemporary", "Fiction", "Adult", "Horror", "Thriller"], "asin": "006112429X", "isbn": "006112429X", "isbn13": "9780061124297", "publisher": "Harper Perennial", "author": ["Lionel Shriver"], "publishDate": 1151910000000, "characters": ["Eva Khatchadourian", "Kevin Khatchadourian", "Celia Khatchadourian", "Franklin Plaskett"], "ratingHistogram": [6158, 9389, 27918, 67953, 79585], "ratingsCount": 191003, "reviewsCount": 16753, "numPages": 400, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Orange Prize", "awardedAt": 1104566400000, "category": "Fiction", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/93101.The_Arabian_Nights", "title": "The Arabian Nights", "titleComplete": "The Arabian Nights", "description": "This volume reproduces the 1932 Modern Library edition, for which Bennett A. Cerf chose the most famous and representative stories from Sir Richard F. Burton's multivolume translation, and includes Burton's extensive and acclaimed explanatory notes. The tales of told by Shahrazad over a thousand and one nights to delay her execution by the vengeful King Shahriyar have become among the most popular in both Eastern and Western literature, as recounted by Sir Francis Burton. From the epic adventures of \"Aladdin and the Enchanted Lamp\" to the farcical \"Young Woman and her Five Lovers\" and the social criticism of \"The Tale of the Hunchback\", the stories depict a fabulous world of all-powerful sorcerers, jinns imprisoned in bottles and enchanting princesses. But despite their imaginative extravagance, the Tales are anchored to everyday life by their realism, providing a full and intimate record of medieval Islam.'", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1657544409i/93101.jpg", "genres": ["Adventure", "Short Stories", "Mythology", "Classic Literature", "Folklore", "Literature", "Fantasy", "Fairy Tales", "Fiction", "Classics"], "asin": "0812972147", "isbn": "0812972147", "isbn13": "9780812972146", "publisher": "Modern Library", "author": ["Richard Francis Burton", "Anonymous", "A.S. Byatt"], "publishDate": 1086073200000, "ratingHistogram": [1248, 3416, 15768, 26571, 28963], "ratingsCount": 75966, "reviewsCount": 2247, "numPages": 1049, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/15638.Cyrano_de_Bergerac", "title": "Cyrano de Bergerac", "titleComplete": "Cyrano de Bergerac", "description": "This is Edmond Rostand's immortal play in which chivalry and wit, bravery and love are forever captured in the timeless spirit of romance. Set in Louis XIII's reign, it is the moving and exciting drama of one of the finest swordsmen in France, gallant soldier, brilliant wit, tragic poet-lover with the face of a clown. Rostand's extraordinary lyric powers gave birth to a universal hero--Cyrano De Bergerac--and ensured his own reputation as author of one of the best-loved plays in the literature of the stage.This translation, by the American poet Brian Hooker, is nearly as famous as the original play itself, and is generally considered to be one of the finest English verse translations ever written.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1386920459i/15638.jpg", "genres": ["Romance", "Drama", "Literature", "Theatre", "School", "Fiction", "France", "Historical Fiction", "Classics", "Plays"], "asin": "0451528921", "isbn": "0451528921", "isbn13": "9780451528926", "publisher": "Signet Classics", "author": ["Eteel Lawson", "Lowell Bair", "Edmond Rostand"], "publishDate": 1060066800000, "characters": ["Le Bret", "Cyrano de Bergerac", "Christian de Neuvillette", "Ragueneau", "Count de Guiche", "Roxane"], "places": ["Arras", "Paris", "France"], "ratingHistogram": [1315, 3859, 16560, 27941, 33352], "ratingsCount": 83027, "reviewsCount": 2887, "numPages": 240, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/40909452-drums-of-autumn", "title": "Drums of Autumn", "titleComplete": "Drums of Autumn (Outlander, #4)", "description": "In this breathtaking novel, rich in history and adventure, #1 New York Times bestselling author Diana Gabaldon continues the story of Claire Randall and Jamie Fraser that started with the now-classic novel Outlander and continued in Dragonfly in Amber and Voyager. Once again spanning continents and centuries, Gabaldon has created a work of sheer brilliance. What if you knew someone you loved was going to die? What if you thought you could save them? How much would you risk to try?Claire Randall has gone to find Jamie Fraser, the man she loved more than life, and has left half her heart behind with their daughter, Brianna. Claire gave up Jamie to save Brianna, and now Bree has sent her mother back to the Scottish warrior who was willing to give his life to save them both. But a chilling discovery in the pages of history suggests that Jamie and Claire's story doesn't have a happy ending.Brianna dares a terrifying leap into the unknown in search of her mother and the father she has never met, risking her own future to try to change history . . . and to save their lives. But as Brianna plunges into an uncharted wilderness, a heartbreaking encounter may strand her forever in the past . . . or root her in the place she should be, where her heart and soul belong.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1536699977i/40909452.jpg", "genres": ["Adventure", "Time Travel", "Historical Romance", "Fantasy", "Historical", "Fiction", "Audiobook", "Adult", "Historical Fiction", "Romance"], "asin": "0525618732", "isbn": "0525618732", "isbn13": "9780525618737", "publisher": "Bantam", "series": ["Le Chardon et le Tartan", "Outlander"], "author": ["Diana Gabaldon"], "publishDate": 1539673200000, "characters": ["Brianna Randall", "Ian Murray", "Stephen Bonnet", "D