{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/366522.P_S_I_Love_You", "title": "P.S. I Love You", "titleComplete": "P.S. I Love You (P.S. I Love You, #1)", "description": "A novel about holding on, letting go, and learning to love again.Now in paperback, the endearing novel that captured readers' hearts and introduced a fresh new voice in women's fiction Cecelia Ahern. Holly couldn't live without her husband Gerry, until the day she had to. They were the kind of young couple who could finish each other's sentences. When Gerry succumbs to a terminal illness and dies, 30-year-old Holly is set adrift, unable to pick up the pieces. But with the help of a series of letters her husband left her before he died and a little nudging from an eccentric assortment of family and friends, she learns to laugh, overcome her fears, and discover a world she never knew existed. The kind of enchanting novel with cross-generational appeal that comes along once in a great while, PS, I Love You is a captivating love letter to the world!", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1392344536i/366522.jpg", "genres": ["Chick Lit", "Drama", "Contemporary Romance", "Ireland", "Love", "Contemporary", "Fiction", "Adult", "Adult Fiction", "Romance"], "asin": "0786890754", "isbn": "0786890754", "isbn13": "9780786890750", "publisher": "Hachette Books", "series": ["P.S. I Love You"], "author": ["Cecelia Ahern"], "publishDate": 1104307200000, "characters": ["Tom O'Connor", "Richard Kennedy", "Denise Hennessey", "Frank Kennedy", "John McCarthy", "Sharon McCarthy", "Holly Kennedy", "Jack Kennedy", "Daniel Connolly", "Declan Kennedy", "Ciara Kennedy", "Gerry Clark", "Elizabeth Kennedy"], "places": ["Ireland", "Dublin"], "ratingHistogram": [9392, 20796, 72956, 118963, 153503], "ratingsCount": 375610, "reviewsCount": 9662, "numPages": 501, "language": "English"}
