{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/56728.You_Are_Special", "title": "You Are Special", "titleComplete": "You Are Special (Wemmicksville, #1)", "description": "Max was interested in helping children understand their value - not from the world's perspective, but from God's. Wemmicksville is a land created by Eli, the \"God\" figure of the story. He creates each Wemmick in Wemmicksville uniquely, each with its own look and personality. Each story and video is a new adventure with the citizens of Wemmicksville. Punchinello is the central character, along with his friends Lucia, Splint, and Chip. When Punchinello strays from Eli, he begins to have problems. Only when Punchinello stays close to Eli does he clearly see how to walk through his life in Wemmicksville. In this heartwarming tale, Eli helps Punchinello understand how special he is-no matter what other Wemmicks may think. Children will learn a vital lesson-regardless of how the world sees them, God loves each of them just as they are.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1348346102i/56728.jpg", "genres": ["Childrens", "Christianity", "Inspirational", "Picture Books", "Faith", "Religion", "Christian", "Fantasy", "Fiction", "Christian Fiction"], "asin": "1859855423", "isbn": "1859855423", "isbn13": "9781859855423", "publisher": "Candle Books", "series": ["Wemmicksville"], "author": ["Max Lucado"], "publishDate": 1095404400000, "ratingHistogram": [849, 1350, 5047, 11379, 33644], "ratingsCount": 52269, "reviewsCount": 1446, "numPages": 32, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/2299110.Acheron", "title": "Acheron", "titleComplete": "Acheron (Dark-Hunter, #14)", "description": "Eleven thousand years ago a god was born. Cursed into the body of a human, Acheron endured a lifetime of hatred. His human death unleashed an unspeakable horror that almost destroyed the earth. Brought back against his will, he became the sole defender of mankind.Only it was never that simple\u2026For centuries, he has fought for our survival and hidden a past he never wants revealed.Now his survival, and ours, hinges on the very woman who threatens him. Old enemies reawaken and unite to kill them both.War has never been deadlier\u2026 or more fun.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1437687512i/2299110.jpg", "genres": ["Mythology", "Demons", "Fantasy", "Urban Fantasy", "Vampires", "Paranormal Romance", "Adult", "Fiction", "Paranormal", "Romance"], "asin": "0312362153", "isbn": "0312362153", "isbn13": "9780312362157", "publisher": "St. Martin's Press", "series": ["Dark-Hunter", "Hunter Legends"], "author": ["Sherrilyn Kenyon"], "publishDate": 1217919600000, "characters": ["Soteria \"Tory\" Eleni Athena Kafieri", "Ryssa of Didymos", "Apollo (Styxx)", "Acheron \"Ash\" Parthenopaeus", "Artemis Agrotera", "Strykerius", "Styxx of Didymos", "Apollymi", "Jaden (Dark-Hunters/Dream-Hunters)"], "places": ["Atlantis", "New Orleans, Louisiana", "Greece", "Nashville, Tennessee"], "ratingHistogram": [697, 1197, 4173, 11107, 41941], "ratingsCount": 59115, "reviewsCount": 3863, "numPages": 723, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/140077.Dead_to_the_World", "title": "Dead to the World", "titleComplete": "Dead to the World (Sookie Stackhouse, #4)", "description": "Sookie Stackhouse is a cocktail waitress in Bon Temps, Louisiana. She has only a few close friends, because not everyone appreciates Sookie\u2019s gift: she can read minds. That\u2019s not exactly every man\u2019s idea of date bait \u2013 unless they\u2019re undead; vampires and the like can be tough to read. And that\u2019s just the kind of guy Sookie\u2019s been looking for. Maybe that\u2019s why, when she comes across a naked vampire, she doesn\u2019t just drive on by. He hasn\u2019t got a clue who he is, but Sookie has: Eric looks just as scary and sexy \u2013 and dead \u2013 as ever. But now he has amnesia, he\u2019s sweet, vulnerable, and in need of Sookie\u2019s help \u2013 because whoever took his memory now wants his life.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1468561630i/140077.jpg", "genres": ["Supernatural", "Fantasy", "Urban Fantasy", "Vampires", "Paranormal Romance", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Adult", "Paranormal", "Romance"], "asin": "0441012183", "isbn": "0441012183", "isbn13": "9780441012183", "publisher": "Ace Books", "series": ["Sookie Stackhouse"], "author": ["Charlaine Harris"], "publishDate": 1115103600000, "characters": ["Eric Northman", "Pam Ravenscroft", "Alcide Herveaux", "Tara Thornton", "Jason Stackhouse", "Sookie Stackhouse", "Bill Compton", "Sam Merlotte"], "places": ["Bon Temps, Louisiana"], "ratingHistogram": [2878, 7856, 47762, 94570, 103552], "ratingsCount": 256618, "reviewsCount": 6151, "numPages": 291, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/16981.Invisible_Man", "title": "Invisible Man", "titleComplete": "Invisible Man", "description": "First published in 1952 and immediately hailed as a masterpiece, Invisible Man is one of those rare novels that have changed the shape of American literature. For not only does Ralph Ellison's nightmare journey across the racial divide tell unparalleled truths about the nature of bigotry and its effects on the minds of both victims and perpetrators, it gives us an entirely new model of what a novel can be.As he journeys from the Deep South to the streets and basements of Harlem, from a horrifying \"battle royal\" where black men are reduced to fighting animals, to a Communist rally where they are elevated to the status of trophies, Ralph Ellison's nameless protagonist ushers readers into a parallel universe that throws our own into harsh and even hilarious relief. Suspenseful and sardonic, narrated in a voice that takes in the symphonic range of the American language, black and white, Invisible Man is one of the most audacious and dazzling novels of our century.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1556482805i/16981.jpg", "genres": ["Literary Fiction", "Race", "Literature", "School", "Fiction", "American", "African American", "Historical Fiction", "Classics", "Novels"], "publisher": "Vintage", "author": ["Ralph Ellison"], "publishDate": 791625600000, "characters": ["Brother Jack", "Lucius Brockway", "Tod Clifton", "Mr. Norton", "Ras the Exhorter", "Dr. Hebert Bledsoe", "Jim Trueblood", "Unnamed Narrator", "Mary Rambo", "Sybil (Invisible Man)"], "places": ["Harlem, New York City, New York", "New York City, New York", "Alabama", "The United States of America"], "ratingHistogram": [5195, 12651, 39188, 63049, 63281], "ratingsCount": 183364, "reviewsCount": 7952, "numPages": 581, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "National Book Award", "awardedAt": -536428800