{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/8130077-the-screwtape-letters", "title": "The Screwtape Letters", "titleComplete": "The Screwtape Letters", "description": "The Screwtape Letters by C.S.\u00a0 Lewis is a classic masterpiece of religious satire that entertains readers with its sly and ironic portrayal of human life and foibles from the vantage point of Screwtape, a highly placed assistant to \"Our Father Below.\" At once wildly comic, deadly serious, and strikingly original, C.S. Lewis's The Screwtape Letters is the most engaging account of temptation\u2014and triumph over it\u2014ever written.\u00a0", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1476379778i/8130077.jpg", "genres": ["Christianity", "Philosophy", "Faith", "Religion", "Christian", "Fantasy", "Fiction", "Christian Fiction", "Classics", "Theology"], "asin": "B002BD2V2Y", "publisher": "HarperCollins e-books", "author": ["C.S. Lewis"], "publishDate": 1243494000000, "characters": ["Wormwood", "The Patient", "Screwtape"], "ratingHistogram": [9016, 15472, 55109, 124294, 222415], "ratingsCount": 426306, "reviewsCount": 15457, "numPages": 222, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Nautilus Book Award", "awardedAt": 1262332800000, "category": "Audio Books & Spoken Word", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Audie Award", "awardedAt": 946713600000, "category": "Classic", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6752378-city-of-fallen-angels", "title": "City of Fallen Angels", "titleComplete": "City of Fallen Angels (The Mortal Instruments, #4)", "description": "The Mortal War is over, and sixteen-year-old Clary Fray is back home in New York, excited about all the possibilities before her. She\u2019s training to become a Shadowhunter and to use her unique power. Her mother is getting married to the love of her life. Downworlders and Shadowhunters are at peace at last. And\u2014most importantly of all\u2014she can finally call Jace her boyfriend.But nothing comes without a price.Someone is murdering Shadowhunters, provoking tensions between Downworlders and Shadowhunters that could lead to a second, bloody war. Clary\u2019s best friend, Simon, can\u2019t help her\u2014his mother just found out that he\u2019s a vampire, and now he\u2019s homeless. When Jace begins to pull away from her without explaining why, Clary is forced to delve into the heart of a mystery whose solution reveals her worst nightmare: she herself has set in motion a terrible chain of events that could lead to her losing everything she loves. Even Jace.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1369452302i/6752378.jpg", "genres": ["Angels", "Young Adult Fantasy", "Supernatural", "Fantasy", "Urban Fantasy", "Vampires", "Young Adult", "Fiction", "Paranormal", "Romance"], "asin": "1442403543", "isbn": "1442403543", "isbn13": "9781442403543", "publisher": "Margaret K. McElderry Books", "series": ["Shadowhunter Chronicles", "The Mortal Instruments"], "author": ["Cassandra Clare"], "publishDate": 1301986800000, "characters": ["Jonathan \"Jace\" Wayland", "Jordan Kyle", "Simon Lewis", "Clarissa \"Clary\" Fray", "Magnus Bane", "Maia Roberts", "Jocelyn Fray", "Camille Belcourt", "Isabelle \"Izzy\" Sophia Lightwood", "Luke Garroway", "Alexander \"Alec\" Lightwood"], "places": ["New York City, New York"], "ratingHis