{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/7069.The_World_According_to_Garp", "title": "The World According to Garp", "titleComplete": "The World According to Garp", "description": "This is the life and times of T. S. Garp, the bastard son of Jenny Fields\u2014a feminist leader ahead of her times. This is the life and death of a famous mother and her almost-famous son; theirs is a world of sexual extremes\u2014even of sexual assassinations. It is a novel rich with \"lunacy and sorrow\"; yet the dark, violent events of the story do not undermine a comedy both ribald and robust. In more than thirty languages, in more than forty countries\u2014with more than ten million copies in print\u2014this novel provides almost cheerful, even hilarious evidence of its famous last line: \"In the world according to Garp, we are all terminal cases.\"", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1447234581i/7069.jpg", "genres": ["Humor", "Drama", "Literary Fiction", "Literature", "Contemporary", "Fiction", "American", "Adult Fiction", "Classics", "Novels"], "asin": "0345915593", "isbn": "0345915593", "isbn13": "9780345915597", "publisher": "Ballantine Books", "author": ["John Irving"], "publishDate": 922953600000, "characters": ["Roberta Muldoon", "T.S. Garp", "Helen Garp", "Jenny Fields"], "places": ["Vienna", "Boston, Massachusetts", "Austria", "New England", "The United States of America"], "ratingHistogram": [3623, 9297, 37967, 84516, 89981], "ratingsCount": 225384, "reviewsCount": 6599, "numPages": 610, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "National Book Award", "awardedAt": 315561600000, "category": "Fiction (Paperback)", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "National Book Critics Circle Award", "awardedAt": 252489600000, "category": "Fiction", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "National Book Award Finalist", "awardedAt": 284025600000, "category": "Fiction", "hasWon": null}]}
