{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/51737.The_Truth_About_Forever", "title": "The Truth About Forever", "titleComplete": "The Truth About Forever", "description": "That's what Macy has to look forward to while her boyfriend, Jason, is away at Brain Camp. Days will be spent at a boring job in the library, evenings will be filled with vocabulary drills for the SATs, and spare time will be passed with her mother, the two of them sharing a silent grief at the traumatic loss of Macy's father.But sometimes, unexpected things can happen\u2014things such as the catering job at Wish, with its fun-loving, chaotic crew. Or her sister's project of renovating the neglected beach house, awakening long-buried memories. Things such as meeting Wes, a boy with a past, a taste for Truth-telling, and an amazing artistic talent, the kind of boy who could turn any girl's world upside down. As Macy ventures out of her shell, she begins to question her sheltered life.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1362767907i/51737.jpg", "genres": ["Chick Lit", "Teen", "Young Adult Contemporary", "High School", "Young Adult Romance", "Young Adult", "Contemporary", "Fiction", "Realistic Fiction", "Romance"], "asin": "0142406252", "isbn": "0142406252", "isbn13": "9780142406250", "publisher": "Penguin Group Inc.", "author": ["Sarah Dessen"], "publishDate": 1084258800000, "characters": ["Kristy Palmetto", "Jason Talbot", "Wes Baker", "Caroline Queen", "Monica Palmetto", "Deborah Queen", "Macy Queen", "Bert Baker"], "ratingHistogram": [3392, 9153, 40420, 73217, 95362], "ratingsCount": 221544, "reviewsCount": 8916, "numPages": 374, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Romantic Times Reviewers' Choice Award (RT Award)", "awardedAt": 1072944000000, "category": "Urban Fantasy", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "South Carolina Book Award", "awardedAt": 1167638400000, "category": "Young Adult Book Award", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Lincol