{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/3682.A_Great_and_Terrible_Beauty", "title": "A Great and Terrible Beauty", "titleComplete": "A Great and Terrible Beauty (Gemma Doyle, #1)", "description": "In this debut gothic novel mysterious visions, dark family secrets and a long-lost diary thrust Gemma and her classmates back into the horrors that followed her from India. (Ages 12+)It's 1895, and after the suicide of her mother, 16-year-old Gemma Doyle is shipped off from the life she knows in India to Spence, a proper boarding school in England. Lonely, guilt-ridden, and prone to visions of the future that have an uncomfortable habit of coming true, Gemma's reception there is a chilly one. To make things worse, she's been followed by a mysterious young Indian man, a man sent to watch her. But why? What is her destiny? And what will her entanglement with Spence's most powerful girls\u2014and their foray into the spiritual world\u2014lead to?", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1284558475i/3682.jpg", "genres": ["Magic", "Teen", "Young Adult Fantasy", "Fantasy", "Historical", "Young Adult", "Fiction", "Paranormal", "Historical Fiction", "Romance"], "asin": "0689875347", "isbn": "0689875347", "isbn13": "9780689875342", "publisher": "Simon and Schuster", "series": ["Gemma Doyle"], "author": ["Libba Bray"], "publishDate": 1070956800000, "characters": ["Felicity Worthington", "Ann Bradshaw", "Pippa Cross", "Gemma Doyle", "Kartik"], "places": ["London, England", "India", "England", "United Kingdom"], "ratingHistogram": [8301, 19679, 52719, 69086, 71242], "ratingsCount": 221027, "reviewsCount": 10443, "numPages": 403, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Iowa High School Book Award", "awardedAt": 1167638400000, "category": "", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Lincoln Award", "awardedAt": 1167638400000, "category": null, "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/197084.Are_You_My_Mother_", "title": "Are You My Mother?", "titleComplete": "Are You My Mother?", "description": "ARE YOU MY MOTHER? tells a very simple story for children who have just started to read. their younger brothers or sisters will also want to follow the baby bird's quest as he asks everyone and everything he meets, \"Are You My Mother?\".Back in 1957, Theodor Geisel responded to an article in Life magazine that lamented the use of boring reading primers in schools. Using the pseudonym of \"Dr. Seuss\" (Seuss was Geisel's middle name) and only two hundred twenty-three words, Geisel created a replacement for those dull primers: \"The Cat in the Hat.\" The instant success of the book prompted Geisel and his wife to found Beginner Books, and Geisel wrote many popular books in this series, including \"Hop on Pop,\" \"Fox in Socks,\" and \"Green Eggs and Ham.\" Other favorite titles in this series are \"Go, Dog, Go!\" and \"Are You My Mother?\" by P. D. Eastman, \"A Fly Went By,\" by Mike McClintock, and \"Put Me in the Zoo,\" by Robert Lopshire. These affordable hardcover books combine large print, easy vocabulary, and large, bright illustrations in stories kids will want to read again and again. Grades 1 - Grades 2.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1389098758i/197084.jpg", "genres": ["Childrens", "Kids", "Family", "Humor", "Picture Books", "Birds", "Animals", "Young Adult", "Fiction", "Classics"], "asin": "0001713221", "isbn": "0001713221", "isbn13": "9780001713222", "publisher": "Random House, Inc.", "author": ["P.D. Eastman"], "publishDate": -252432000000, "ratingHistogram": [5645, 10515, 38882, 58642, 126016], "ratingsCount": 239700, "reviewsCount": 2741, "numPages": 64, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/4799.Cannery_Row", "title": "Cannery Row", "titleComplete": "Cannery Row (Cannery Row, #1)", "description": "Cannery Row is a book without much of a plot. Rather, it is an attempt to capture the feeling and people of a place, the cannery district of Monterey, California, which is populated by a mix of those down on their luck and those who choose for other reasons not to live \"up the hill\" in the more respectable area of town. The flow of the main plot is frequently interrupted by short vignettes that introduce us to various denizens of the Row, most of whom are not directly connected with the central story. These vignettes are often characterized by direct or indirect reference to extreme violence: suicides, corpses, and the cruelty of the natural world.The \"story\" of Cannery Row follows the adventures of Mack and the boys, a group of unemployed yet resourceful men who inhabit a converted fish-meal shack on the edge of a vacant lot down on the Row.Sweet Thursday is the sequel to Cannery Row.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1388188936i/4799.jpg", "genres": ["20th Century", "Classic Literature", "Literary Fiction", "The United States Of America", "Literature", "Fiction", "American", "Historical Fiction", "Classics", "Novels"], "asin": "014200068X", "isbn": "014200068X", "isbn13": "9780142000687", "publisher": "Penguin Books", "series": ["Cannery Row"], "author": ["John Steinbeck"], "publishDate": 1012896000000, "characters": ["Eddie, Doc, Dora, Lee Chong, Mack", "Cannery Row", "Lee Chong", "Gay", "Eddie", "\"Doc\" Bradley Stanwick", "Hughie", "Dora", "Hazel", "Mack"], "places": ["California", "Monterey, California", "The United States of America"], "ratingHistogram": [1166, 4860, 26855, 53556, 47216], "ratingsCount": 133653, "reviewsCount": 7188, "numPages": 181, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/20448515-bared-to-you", "title": "Bared to You", "titleComplete": "Bared to You (Crossfire, #1)", "description": "From #1 New York Times bestselling author Sylvia Day comes the provocative masterstroke of abandon and obsession that redefined the meaning of desire and became a global phenomenon...Gideon Cross came into my life like lightning in the darkness. He was beautiful and brilliant, jagged and white-hot. I was drawn to him as I'd never been to anything or anyone in my life. I craved his touch like a drug, even knowing it would weaken me. I was flawed and damaged, and he opened those cracks in me so easily.Gideon knew. He had demons of his own. And we would become the mirrors that reflected each other's most private wounds and desires.The bonds of his love transformed me, even as I prayed that the torment of our pasts didn't tear us apart", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1433411511i/20448515.jpg", "genres": ["New Adult", "Chick Lit", "Erotic Romance", "Contemporary Romance", "BDSM", "Contemporary", "Erotica", "Adult", "Fiction", "Romance"], "publisher": "Berkley", "series": ["Crossfire"], "author": ["Sylvia Day"], "publishDate": 1391500800000, "characters": ["Gideon Cross", "Eva Tramell"], "places": ["New York City, New York"], "ratingHistogram": [14963, 28196, 78542, 139339, 256701], "ratingsCount": 517741, "reviewsCount": 20882, "numPages": 352, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "All About Romance (AAR) Annual Reader Poll", "awardedAt": 1357027200000, "category": "Best Erotic Romance AND Most Tortured Hero", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Goodreads Choice Award", "awardedAt": 1325404800000, "category": "Romance and for Goodreads Author", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/5797.Vanity_Fair", "title": "Vanity Fair", "titleComplete": "Vanity Fair", "description": "A novel that chronicles the lives of two women who could not be more different: Becky Sharp, an orphan whose only resources are her vast ambitions, her native wit, and her loose morals; and her schoolmate Amelia Sedley, a typically naive Victorian heroine, the pampered daughter of a wealthy family.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1344386439i/5797.jpg", "genres": ["Romance", "Classic Literature", "Literature", "British Literature", "Victorian", "19th Century", "Fiction", "Historical Fiction", "Classics", "Novels"], "asin": "0141439831", "isbn": "0141439831", "isbn13": "9780141439839", "publisher": "Penguin Books", "author": ["William Makepeace Thackeray", "John Carey"], "publishDate": 1051599600000, "characters": ["Amelia Sedley", "Rebecca Sharp", "Matilda Crawley", "George Osborne", "Jos Sedley", "Rawdon Crawley", "William Dobbin", "Sir Pitt Crawley"], "places": ["England", "United Kingdom"], "ratingHistogram": [3839, 9704, 32095, 43488, 37630], "ratingsCount": 126756, "reviewsCount": 4352, "numPages": 867, "language": "English"}
