{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/5308.The_Pearl", "title": "The Pearl", "titleComplete": "The Pearl", "description": "Like his father and grandfather before him, Kino is a poor diver, gathering pearls from the gulf beds that once brought great wealth to the kings of Spain and now provide Kino, Juana, and their infant son with meager subsistence. Then, on a day like any other, Kino emerges from the sea with a pearl as large as a sea gull\u2019s egg, as \u201cperfect as the moon.\u201d With the pearl comes hope, the promise of comfort and of security\u2026A story of classic simplicity, based on a Mexican folk tale, The Pearl explores the secrets of man\u2019s nature, greed, the darkest depths of evil, and the luminous possibilities of love.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1437234939i/5308.jpg", "genres": ["Short Stories", "Novella", "Literature", "Read For School", "School", "Fiction", "American", "Historical Fiction", "Classics", "Novels"], "asin": "0142000698", "isbn": "0142000698", "isbn13": "9780142000694", "publisher": "Penguin Books", "author": ["John Steinbeck"], "publishDate": 1010476800000, "characters": ["Apolonia", "Juana", "Juan Tomas", "Coyotito", "Kino"], "places": ["Nayarit", "Santa Rosalia", "La Paz", "The Gulf", "Loreto, Baja California Sur"], "ratingHistogram": [11438, 24635, 71358, 76895, 45493], "ratingsCount": 229819, "reviewsCount": 11904, "numPages": 96, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/17788401-ugly-love", "title": "Ugly Love", "titleComplete": "Ugly Love", "description": "When Tate Collins meets airline pilot Miles Archer, she knows it isn\u2019t love at first sight. They wouldn\u2019t even go so far as to consider themselves friends. The only thing Tate and Miles have in common is an undeniable mutual attraction. Once their desires are out in the open, they realize they have the perfect set-up. He doesn\u2019t want love, she doesn\u2019t have time for love, so that just leaves the sex. Their arrangement could be surprisingly seamless, as long as Tate can stick to the only two rules Miles has for her.Never ask about the past.Don\u2019t expect a future.They think they can handle it, but realize almost immediately they can\u2019t handle it at all.Hearts get infiltrated.Promises get broken.Rules get shattered.Love gets ugly.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1632597571i/17788401.jpg", "genres": ["New Adult", "Chick Lit", "Contemporary Romance", "Love", "Contemporary", "Young Adult", "Fiction", "Audiobook", "Adult", "Romance"], "asin": "B00HB62MC0", "publisher": "Atria Books", "author": ["Colleen Hoover"], "publishDate": 1407222000000, "characters": ["Tate Collins", "Miles Archer"], "places": ["San Francisco, California"], "ratingHistogram": [48621, 90053, 249899, 475766, 716077], "ratingsCount": 1580416, "reviewsCount": 116702, "numPages": 333, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Goodreads Choice Award", "awardedAt": 1388563200000, "category": "Romance", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/222910.The_Two_Towers", "title": "The Two Towers", "titleComplete": "The Two Towers (The Lord of the Rings, #2)", "description": "Alternate Cover Edition ISBN 0345296060 (ISBN13: 9780345296061)One Ring to rule them all, One Ring to find them, One Ring to bring them all and in the darkness bind themFrodo and his Companions of the Ring have been beset by danger during their quest to prevent the Ruling Ring from falling into the hands of the Dark Lord by destroying it in the Cracks of Doom. They have lost the wizard, Gandalf, in a battle in the Mines of Moria. And Boromir, seduced by the power of the Ring, tried to seize it by force. While Frodo and Sam made their escape, the rest of the company was attacked by Orcs. Now they continue the journey alone down the great River Anduin\u2014alone, that is, save for the mysterious creeping figure that follows wherever they go.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1486871714i/222910.jpg", "genres": ["Adventure", "Science Fiction Fantasy", "Novels", "Literature", "Fantasy", "Classics", "Fiction", "Audiobook", "High Fantasy", "Epic Fantasy"], "publisher": "Ballantine Books", "series": ["The Lord of the Rings"], "author": ["J.R.R. Tolkien"], "publishDate": 116665200000, "characters": ["\u00c9owyn", "Elrond Half-elven", "Arwen Und\u00f3miel", "Eriol", "R\u00famil", "\u00c9omer", "Frodo Baggins", "Galadriel", "Boromir", "Faramir", "Bilbo Baggins", "Treebeard", "Saruman", "Sam Gamgee", "Aragorn", "Gollum", "Peregrin Took", "Gimli", "Legolas", "Gandalf", "Meriadoc Brandybuck"], "places": ["Middle-earth"], "ratingHistogram": [5339, 15120, 82394, 252215, 570404], "ratingsCount": 925472, "reviewsCount": 17919, "numPages": 447, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/137791.Divine_Secrets_of_the_Ya_Ya_Sisterhood", "title": "Divine Secrets of the Ya-Ya Sisterhood", "titleComplete": "Divine Secrets of the Ya-Ya Sisterhood", "description": "When Siddalee Walker, oldest daughter of Vivi Abbott Walker, Ya-Ya extraordinaire, is interviewed in the New York Times about a hit play she's directed, her mother gets described as a \"tap-dancing child abuser.\" Enraged, Vivi disowns Sidda. Devastated, Sidda begs forgiveness, and postpones her upcoming wedding. All looks bleak until the Ya-Yas step in and convince Vivi to send Sidda a scrapbook of their girlhood mementos, called \"Divine Secrets of the Ya-Ya Sisterhood.\" As Sidda struggles to analyze her mother, she comes face to face with the tangled beauty of imperfect love, and the fact that forgiveness, more than understanding, is often what the heart longs for.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1408313524i/137791.jpg", "genres": ["Humor", "Chick Lit", "Southern", "Contemporary", "Fiction", "Adult", "Book Club", "Historical Fiction", "Adult Fiction", "Novels"], "asin": "006075995X", "isbn": "006075995X", "isbn13": "9780060759957", "publisher": "Harper Perennial", "series": ["Ya Yas"], "author": ["Rebecca Wells"], "publishDate": 1102406400000, "places": ["The United States of America"], "ratingHistogram": [16805, 37831, 134227, 186210, 177423], "ratingsCount": 552496, "reviewsCount": 4739, "numPages": 383, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Orange Prize", "awardedAt": 946713600000, "category": "Fiction Shortlist", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "American Booksellers Book Of The Year  Award", "awardedAt": 915177600000, "category": "Adult Trade", "hasWon": null}]}
