{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/3087.A_Room_with_a_View", "title": "A Room with a View", "titleComplete": "A Room with a View", "description": "\"But you do,\" he went on, not waiting for contradiction. \"You love the boy body and soul, plainly, directly, as he loves you, and no other word expresses it ...\"Lucy has her rigid, middle-class life mapped out for her, until she visits Florence with her uptight cousin Charlotte, and finds her neatly ordered existence thrown off balance. Her eyes are opened by the unconventional characters she meets at the Pension Bertolini: flamboyant romantic novelist Eleanor Lavish, the Cockney Signora, curious Mr Emerson and, most of all, his passionate son George.Lucy finds herself torn between the intensity of life in Italy and the repressed morals of Edwardian England, personified in her terminally dull fianc\u00e9 Cecil Vyse. Will she ever learn to follow her own heart?", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1388781285i/3087.jpg", "genres": ["20th Century", "Literature", "British Literature", "Classics", "Fiction", "Italy", "Audiobook", "Historical Fiction", "Romance", "Novels"], "asin": "1420925431", "isbn": "1420925431", "isbn13": "9781420925432", "publisher": "Digireads.Com", "author": ["E.M. Forster"], "publishDate": 1104566400000, "characters": ["Lucy Honeychurch", "Mr. Emerson", "Freddy Honeychurch", "Rev. Cuthbert Eager", "Eleanor Lavish", "Rev. Arthur Beebe", "Miss Alan", "Cecil Vyse", "George Emerson", "Charlotte Bartlett"], "places": ["Surrey, England", "Florence, Tuscany", "Tuscany", "Italy", "England"], "ratingHistogram": [3229, 10686, 42869, 66463, 56245], "ratingsCount": 179492, "reviewsCount": 8275, "numPages": 119, "language": "English"}
