{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/77142.Snow_Falling_on_Cedars", "title": "Snow Falling on Cedars", "titleComplete": "Snow Falling on Cedars", "description": "Gripping, tragic, and densely atmospheric\u2014a masterpiece of suspense San Piedro Island, north of Puget Sound, is a place so isolated that no one who lives there can afford to make enemies. But in 1954 a local fisherman is found suspiciously drowned, and a Japanese American named Kabuo Miyamoto is charged with his murder. In the course of the ensuing trial, it becomes clear that what is at stake is more than a man's guilt. For on San Pedro, memories of a charmed love affair between a white boy and the Japanese girl who grew up to become Kabuo's wife; memories of land desired, paid for, and lost. Above all, San Piedro is haunted by the memory of what happened to its Japanese residents during World War II, when an entire community was sent into exile while its neighbors watched.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1479863528i/77142.jpg", "genres": ["Literary Fiction", "Literature", "Historical", "Classics", "Mystery", "Fiction", "Historical Fiction", "Adult Fiction", "Romance", "Novels"], "asin": "067976402X", "isbn": "067976402X", "isbn13": "9780679764021", "publisher": "Vintage", "author": ["David Guterson"], "publishDate": 812098800000, "characters": ["Ishmael Chambers", "Carl Heine", "Hatsue Miyamoto", "Kabuo Miyamoto"], "places": ["San Piedro Island, Washington", "Pacific Northwest", "Washington (state)"], "ratingHistogram": [3337, 11247, 45194, 73484, 51218], "ratingsCount": 184480, "reviewsCount": 5708, "numPages": 460, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Anthony Award", "awardedAt": 788947200000, "category": "Best First Novel", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "PEN/Faulkner Award for Fiction", "awardedAt": 788947200000, "category": null, "hasWon": null}, {"name": "American Booksellers Book Of The Year  Award", "awardedAt": 82