{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/3950967-the-tales-of-beedle-the-bard", "title": "The Tales of Beedle the Bard", "titleComplete": "The Tales of Beedle the Bard (Hogwarts Library, #3)", "description": "\"The Tales of Beedle the Bard\" contains five richly diverse fairy tales, each with its own magical character, that will variously bring delight, laughter and the thrill of mortal peril.Additional notes for each story penned by Professor Albus Dumbledore will be enjoyed by Muggles and wizards alike, as the Professor muses on the morals illuminated by the tales, and reveals snippets of information about life at Hogwarts.A uniquely magical volume, with illustrations by the author, J. K. Rowling, that will be treasured for years to come.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1630876355i/3950967.jpg", "genres": ["Childrens", "Magic", "Short Stories", "Science Fiction Fantasy", "Fantasy", "Young Adult", "Fairy Tales", "Fiction", "Middle Grade", "Audiobook"], "asin": "0747599874", "isbn": "0747599874", "isbn13": "9780747599876", "publisher": "Bloomsbury", "series": ["Hogwarts Library"], "author": ["J.K. Rowling", "Hermione Granger"], "publishDate": 1199174400000, "places": ["United Kingdom"], "ratingHistogram": [5522, 22061, 104558, 160230, 185424], "ratingsCount": 477795, "reviewsCount": 18043, "numPages": 105, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Locus Award", "awardedAt": 1546329600000, "category": "Art Book", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/11324204-houdini-heart", "title": "Houdini Heart", "titleComplete": "Houdini Heart", "description": "HOUDINI HEART harkens back to the masters of suspenseful supernatural Poe, Lovecraft, Shirley Jackson, but speaks with a wholly fresh voice. Once caught in its pages, there's no escaping Longfellow's terrible tale. Weeks ago, she was one of Hollywood's biggest writers, wed to one of its greatest stars. The doting mother of their golden child. But now? She's alone, tortured by a horrifying secret no woman could bear. Pursued by those she can't outrun, anguished by a guilt she can't endure, and driven close to madness, she flees to the one place she's ever called a small town in Vermont where River House still stands. To a child, the splendid hotel was mysterious and magical and all its glamorous guests knew delicious secrets.Cocooned in its walls, she will write one last book. Her atonement? Or her suicide note? But life is never as you dream it, and River House isn't what she'd always imagined it was. Intense, literary, and harrowing, Houdini Heart is a tale of bone-chilling horror, emotional torment, and psychological terror. Gripped by River House, trapped in an aging hotel of mirrors only Houdini could escape, how much can haunt a mind before it too is only a thing once imagined? \"A haunting and disturbing journey through the psyche.\"\u2014Erika Mailman, Author of \"The Witch's Trinity\"", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1510418043i/11324204.jpg", "genres": ["Supernatural", "Literature", "Fantasy", "Gothic", "Psychological Horror", "Magical Realism", "Fiction", "Mystery", "Horror", "Thriller"], "asin": "0975925512", "isbn": "0975925512", "isbn13": "9780975925515", "publisher": "Eio Books", "author": ["Ki Longfellow"], "publishDate": 1303714800000, "ratingHistogram": [483, 483, 819, 1699, 2236], "ratingsCount": 5720, "reviewsCount": 228, "numPages": 254, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/17716.Waiting_for_Godot", "title": "Waiting for Godot", "titleComplete": "Waiting for Godot", "description": "The story revolves around two seemingly homeless men simply waiting for someone\u2014or something\u2014named Godot. Vladimir and Estragon wait near a tree, inhabiting a drama spun of their own consciousness. The result is a comical wordplay of poetry, dreamscapes, and nonsense, which has been interpreted as mankind\u2019s inexhaustible search for meaning. Beckett\u2019s language pioneered an expressionistic minimalism that captured the existential post-World War II Europe. His play remains one of the most magical and beautiful allegories of our time.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1327910301i/17716.jpg", "genres": ["Philosophy", "Drama", "Literature", "Classics", "Theatre", "School", "Fiction", "Plays", "France", "Irish Literature"], "publisher": "Grove", "author": ["Samuel Beckett"], "publishDate": 1293868800000, "characters": ["Lucky", "Pozzo", "Vladimir (Samuel Beckett)", "Estragon", "boy"], "ratingHistogram": [7765, 15854, 42158, 63824, 65892], "ratingsCount": 195493, "reviewsCount": 8261, "numPages": 109, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/7354.The_Shipping_News", "title": "The Shipping News", "titleComplete": "The Shipping News", "description": "Alternate Cover Edition ISBN 0671510053 (ISBN13: 9780671510053)At thirty-six, Quoyle, a third-rate newspaperman, is wrenched violently out of his workaday life when his two-timing wife meets her just deserts. He retreats with his two daughters to his ancestral home on the starkly beautiful Newfoundland coast, where a rich cast of local characters all play a part in Quoyle's struggle to reclaim his life. As three generations of his family cobble up new lives, Quoyle confronts his private demons--and the unpredictable forces of nature and society--and begins to see the possibility of love without pain or misery.A vigorous, darkly comic, and at times magical portrait of the contemporary American family, The Shipping News shows why E. Annie Proulx is recognized as one of the most gifted and original writers in America today.(back cover)", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1554192241i/7354.jpg", "genres": ["Literary Fiction", "Literature", "Contemporary", "Fiction", "Canada", "Adult", "American", "Adult Fiction", "Classics", "Novels"], "asin": "0743225422", "isbn": "0743225422", "isbn13": "9780743225427", "publisher": "Scribner", "author": ["Annie Proulx"], "publishDate": 1009872000000, "characters": ["Dennis Buggit", "B. Beaufield Nutbeem", "Billy Pretty", "Jack Buggit", "Wavey Prowse", "Beety Buggit", "Bunny", "Sunshine", "Quoyle", "Agnis Hamm", "Tert Card", "Petal Bear"], "places": ["Newfoundland and Labrador", "Canada"], "ratingHistogram": [3976, 9975, 31560, 53064, 45377], "ratingsCount": 143952, "reviewsCount": 5957, "numPages": 337, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Pulitzer Prize", "awardedAt": 757411200000, "category": "Fiction", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "National Book Award", "awardedAt": 725875200000, "category": "Fiction", "hasWon": 