{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/285092.High_Fidelity", "title": "High Fidelity", "titleComplete": "High Fidelity", "description": "Do you know your desert-island, all-time, top five most memorable split-ups?Rob does. He keeps a list, in fact. But Laura isn't on it - even though she's just become his latest ex. He's got his life back, you see. He can just do what he wants when he wants: like listen to whatever music he likes, look up the girls that are on his list, and generally behaves as if Laura never mattered. But Rob finds he can't move on. He's stuck in a really deep groove - and it's called Laura. Soon, Rob's asking himself some big questions: about love, about life - and about why we choose to share ours with the people we do.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1327928082i/285092.jpg", "genres": ["Humor", "Novels", "Literature", "British Literature", "Contemporary", "Fiction", "Adult Fiction", "Romance", "Music", "Comedy"], "asin": "1573225517", "isbn": "1573225517", "isbn13": "9781573225519", "publisher": "Riverhead Books", "author": ["Nick Hornby"], "publishDate": 831279600000, "characters": ["Rob Gordon"], "places": ["London, England"], "ratingHistogram": [2673, 10217, 45866, 81721, 56974], "ratingsCount": 197451, "reviewsCount": 7637, "numPages": 340, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/187181.The_Chosen", "title": "The Chosen", "titleComplete": "The Chosen (Reuven Malther, #1)", "description": "It is the now-classic story of two fathers and two sons and the pressures on all of them to pursue the religion they share in the way that is best suited to each. And as the boys grow into young men, they discover in the other a lost spiritual brother, and a link to an unexplored world that neither had ever considered before. In effect, they exchange places, and find the peace that neither will ever retreat from again. . . .", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1403191327i/187181.jpg", "genres": ["Judaism", "Literature", "Religion", "School", "Young Adult", "Jewish", "Fiction", "Historical Fiction", "Classics", "Novels"], "asin": "0449213447", "isbn": "0449213447", "isbn13": "9780449213445", "publisher": "Fawcett Books", "series": ["Reuven Malther"], "author": ["Chaim Potok"], "publishDate": 545209200000, "characters": ["Danny Saunders", "Reuven Malter"], "places": ["Williamsburg, Brooklyn, New York", "Brooklyn, New York City, New York"], "ratingHistogram": [1671, 4205, 16446, 34135, 35778], "ratingsCount": 92235, "reviewsCount": 4908, "numPages": 304, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Edward Lewis Wallant Award", "awardedAt": -94665600000, "category": "", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "National Book Award Finalist", "awardedAt": -63129600000, "category": "Fiction", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/13214.I_Know_Why_the_Caged_Bird_Sings", "title": "I Know Why the Caged Bird Sings", "titleComplete": "I Know Why the Caged Bird Sings (Maya Angelou's Autobiography, #1)", "description": "Maya Angelou\u2019s debut memoir is a modern American classic beloved worldwide. Her life story is told in the documentary film And Still I Rise, as seen on PBS\u2019s American Masters.Here is a book as joyous and painful, as mysterious and memorable, as childhood itself. I Know Why the Caged Bird Sings captures the longing of lonely children, the brute insult of bigotry, and the wonder of words that can make the world right. Maya Angelou\u2019s debut memoir is a modern American classic beloved worldwide. Sent by their mother to live with their devout, self-sufficient grandmother in a small Southern town, Maya and her brother, Bailey, endure the ache of abandonment and the prejudice of the local \u201cpowhitetrash.\u201d At eight years old and back at her mother\u2019s side in St. Louis, Maya is attacked by a man many times her age\u2014and has to live with the consequences for a lifetime. Years later, in San Francisco, Maya learns that love for herself, the kindness of others, her own strong spirit, and the ideas of great authors (\u201cI met and fell in love with William Shakespeare\u201d) will allow her to be free instead of imprisoned. Poetic and powerful, I Know Why the Caged Bird Sings will touch hearts and change minds for as long as people read.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1327957927i/13214.jpg", "genres": ["Feminism", "Nonfiction", "Biography Memoir", "Memoir", "Race", "Classics", "African American", "Autobiography", "Poetry", "Biography"], "asin": "B00P4JQBIC", "isbn": "0553279378", "isbn13": "9780553279375", "publisher": "Bantam Books", "series": ["Maya Angelou's Autobiography"], "author": ["Maya Angelou"], "publishDate": 752140800000, "characters": ["Maya