{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/14706.Faust_First_Part", "title": "Faust, First Part", "titleComplete": "Faust, First Part", "description": "Goethe\u2019s masterpiece and perhaps the greatest work in German literature, Faust has made the legendary German alchemist one of the central myths of the Western world. Here indeed is a monumental Faust, an audacious man boldly wagering with the devil, Mephistopheles, that no magic, sensuality, experience, or knowledge can lead him to a moment he would wish to last forever. Here, in Faust, Part I, the tremendous versatility of Goethe\u2019s genius creates some of the most beautiful passages in literature. Here too we experience Goethe\u2019s characteristic humor, the excitement and eroticism of the witches\u2019 Walpurgis Night, and the moving emotion of Gretchen\u2019s tragic fate.This authoritative edition, which offers Peter Salm\u2019s wonderfully readable translation as well as the original German on facing pages, brings us Faust in a vital, rhythmic American idiom that carefully preserves the grandeur, integrity, and poetic immediacy of Goethe\u2019s words.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1435405022i/14706.jpg", "genres": ["Philosophy", "Drama", "Literature", "Fantasy", "German Literature", "School", "Fiction", "Classics", "Poetry", "Plays"], "asin": "0553213482", "isbn": "0553213482", "isbn13": "9780553213485", "publisher": "Bantam Classics", "series": ["Goethes Faust"], "author": ["Peter Salm", "Johann Wolfgang von Goethe"], "publishDate": 586422000000, "characters": ["Faust", "Mephistopheles", "Gretchen"], "ratingHistogram": [2085, 5606, 16910, 24779, 24275], "ratingsCount": 73655, "reviewsCount": 1887, "numPages": 327, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Premi de Traducci\u00f3 Vidal Alcover", "awardedAt": 1104566400000, "category": " Jaume Ortol\u00e0 Font", "hasWon": null}]}
