{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/12898.Death_of_a_Salesman", "title": "Death of a Salesman", "titleComplete": "Death of a Salesman", "description": "'For a salesman, there is no rock bottom to life. He don't put a bolt to a nut, he don't tell you the law or give you medicine. He's a man way out there in the blue, riding on a smile and a shoeshine.'Willy Loman has been a salesman for 34 years. At 60, he is cast aside, his usefulness now exhausted. With no future to dream about he must face the crushing disappointments of his past. He takes one final brave action, but is he heroic at last?, or a self-deluding fool?", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1554514105i/12898.jpg", "genres": ["Drama", "Literature", "High School", "Read For School", "School", "Theatre", "Fiction", "American", "Classics", "Plays"], "asin": "0435233076", "isbn": "0435233076", "isbn13": "9780435233075", "publisher": "Heinemann", "author": ["Arthur  Miller"], "publishDate": 757411200000, "characters": ["Ben Loman", "Happy Loman", "Linda Loman", "Biff Loman", "Willy Loman", "Howard Wagner"], "places": ["New York City, New York"], "ratingHistogram": [9326, 26460, 67904, 73378, 50214], "ratingsCount": 227282, "reviewsCount": 7293, "numPages": 144, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Pulitzer Prize", "awardedAt": -662659200000, "category": "Drama", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "New York Drama Critics' Circle Award", "awardedAt": -662659200000, "category": "Best American Play", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/8490112-daughter-of-smoke-bone", "title": "Daughter of Smoke & Bone", "titleComplete": "Daughter of Smoke & Bone (Daughter of Smoke & Bone, #1)", "description": "Around the world, black hand prints are appearing on doorways, scorched there by winged strangers who have crept through a slit in the sky.In a dark and dusty shop, a devil\u2019s supply of human teeth grows dangerously low.And in the tangled lanes of Prague, a young art student is about to be caught up in a brutal otherworldly war.Meet Karou. She fills her sketchbooks with monsters that may or may not be real, she\u2019s prone to disappearing on mysterious \"errands\", she speaks many languages - not all of them human - and her bright blue hair actually grows out of her head that color. Who is she? That is the question that haunts her, and she\u2019s about to find out.When beautiful, haunted Akiva fixes fiery eyes on her in an alley in Marrakesh, the result is blood and starlight, secrets unveiled, and a star-crossed love whose roots drink deep of a violent past. But will Karou live to regret learning the truth about herself?", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1461353773i/8490112.jpg", "genres": ["Magic", "Angels", "Young Adult Fantasy", "Supernatural", "Fantasy", "Urban Fantasy", "Young Adult", "Fiction", "Paranormal", "Romance"], "asin": "0316134023", "isbn": "0316134023", "isbn13": "9780316134026", "publisher": "Little, Brown Books for Young Readers", "series": ["Daughter of Smoke & Bone"], "author": ["Laini Taylor"], "publishDate": 1317106800000, "characters": ["Mik", "Thiago", "Brimstone", "Ziri", "Akiva (Daughter of Smoke & Bone)", "Madrigal", "Zuzana", "Issa", "Karou", "Kazimir"], "places": ["Prague (Praha)", "Eretz", "Marrakesh (Marrakech)"], "ratingHistogram": [11851, 21350, 65779, 122855, 141770], "ratingsCount": 363605, "reviewsCount": 33543, "numPages": 418, "language": "English", "awa