{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/12220.A_Streetcar_Named_Desire", "title": "A Streetcar Named Desire", "titleComplete": "A Streetcar Named Desire", "description": "The Pulitzer Prize and Drama Critics Circle Award winning play\u2014reissued with an introduction by Arthur Miller (Death of a Salesman and The Crucible), and Williams\u2019 essay \u201cThe World I Live In.\u201dIt is a very short list of 20th-century American plays that continue to have the same power and impact as when they first appeared\u201457 years after its Broadway premiere, Tennessee Williams\u2019 A Streetcar Named Desire is one of those plays. The story famously recounts how the faded and promiscuous Blanche DuBois is pushed over the edge by her sexy and brutal brother-in-law, Stanley Kowalski. Streetcar launched the careers of Marlon Brando, Jessica Tandy, Kim Hunter, and Karl Malden, and solidified the position of Tennessee Williams as one of the most important young playwrights of his generation, as well as that of Elia Kazan as the greatest American stage director of the \u201940s and \u201950s.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1389153133i/12220.jpg", "genres": ["20th Century", "Drama", "Literature", "Classics", "School", "Theatre", "Fiction", "American", "Plays", "Read For School"], "asin": "0822210894", "isbn": "0822210894", "isbn13": "9780822210894", "publisher": "Dramatists Play Service, Inc.", "author": ["Tennessee Williams"], "publishDate": 883641600000, "characters": ["Harold \"Mitch\" Mitchell", "Eunice Hubbel", "Steve Hubbel", "Stella Kowalski", "Blanche DuBois", "Stanley Kowalski"], "places": ["New Orleans, Louisiana", "The United States of America", "Louisiana"], "ratingHistogram": [5088, 16074, 65185, 110562, 106411], "ratingsCount": 303320, "reviewsCount": 6546, "numPages": 107, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Pulitzer Prize", "awardedAt": -694281600000, "category": "Drama", "hasWon": nu