{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/386187.Midnight_in_the_Garden_of_Good_and_Evil", "title": "Midnight in the Garden of Good and Evil", "titleComplete": "Midnight in the Garden of Good and Evil", "description": "Shots rang out in Savannah's grandest mansion in the misty, early morning hours of May 2, 1981. Was it murder or self-defense? For nearly a decade, the shooting and its aftermath reverberated throughout this city of moss-hung oaks and shaded squares. John Berendt's narrative reads like a thoroughly engrossing novel, and yet it is a work of nonfiction. Berendt interweaves a first-person account of life in this isolated remnant of the Old South with the unpredictable twists and turns of a landmark murder case.The story is peopled by a gallery of remarkable characters: the well-bred society ladies of the Married Woman's Card Club; the turbulent young redneck gigolo; the hapless recluse who owns a bottle of poison so powerful it could kill every man, woman, and child in Savannah; the aging and profane Southern belle who is the \"soul of pampered self-absorption\"; the uproarious black drag queen; the acerbic and arrogant antiques dealer; the sweet-talking, piano-playing con artist; young blacks dancing the minuet at the black debutante ball; and Minerva, the voodoo priestess who works her magic in the graveyard at midnight. These and other Savannahians act as a Greek chorus, with Berendt revealing the alliances, hostilities, and intrigues that thrive in a town where everyone knows everyone else.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1427166915i/386187.jpg", "genres": ["Crime", "Nonfiction", "Southern", "Memoir", "Travel", "History", "Classics", "Mystery", "Audiobook", "True Crime"], "asin": "0679751521", "isbn": "0679751521", "isbn13": "9780679751526", "publisher": "Vintage", "author": ["John Berendt"], "publishDate": 930553200000, "characters": ["Joe Odom", "Luther Driggers", "Mandy Nichol