{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/130440.Doctor_Zhivago", "title": "Doctor Zhivago", "titleComplete": "Doctor Zhivago", "description": "This epic tale about the effects of the Russian Revolution and its aftermath on a bourgeois family was not published in the Soviet Union until 1987. One of the results of its publication in the West was Pasternak's complete rejection by Soviet authorities; when he was awarded the Nobel Prize for Literature in 1958 he was compelled to decline it. The book quickly became an international best-seller.Dr. Yury Zhivago, Pasternak's alter ego, is a poet, philosopher, and physician whose life is disrupted by the war and by his love for Lara, the wife of a revolutionary. His artistic nature makes him vulnerable to the brutality and harshness of the Bolsheviks. The poems he writes constitute some of the most beautiful writing featured in the novel.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1385508725i/130440.jpg", "genres": ["War", "Romance", "Russia", "Literature", "Historical", "Russian Literature", "Fiction", "Historical Fiction", "Classics", "Novels"], "asin": "0679774386", "isbn": "0679774386", "isbn13": "9780679774389", "publisher": "Pantheon", "author": ["Max Hayward", "Boris Pasternak", "John Bayley", "Manya Harari"], "publishDate": 858672000000, "characters": ["Antonina Alexandrovna Gromeko", "Kologrivov", "Victor Ippolitovich Komarovsky", "Evgraf Andreevi\u010d Zivago", "Yury Andreyevich Zhivago", "Nikolay Nikolayevich Vedenyapin", "Misha Gordon", "Iosif Gimazetdinovich Galiullin", "Anna Ivanovna Gromeko", "Alexander Alexandrovich Gromeko", "Nicky Dudorov", "Pavel Pavlovich Antipov", "Rodyon Fyodorovich Guishar", "Anfim Yefimovitch Samdevyatov", "Larissa F\u00ebdorovna Antipova", "Kuprik Tiverzin", "Nadya Kologrigova", "Markel Shchapov", "Marina (Doctor Zhivago)", "Amalia Karlovna Guishar"], "places": ["Siberia", "Yuriatin", "Moscow", "Russia", "Soviet Union"], "