{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/22232.Stargirl", "title": "Stargirl", "titleComplete": "Stargirl (Stargirl, #1)", "description": "A celebration of nonconformity; a tense, emotional tale about the fleeting, cruel nature of popularity--and the thrill and inspiration of first love. Ages 12+Leo Borlock follows the unspoken rule at Mica Area High School: don't stand out--under any circumstances! Then Stargirl arrives at Mica High and everything changes--for Leo and for the entire school. After 15 years of home schooling, Stargirl bursts into tenth grade in an explosion of color and a clatter of ukulele music, enchanting the Mica student body.But the delicate scales of popularity suddenly shift, and Stargirl is shunned for everything that makes her different. Somewhere in the midst of Stargirl's arrival and rise and fall, normal Leo Borlock has tumbled into love with her.In a celebration of nonconformity, Jerry Spinelli weaves a tense, emotional tale about the fleeting, cruel nature of popularity--and the thrill and inspiration of first love.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1335947642i/22232.jpg", "genres": ["Childrens", "Teen", "School", "Contemporary", "Young Adult", "Fiction", "Middle Grade", "Realistic Fiction", "Coming Of Age", "Romance"], "asin": "0439488400", "isbn": "0439488400", "isbn13": "9780439488402", "publisher": "Scholastic", "series": ["Stargirl"], "author": ["Jerry Spinelli"], "publishDate": 1030863600000, "characters": ["Archie Brubaker", "Leo Borlock", "Stargirl Caraway"], "places": ["The United States of America", "Mica, Arizona", "Arizona"], "ratingHistogram": [12370, 28324, 80995, 101298, 100045], "ratingsCount": 323032, "reviewsCount": 16440, "numPages": 186, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Book Sense Book of the Year Award", "awardedAt": 978336000000, "category": "Children's Literature", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "South Carolina Book Award", "awardedAt": 1