{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6319.The_BFG", "title": "The BFG", "titleComplete": "The BFG", "description": "Captured by a giant! The BFG is no ordinary bone-crunching giant. He is far too nice and jumbly. It's lucky for Sophie that he is. Had she been carried off in the middle of the night by the Bloodbottler, the Fleshlumpeater, the Bonecruncher, or any of the other giants-rather than the BFG-she would have soon become breakfast. When Sophie hears that they are flush-bunking off in England to swollomp a few nice little chiddlers, she decides she must stop them once and for all. And the BFG is going to help her!", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1327872673i/6319.jpg", "genres": ["Childrens", "Humor", "Adventure", "Juvenile", "Fantasy", "Young Adult", "Fiction", "Middle Grade", "Audiobook", "Classics"], "asin": "0141311371", "isbn": "0141311371", "isbn13": "9780141311371", "publisher": "Puffin Books", "author": ["Roald Dahl", "Quentin Blake"], "publishDate": 978336000000, "characters": ["The Meatdripper", "The Bloodbottler", "The Fleshlumpeater", "the Big Friendly Giant", "The Gizzardgulper", "Mary (the BFG)", "The Manhugger", "Mr. Tibbs (the BFG)", "The Bonecruncher", "The Maidmasher", "Queen Elizabeth II", "The Childchewer", "The Butcher Boy", "Sophie (the BFG)"], "places": ["London, England", "England", "United Kingdom"], "ratingHistogram": [7438, 15284, 70485, 145129, 228852], "ratingsCount": 467188, "reviewsCount": 12171, "numPages": 199, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Zilveren Griffel", "awardedAt": 441792000000, "category": null, "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Books I Loved Best Yearly (BILBY) Awards", "awardedAt": 662716800000, "category": "Read Aloud, Read Alone", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "West Australian Young Readers' Book Award (WAYRBA)", "awardedAt": 473414400000, "category": "Younger Readers", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Red House Children's Book Award", "awarded