{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/10644930-11-22-63", "title": "11/22/63", "titleComplete": "11/22/63", "description": "On November 22, 1963, three shots rang out in Dallas, President Kennedy died, and the world changed. Unless...In 2011, Jake Epping, an English teacher from Lisbon Falls, Maine, sets out on an insane \u2014 and insanely possible \u2014 mission to prevent the Kennedy assassination.Leaving behind a world of computers and mobile phones, he goes back to a time of big American cars and diners, of Lindy Hopping, the sound of Elvis, and the taste of root beer.In this haunting world, Jake falls in love with Sadie, a beautiful high school librarian. And, as the ominous date of 11/22/63 approaches, he encounters a troubled loner named Lee Harvey Oswald...", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1327876792i/10644930.jpg", "genres": ["Time Travel", "Science Fiction", "Fantasy", "Historical", "Fiction", "Audiobook", "Mystery", "Horror", "Historical Fiction", "Thriller"], "asin": "1451627289", "isbn": "1451627289", "isbn13": "9781451663839", "publisher": "Scribner", "author": ["Stephen King"], "publishDate": 1320739200000, "characters": ["Harry Dunning", "Marina Oswald Porter", "John F. Kennedy", "Al Templeton", "Sadie Dunhill", "George de Mohrenschildt", "Richie Tozier", "Lee Harvey Oswald", "Yellow Card Man", "Beverly Marsh", "Ellen Dockerty", "Jake Epping", "Deacon \"Deke\" Simmons", "Bill Titus"], "places": ["Derry, Maine", "Jodie, Texas", "Maine"], "ratingHistogram": [5162, 12514, 56387, 178081, 267967], "ratingsCount": 520111, "reviewsCount": 46134, "numPages": 849, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Locus Award", "awardedAt": 1325404800000, "category": "Best SF Novel", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "World Fantasy Award", "awardedAt": 1325404800000, "category": "Best Novel", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "ITW Thriller Award", "awardedAt": 1325404800000, "category": "Best Hard Cover Nov