{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/7588.A_Portrait_of_the_Artist_as_a_Young_Man", "title": "A Portrait of the Artist as a Young Man", "titleComplete": "A Portrait of the Artist as a Young Man", "description": "The portrayal of Stephen Dedalus's Dublin childhood and youth, his quest for identity through art and his gradual emancipation from the claims of family, religion and Ireland itself, is also an oblique self-portrait of the young James Joyce and a universal testament to the artist's 'eternal imagination'. Both an insight into Joyce's life and childhood, and a unique work of modernist fiction, A Portrait of the Artist as a Young Man is a novel of sexual awakening, religious rebellion and the essential search for voice and meaning that every nascent artist must face in order to blossom fully into themselves.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1646339380i/7588.jpg", "genres": ["20th Century", "Classic Literature", "Literary Fiction", "Literature", "Ireland", "School", "Fiction", "Classics", "Novels", "Irish Literature"], "asin": "0142437344", "isbn": "0142437344", "isbn13": "9780142437346", "publisher": "Penguin Classics", "author": ["D\u00e1maso Alonso", "James Joyce", "Seamus Deane", "Dana Cr\u0103ciun", "Antoaneta Ralian"], "publishDate": 1048579200000, "characters": ["Fr. John Conmee", "Simon Dedalus", "Stephen Dedalus", "Mary Dedalus"], "places": ["Ireland", "Clongowes Wood College, Kildare"], "ratingHistogram": [8225, 15491, 37733, 47883, 39071], "ratingsCount": 148403, "reviewsCount": 7311, "numPages": 329, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/14905.The_Complete_Novels", "title": "The Complete Novels", "titleComplete": "The Complete Novels", "description": "Few novelists have conveyed the subtleties and nuances of their own social milieu with the wit and insight of Jane Austen. Through her vivacious and spirited heroines and their circle, she paints vivid portraits of English middle-class life as the eighteenth century came to a close. Each of the novels is a love story and a story about marriage \u2014 marriage for love, for financial security, for social status. But they are not mere romances; ironic, comic and wise, they are masterly studies of the society Jane Austen observed. The seven novels in this volume contain some of the most brilliant, dazzling prose in the English language.--back coverEmma / Lady Susan / Mansfield Park / Northanger Abbey / Persuasion / Pride and Prejudice / Sense and Sensibility", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1388178574i/14905.jpg", "genres": ["Classic Literature", "Literature", "British Literature", "Classics", "Historical", "Anthologies", "Fiction", "Historical Fiction", "Romance", "Novels"], "asin": "0140259449", "isbn": "0140259449", "isbn13": "9780140259445", "publisher": "Penguin Books", "author": ["Jane Austen"], "publishDate": 820483200000, "characters": ["John Knightley", "Fitzwilliam Darcy", "Lady Russell", "William Price", "George Wickham", "Mrs. Bennet", "Colonel Fitzwilliam", "Anne de Bourgh", "Sir John Middleton", "Cher", "Miss Bates", "Tai", "Edward Ferrars", "Sir Thomas Bertram", "Charles Bingley", "Marianne Dashwood", "Mr. Bennet", "General Tilney", "Fanny Dashwood", "Edmund Bertram", "Colonel Brandon", "Georgiana Darcy", "Julia Bertram", "Mr. Rushworth", "Mr. Yates", "Anne Elliot", "Mel Horowitz", "Henry Tilney", "Isabella Thorpe", "Lydia Bennet", "Lady Bertram", "Lady Catherine de Bourgh", "Mrs. Gardiner", "Mrs. Dashwood", "Elton", "Mr. Gardine