{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/43615.The_Gunslinger", "title": "The Gunslinger", "titleComplete": "The Gunslinger (The Dark Tower, #1)", "description": "In the first book of this series, Stephen King introduces readers to one of his most enigmatic heroes, Roland of Gilead, The Last Gunslinger. He is a haunting figure, a loner on a spellbinding journey into good and evil. In his desolate world, which frighteningly mirrors our own, Roland pursues The Man in Black, encounters an alluring woman named Alice, and begins a friendship with the Kid from Earth called Jake. Both grippingly realistic and eerily dreamlike, The Gunslinger leaves readers eagerly awaiting the next chapter.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1554220416i/43615.jpg", "genres": ["Adventure", "Science Fiction Fantasy", "Science Fiction", "Post Apocalyptic", "Fantasy", "Westerns", "Fiction", "Audiobook", "Horror", "Thriller"], "publisher": "Plume", "series": ["The Dark Tower"], "author": ["Stephen King"], "publishDate": 1057042800000, "characters": ["Jake Chambers", "Roland Deschain"], "ratingHistogram": [17152, 43138, 128682, 182765, 223080], "ratingsCount": 594817, "reviewsCount": 23866, "numPages": 231, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/18710190-allegiant", "title": "Allegiant", "titleComplete": "Allegiant (Divergent, #3)", "description": "The faction-based society that Tris Prior once believed in is shattered - fractured by violence and power struggles and scarred by loss and betrayal. So when offered a chance to explore the world past the limits she's known, Tris is ready. Perhaps beyond the fence, she and Tobias will find a simple new life together, free from complicated lies, tangled loyalties, and painful memories.But Tris's new reality is even more alarming than the one she left behind. Old discoveries are quickly rendered meaningless. Explosive new truths change the hearts of those she loves. And once again, Tris must battle to comprehend to complexities of human nature - and of herself - while facing impossible choices about courage, allegiance, sacrifice, and love.Told from a riveting dual perspective, ALLEGIANT, by #1 New York Times best-selling author Veronica Roth, brings the DIVERGENT series to a powerful conclusion while revealing the secrets of the dystopian world that has captivated millions of readers in DIVERGENT and INSURGENT.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1395582745i/18710190.jpg", "genres": ["Adventure", "Post Apocalyptic", "Science Fiction", "Teen", "Fantasy", "Young Adult", "Dystopia", "Fiction", "Audiobook", "Romance"], "asin": "0007524277", "isbn": "0007524277", "isbn13": "9780007524273", "publisher": "HarperCollins Children's Book's", "series": ["Divergent"], "author": ["Veronica Roth"], "publishDate": 1382425200000, "characters": ["Beatrice Prior", "Marcus Eaton", "Tobias Eaton", "Caleb Prior", "Peter", "Christina"], "places": ["Chicago, Illinois"], "ratingHistogram": [54100, 123729, 272748, 290677, 279180], "ratingsCount": 1020434, "reviewsCount": 70243, "numPages": 531, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Goodreads Choice Award", "awardedAt": 13570