{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/37732.Are_You_There_God_It_s_Me_Margaret", "title": "Are You There God? It's Me, Margaret", "titleComplete": "Are You There God? It's Me, Margaret", "description": "Margaret Simon, almost twelve, likes long hair, tuna fish, the smell of rain, and things that are pink. She\u2019s just moved from New York City to Farbook, New Jersey, and is anxious to fit in with her new friends\u2014Nancy, Gretchen, and Janie. When they form a secret club to talk about private subjects like boys, bras, and getting their first periods, Margaret is happy to belong.But none of them can believe Margaret doesn\u2019t have religion, and that she isn\u2019t going to the Y or the Jewish Community Center. What they don\u2019t know is Margaret has her own very special relationship with God. She can talk to God about everything\u2014family, friends, even Moose Freed, her secret crush.Margaret is funny and real, and her thoughts and feelings are oh-so-relatable\u2014you\u2019ll feel like she\u2019s talking right to you, sharing her secrets with a friend.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1388356524i/37732.jpg", "genres": ["Childrens", "Juvenile", "Banned Books", "Young Adult", "Contemporary", "Fiction", "Middle Grade", "Realistic Fiction", "Coming Of Age", "Classics"], "asin": "0689841582", "isbn": "0689841582", "isbn13": "9780689841583", "publisher": "Richard Jackson/Athaneum Books for Young Readers", "author": ["Judy Blume"], "publishDate": 999327600000, "places": ["New Jersey", "Farbrook, New Jersey", "New York City, New York"], "ratingHistogram": [4674, 12783, 53610, 80925, 78942], "ratingsCount": 230934, "reviewsCount": 11082, "numPages": 149, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Young Hoosier Book Award", "awardedAt": 189331200000, "category": "", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Nene Award", "awardedAt": 157795200000, "category": null, "hasWon": null}, {"name": "North Dakota Ch