{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/15997.Paradise_Lost", "title": "Paradise Lost", "titleComplete": "Paradise Lost", "description": "John Milton's Paradise Lost is one of the greatest epic poems in the English language. It tells the story of the Fall of Man, a tale of immense drama and excitement, of rebellion and treachery, of innocence pitted against corruption, in which God and Satan fight a bitter battle for control of mankind's destiny. The struggle rages across three worlds - heaven, hell, and earth - as Satan and his band of rebel angels plot their revenge against God. At the center of the conflict are Adam and Eve, who are motivated by all too human temptations but whose ultimate downfall is unyielding love.Marked by Milton's characteristic erudition, Paradise Lost is a work epic both in scale and, notoriously, in ambition. For nearly 350 years, it has held generation upon generation of audiences in rapt attention, and its profound influence can be seen in almost every corner of Western culture.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1526070678i/15997.jpg", "genres": ["Epic", "Philosophy", "Classic Literature", "Literature", "Religion", "Fantasy", "School", "Fiction", "Classics", "Poetry"], "asin": "0140424393", "isbn": "0140424393", "isbn13": "9780140424393", "publisher": "Penguin Classics", "author": ["John Milton"], "publishDate": 1051599600000, "characters": ["Jesus", "Belial", "Raphael (angel)", "Satan", "God", "Mammon", "Michael (angel)", "Eve", "Adam (Bible)", "Belzebub"], "places": ["Heaven", "Hell", "Eden (Biblical)"], "ratingHistogram": [6189, 13027, 36665, 50450, 54888], "ratingsCount": 161219, "reviewsCount": 5376, "numPages": 453, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Ignatz Award", "awardedAt": 1483257600000, "category": "Outstanding Artist", "hasWon": null}]}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/19380.Candide", "title": "Candide", "titleComplete": "Candide", "description": "Candide is the story of a gentle man who, though pummeled and slapped in every direction by fate, clings desperately to the belief that he lives in \"the best of all possible worlds.\" On the surface a witty, bantering tale, this eighteenth-century classic is actually a savage, satiric thrust at the philosophical optimism that proclaims that all disaster and human suffering is part of a benevolent cosmic plan. Fast, funny, often outrageous, the French philosopher's immortal narrative takes Candide around the world to discover that -- contrary to the teachings of his distinguished tutor Dr. Pangloss -- all is not always for the best. Alive with wit, brilliance, and graceful storytelling, Candide has become Voltaire's most celebrated work.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1345060082i/19380.jpg", "genres": ["Humor", "Novels", "Philosophy", "Literature", "School", "Fiction", "French Literature", "18th Century", "Classics", "France"], "asin": "0486266893", "isbn": "0486266893", "isbn13": "9780486266893", "publisher": "Dover Publications, Incorporated", "author": ["Rockwell Kent", "Walter Jerrold", "Sara Gioacchino Corcos", "Don Hagen", "Voltaire"], "publishDate": 662716800000, "characters": ["Dr. Pangloss", "Pangloss", "Candide (Voltaire)", "Cunegonde"], "places": ["Istanbul", "Portugal", "Turkey", "Lisbon", "Suriname", "Buenos Aires", "Transylvania", "Paraguay", "Romania", "Germany", "Argentina", "Netherlands", "England", "Constantinople"], "ratingHistogram": [7770, 21999, 70711, 93613, 74194], "ratingsCount": 268287, "reviewsCount": 10963, "numPages": 129, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6334.Never_Let_Me_Go", "title": "Never Let Me Go", "titleComplete": "Never Let Me Go", "description": "Hailsham seems like a pleasant English boarding school, far from the influences of the city. Its students are well tended and supported, trained in art and literature, and become just the sort of people the world wants them to be. But, curiously, they are taught nothing of the outside world and are allowed little contact with it.Within the grounds of Hailsham, Kathy grows from schoolgirl to young woman, but it\u2019s only when she and her friends Ruth and Tommy leave the safe grounds of the school (as they always knew they would) that they realize the full truth of what Hailsham is.Never Let Me Go breaks through the boundaries of the literary novel. It is a gripping mystery, a beautiful love story, and also a scathing critique of human arrogance and a moral examination of how we treat the vulnerable and different in our society. In exploring the themes of memory and the impact of the past, Ishiguro takes on the idea of a possible future to create his most moving and powerful book to date.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1353048590i/6334.jpg", "genres": ["Science Fiction", "Literary Fiction", "Literature", "Classics", "Contemporary", "Dystopia", "Fiction", "Adult", "Romance", "Novels"], "asin": "1400078776", "publisher": "Vintage Books ", "author": ["Kazuo Ishiguro"], "publishDate": 1283238000000, "characters": ["Ruth (Never Let Me Go)", "Kathy H.", "Tommy D."], "places": ["England", "Hailsham", "United Kingdom"], "ratingHistogram": [16382, 48500, 153958, 242545, 197774], "ratingsCount": 659159, "reviewsCount": 49030, "numPages": 288, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Booker Prize", "awardedAt": 1104566400000, "category": "", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Locus Award", "awardedAt": 1136102400000, "category": "Best SF Novel", "hasWon": null}, {"nam