{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/2175.Madame_Bovary", "title": "Madame Bovary", "titleComplete": "Madame Bovary", "description": "Madame Bovary is the debut novel of French writer Gustave Flaubert, published in 1856. The character lives beyond her means in order to escape the banalities and emptiness of provincial life. When the novel was first serialized in La Revue de Paris between 1 October 1856 and 15 December 1856, public prosecutors attacked the novel for obscenity. The resulting trial in January 1857 made the story notorious. After Flaubert's acquittal on 7 February 1857, Madame Bovary became a bestseller in April 1857 when it was published in two volumes. A seminal work of literary realism, the novel is now considered Flaubert's masterpiece, and one of the most influential literary works in history.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1606770119i/2175.jpg", "genres": ["Romance", "Novels", "Classic Literature", "Literature", "Fiction", "French Literature", "19th Century", "Historical Fiction", "Classics", "France"], "asin": "0192840398", "isbn": "0192840398", "isbn13": "9780192840394", "publisher": "Oxford University Press", "author": ["Margaret Mauldon", "Mark Overstall", "Gustave Flaubert", "Eleanor Marx-Aveling", "Malcolm Bowie"], "publishDate": 1072944000000, "characters": ["Rodolphe Boulanger", "Charles Bovary", "Berthe Bovary", "Monsieur Homais", "L\u00e9on Dupuis", "Emma Bovary"], "places": ["Tostes", "Rouen", "Yonville-l'Abbaye", "France"], "ratingHistogram": [11643, 30146, 86874, 109716, 84667], "ratingsCount": 323046, "reviewsCount": 15463, "numPages": 329, "language": "French"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/191139.Oh_the_Places_You_ll_Go_", "title": "Oh, the Places You'll Go!", "titleComplete": "Oh, the Places You'll Go!", "description": "For out-starting upstarts of all ages, here is a wonderfully wise and blessedly brief graduation speech from the one and only Dr. Seuss!In his inimitable, humorous verse and pictures, he addresses the Great Balancing Act (life itself, and the ups and downs it presents) while encouraging us to find the success that lies within us.\"And will you succeed?Yes! You will indeed!(98 and \u00be percent guaranteed.)\"A modern classic, Oh, the Places You'll Go! was first published one year before Dr. Seuss's death at the age of eighty-seven. In a mere fifty-six pages, Dr, Seuss managed to impart a lifetime of wisdom. It is the perfect send-off for children starting out in the maze of life, be they nursery school grads or newly-minted PhD's. Everyone will find it inspired good fun.With his unique combination of hilarious stories, zany pictures and riotous rhymes, Dr. Seuss has been delighting young children and helping them learn to read for over fifty years. Creator of the wonderfully anarchic 'Cat in the Hat', and ranked among the world's top children's authors, Dr. Seuss is a global best-seller, with nearly half a billion books sold worldwide.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1630510695i/191139.jpg", "genres": ["Childrens", "Kids", "Humor", "Inspirational", "Picture Books", "Fantasy", "Young Adult", "Fiction", "Classics", "Poetry"], "asin": "0679805273", "isbn": "0679805273", "isbn13": "9780679805274", "publisher": "Random House Books for Young Readers", "author": ["Dr. Seuss"], "publishDate": 632995200000, "ratingHistogram": [7101, 12908, 47588, 90011, 236492], "ratingsCount": 394100, "reviewsCount": 6291, "numPages": 44, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/23807.The_Silence_of_the_Lambs", "title": "The Silence of the Lambs", "titleComplete": "The Silence of the Lambs  (Hannibal Lecter, #2)", "description": "A serial murderer known only by a grotesquely apt nickname\u2014Buffalo Bill\u2014is stalking women. He has a purpose, but no one can fathom it, for the bodies are discovered in different states. Clarice Starling, a young trainee at the FBI Academy, is surprised to be summoned by Jack Crawford, chief of the Bureau's Behavioral Science section. Her assignment: to interview Dr. Hannibal Lecter\u2014Hannibal the Cannibal\u2014who is kept under close watch in the Baltimore State Hospital for the Criminally Insane.Dr. Lecter is a former psychiatrist with a grisly history, unusual tastes, and an intense curiosity about the darker corners of the mind. His intimate understanding of the killer and of Clarice herself form the core of \"The Silence of the Lambs\"\u2014an ingenious, masterfully written book and an unforgettable classic of suspense fiction.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1647930822i/23807.jpg", "genres": ["Crime", "Suspense", "Mystery Thriller", "Mystery", "Fiction", "Adult", "Horror", "Classics", "Thriller", "Novels"], "asin": "0099446782", "publisher": "Arrow Books", "series": ["Hannibal Lecter"], "author": ["Thomas  Harris"], "publishDate": 1009872000000, "characters": ["Hannibal Lecter", "Jack Crawford", "Clarice Starling"], "places": ["Washington, D.C.", "Memphis, Tennessee"], "ratingHistogram": [11678, 15509, 69754, 176299, 264746], "ratingsCount": 537986, "reviewsCount": 8929, "numPages": 421, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Bram Stoker Award", "awardedAt": 568022400000, "category": "Best Novel", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "World Fantasy Award", "awardedAt": 599644800000, "category": "Best Novel", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Anthony Award", "awardedAt": 599644800000, "category": "B