{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/13079982-fahrenheit-451", "title": "Fahrenheit 451", "titleComplete": "Fahrenheit 451", "description": "Sixty years after its original publication, Ray Bradbury\u2019s internationally acclaimed novel Fahrenheit 451 stands as a classic of world literature set in a bleak, dystopian future. Today its message has grown more relevant than ever before.Guy Montag is a fireman. His job is to destroy the most illegal of commodities, the printed book, along with the houses in which they are hidden. Montag never questions the destruction and ruin his actions produce, returning each day to his bland life and wife, Mildred, who spends all day with her television \u201cfamily.\u201d But when he meets an eccentric young neighbor, Clarisse, who introduces him to a past where people didn\u2019t live in fear and to a present where one sees the world through the ideas in books instead of the mindless chatter of television, Montag begins to question everything he has ever known.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1383718290i/13079982.jpg", "genres": ["Science Fiction", "Literature", "Fantasy", "School", "Dystopia", "Fiction", "Audiobook", "Adult", "Classics", "Novels"], "asin": "B0064CPN7I", "publisher": "Simon & Schuster", "author": ["Ray Bradbury"], "publishDate": 1322553600000, "characters": ["Clarisse McClellan", "The Mechanical Hound", "Captain Beatty", "Guy Montag", "Mildred Montag", "Professor Faber"], "ratingHistogram": [56901, 131637, 463877, 818132, 827922], "ratingsCount": 2298469, "reviewsCount": 69743, "numPages": 194, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "Prometheus Hall of Fame Award", "awardedAt": 441792000000, "category": null, "hasWon": null}, {"name": "Geffen Award", "awardedAt": 1009872000000, "category": "Best Translated SF Book", "hasWon": null}, {"name": "California Book Award", "awardedAt": -536428800000, "category": "Fiction (Silver)", "hasWon": 