{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/890.Of_Mice_and_Men", "title": "Of Mice and Men", "titleComplete": "Of Mice and Men", "description": "\n  \u201cI got you to look after me, and you got me to look after you, and that's why.\u201d\nThey are an unlikely pair: George is \"small and quick and dark of face\"; Lennie, a man of tremendous size, has the mind of a young child. Yet they have formed a \"family,\" clinging together in the face of loneliness and alienation. Laborers in California's dusty vegetable fields, they hustle work when they can, living a hand-to-mouth existence. But George and Lennie have a plan: to own an acre of land and a shack they can call their own.While the powerlessness of the laboring class is a recurring theme in Steinbeck's work of the late 1930s, he narrowed his focus when composing Of Mice and Men, creating an intimate portrait of two men facing a world marked by petty tyranny, misunderstanding, jealousy, and callousness. But though the scope is narrow, the theme is universal: a friendship and a shared dream that makes an individual's existence meaningful.A unique perspective on life's hardships, this story has achieved the status of timeless classic due to its remarkable success as a novel, a Broadway play, and three acclaimed films.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1511302904i/890.jpg", "genres": ["Novels", "Literature", "High School", "Historical", "School", "Fiction", "American", "Historical Fiction", "Classics", "Read For School"], "asin": "0142000671", "isbn": "0142000671", "isbn13": "9780142000670", "publisher": "Penguin Books", "author": ["John Steinbeck"], "publishDate": 1009872000000, "characters": ["Slim", "Candy", "Curley", "Crooks", "Whit", "Lennie Small", "Curley's Wife", "George Milton", "Carlson"], "places": ["California", "Salinas Valley, California"], "ratingHistogram": [69463, 167702, 554765, 861726, 809927], "ratingsCount": 2463583, "reviewsCou