{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/8127.Anne_of_Green_Gables", "title": "Anne of Green Gables", "titleComplete": "Anne of Green Gables (Anne of Green Gables, #1)", "description": "This heartwarming story has beckoned generations of readers into the special world of Green Gables, an old-fashioned farm outside a town called Avonlea. Anne Shirley, an eleven-year-old orphan, has arrived in this verdant corner of Prince Edward Island only to discover that the Cuthberts\u2014elderly Matthew and his stern sister, Marilla\u2014want to adopt a boy, not a feisty redheaded girl. But before they can send her back, Anne\u2014who simply must have more scope for her imagination and a real home\u2014wins them over completely. A much-loved classic that explores all the vulnerability, expectations, and dreams of a child growing up, Anne of Green Gables is also a wonderful portrait of a time, a place, a family\u2026 and, most of all, love. WITH AN AFTERWORD BY JENNIFER LEE CARELL", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1615094578i/8127.jpg", "genres": ["Childrens", "Coming Of Age", "Historical", "Young Adult", "Fiction", "Middle Grade", "Audiobook", "Canada", "Historical Fiction", "Classics"], "asin": "0451528824", "isbn": "0451528824", "isbn13": "9780451528827", "publisher": "Signet", "series": ["Anne of Green Gables"], "author": ["L.M. Montgomery"], "publishDate": 1052204400000, "characters": ["Diana Barry", "Prissy Andrews", "Rachel Lynde", "Mrs. Allan", "Mr. Phillips", "Gilbert Blythe", "Marilla Cuthbert", "Anne Shirley", "Josie Pye", "Muriel Stacey", "Matthew Cuthbert", "Ruby Gillis", "Jane Andrews"], "places": ["Prince Edward Island", "Canada", "Avonlea, Prince Edward Island"], "ratingHistogram": [14913, 29599, 120426, 266637, 509996], "ratingsCount": 941571, "reviewsCount": 36710, "numPages": 320, "language": "English"}
{"url": "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/24280.Les_Mis_rables", "title": "Les Mis\u00e9rables", "titleComplete": "Les Mis\u00e9rables", "description": "Victor Hugo's tale of injustice, heroism and love follows the fortunes of Jean Valjean, an escaped convict determined to put his criminal past behind him. But his attempts to become a respected member of the community are constantly put under threat: by his own conscience, when, owing to a case of mistaken identity, another man is arrested in his place; and by the relentless investigations of the dogged Inspector Javert. It is not simply for himself that Valjean must stay free, however, for he has sworn to protect the baby daughter of Fantine, driven to prostitution by poverty.", "imageUrl": "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/books/1411852091i/24280.jpg", "genres": ["Romance", "Novels", "Classic Literature", "Literature", "Historical", "Fiction", "French Literature", "Historical Fiction", "Classics", "France"], "publisher": "Penguin", "author": ["Norman MacAfee", "Charles E. Wilbour", "Lee Fahnestock", "Victor Hugo", "Isabel Florence Hapgood"], "publishDate": 541756800000, "characters": ["Cosette", "Fantine", "Bossuet", "Gavroche", "Bishop Myriel", "M. & Mme. Th\u00e9nardier", "Jean Valjean", "Bahorel", "Enjolras", "Combeferre", "Grantaire", "Azelma", "Fauchelevent", "Mademoiselle Gillenorman", "Champmathieu", "Javert", "Marius Pontmercy", "Felix Tholomy\u00e8s", "Toussaint", "\u00c9ponine"], "places": ["Montreuil", "Paris", "France", "Digne"], "ratingHistogram": [18665, 32416, 112049, 230308, 388068], "ratingsCount": 781506, "reviewsCount": 22076, "numPages": 1463, "language": "English", "awards": [{"name": "French-American Foundation Translation Prize", "awardedAt": 1420099200000, "category": "Fiction (Christine Donougher)", "hasWon": null}]}
